title: pound cake
directions: Cream margarine, powdered sugar, and eggs, (one at a time). Beat well after each addition. Add vanilla, and
flour. Beat well.

title: chocolate supreme delight
directions: Find your favorite brownie recipe from Silver Palate or from Baker's chocolate box.
Get old-fashioned hot fudge sauce (like Mrs. Richardsons) and make your own fresh whipped cream or buy the natural Reddi-Wip variety.
Get a solid bar of chocolate and shave swirls off it over the top.
Serve with hot coffee in you favorite flavor with lots of cream.
Great chocolate lover's treat.

title: pea casserole supreme
directions: Mix all ingredients together except bread crumbs.
Microwave 10 minutes on High setting.
Sprinkle bread crumbs on top or cracker crumbs and lightly brown in oven.

title: watergate salad
directions: Dump all ingredients, except marshmallows and cherries, into a large bowl.
Add marshmallows to taste and mix together.
Place into a serving dish and garnish with well-drained cherries.

title: cookie bars
directions: Melt butter in cake pan; add crumbs. Stir until mixed.
Add milk, coconut, chips and walnuts.
Stir just a little.
Bake at 350°
for 20 minutes or to a doneness you like.
Will get hard on the edges.

title: stuffed picnic rolls
directions: Cook until meat is browned and onions soft.
Drain fat and stir in next 3 ingredients.
Remove from heat.
Spread one side of rolls with mustard.
Fill buns with mixture.
Cover tightly with foil and heat slowly to serve.

title: blueberry cheese strata
directions: Layer half of bread cubes, blueberries, sugar, cheese and remaining bread cubes in buttered 8-inch square baking dish. Combine eggs, milk, vanilla and salt; mix well.
Pour mixture over bread; sprinkle with cinnamon.
Cover and refrigerate for 6 to 24 hours.
Uncover and bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes or until knife blade inserted near center comes out clean.
Let stand for 10 minutes before serving.
Top with yogurt or sour cream. Garnish with mint.

title: hershey bar cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour in 3 layer cake pans. Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes or until done.

title: chewy cake
directions: Melt butter over low heat.
Add brown sugar, eggs and flour together.
Mix well.
Add dates, raisins and nuts to flour mixture.
Pour into greased pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fitzwilliam inn ice cream ball
directions: Roll large scoop of ice cream in mixture and serve with favorite topping sauce.

title: scuppernong pie
directions: Stir all ingredients together in a saucepan and cook over low heat until well blended.
Remove from heat and let cool while you prepare pie shell.
Pour mixture into unbaked pie shell and cover with unbaked pie crust either completely or with lattice.
Bake in preheated 400° oven for approximately 10 minutes, until slightly brown.
Turn down to 325° and continue 30 minutes or until firm and golden.

title: fresh or freezer slaw
directions: Mix the vegetables, add 1 tablespoon salt and let stand 1 hour.
Boil
sugar	and
vinegar
with spices for 5 minutes. Pour over cabbage mixture.
Let cool.
Pack and freeze.

title: sarah's mandarin salad
directions: In a small skillet melt 3 tablespoons sugar over low heat. Add almonds; stir until coated.
Cool, break into small pieces and set side.
In a jar with a tight fitting lid, combine next six ingredients and remaining sugar; shake well.
Just before serving, combine lettuce, oranges, onions and almonds in a large salad bowl.
Shake dressing; pour over salad and toss.
Yield:
4 to 6 servings.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix pudding and Cool Whip, then other ingredients.

title: barbecue-seasoned drumsticks
directions: Rinse chicken; pat dry.
Stir together mustard and water. Brush drumsticks with the mustard mixture. Stir together cheese, bread crumbs, barbecue sauce and paprika.
Dip each drumstick in coating mixture.
Arrange drumsticks in baking dish.
Sprinkle with remaining coating mixture.
Bake until chicken is no longer pink.
Serves 3.

title: luscious fruit dessert
directions: Beat egg whites and baking powder. Add sugar and beat. Add nuts. Add to Ritz crackers. Press into greased 9 x 13 pan. Bake for 10 minutes at 350°. Cool thoroughly.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes, or until set in the middle.

title: oatmeal crisps
directions: Thoroughly cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla. Beat well. Add sifted dry ingredients, nuts and oats.
Mix. Form in long roll. Chill thoroughly.
Slice in 1/4-inch pieces. Bake on ungreased cookie sheet in moderate oven at 350° for 10 minutes. Make 5 dozen.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Line bottom of an ungreased 13x9 inch baking dish with 1/3 honey grahams crackers. Whisk together pudding mix and milk; add whipped topping, stirring until mixture thickens. Spread half of pudding mixture over graham crackers. Repeat layers with 1/3
of graham crackers and remaining pudding mixture. Top with remaining graham crackers. Spread
with chocolate frosting. Cover and chill 8 hours.

title: navajo tacos
directions: Roll each biscuit out just to flatten.
Place in hot oil, frying to ensure center is not doughy.
Heat chili until hot. Place fry bread (biscuit) on plate, spoon chili on top.
Add cheese, lettuce, tomatoes, onions, sour cream, olives and whatever you desire.

title: haussner's crab imperial
directions: Pick over crabmeat to remove any shells. Cut bread into cubes. Combine eggs, mayonnaise, mustard, salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce. Add bread and parsley. Fold in crabmeat carefully to prevent breaking.
Spoon into individual baking dishes. Top with Cream Sauce. Sprinkle with paprika. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: squash medley with tomatoes
directions: Saute onions in half of butter.
Cook squash.
Combine cooked squash, sauteed onions, tomatoes, cheese, salt and pepper.
Place mixture into one greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Melt remaining butter, add bread crumbs and stir until browned.
Spread bread crumbs over top of squash mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar. Add eggs and vanilla. Mix in flour, salt, baking powder and baking soda.

title: black bottom pie
directions: Combine sugar and cornstarch.
Add scalded milk to egg yolks; add to sugar mixture. Cook until spoon is coated.
Add 1 cup to chocolate bits.
Add vanilla.
Pour in shell.
Soften gelatin in cold water and add to remaining hot custard.
Stir until dissolved.
Chill.
Fold in egg whites to which 1/4 cup sugar has been added.
Add rum.
Pour over chocolate mixture.
Garnish with whipped cream and chocolate.

title: cherry congealed salad
directions: Mix cherries, sugar and water; bring to a boil.
Pour over gelatin, stirring to dissolve.
Add pineapple, pecans and Coca-Cola.
Chill.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Boil sugar and water for 5 minutes.
Add cranberries.
Cook until cranberries burst; add Jell-O.
Remove from heat.
Add pineapple and pecans.
Chill.

title: mormon rolls
directions: Mix well.
Add to starter.
Feed starter every 3 to 5 days, possibly a week with the ingredients.
Allow to stand out of refrigerator all day (8 to 12 hours).
Mixture will be bubbly. Stir well and remove 1 cup starter to use and return remainder to refrigerator until time to feed again.
If not making bread that day, separate or give to friend.
This is to avoid deflating your starter.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Bring to a boil.
Add chicken; cook on low for 1 hour.
(Sauce is good as gravy.)

title: orange balls
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Form small balls.
Roll in powdered sugar and/or crushed coconut.

title: snow cookies(club member: john waters)
directions: Cream margarine and add powdered sugar and vanilla. Work in flour and add nuts. Make into rounded flattened balls.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes. When cool, roll in powdered sugar.

title: simply delightful
directions: Use 9 or 10-inch round cake pan(s).

title: cornbread pie
directions: Brown meat in shortening using heavy iron skillet.
Add onion, 1 teaspoon salt, chili powder, Worcestershire sauce, soup and water and bring to boil.
Mix cornmeal, buttermilk, 1/2 teaspoon salt, soda, egg and corn.
Pour over chili mixture and bake 20 minutes at 400°.
Serves 6.

title: griddle cakes (pancakes)
directions: Combine all ingredients except flour.
Mix well with hand mixer.
Gradually add flour.
Beat until batter is smooth.
Grease skillet lightly for first pancakes only if you are not using a nonstick skillet.
Pour batter when droplets of water put on griddle dance around.
Flip pancakes when puffy and bubbly.

title: raw vegetable salad
directions: Break vegetables into bite size pieces.
Add thawed peas.
Mix sour cream dressing mix and mayonnaise.
Pour over vegetables and refrigerate.

title: cherry trifle(low-fat, sugar-free)
directions: Tear angel food cake into bite size pieces.
Put into trifle bowl.
Prepare pudding according to package directions.
Mix whipped topping with pudding and pour over cake.
Spoon cherry pie filling over top.
Chill and serve.
Serves 6.

title: seasoned fried chicken
directions: Add seasonings to flour in a Ziploc bag (add a little more than to taste).
Shake bag to mix dry ingredients.
Flour chicken strips by putting in bag and shaking.
Fry in a deep fryer until done!

title: spanish dessert
directions: Drain syrup from fruit cocktail.
Put fruit cocktail in a large bowl.
Add Philadelphia cream cheese to fruit cocktail (microwave cheese for approximately 30 seconds first to soften). Mix thoroughly.
Add 1/2 cup of sweetened milk and mix thoroughly. Chill in refrigerator for 1 hour.
Serve.

title: never-fail hot rolls
directions: Put in a small bowl, warm water, sugar and yeast; let set 15 minutes.
Put in a large bowl, flour and salt.
Mix yeast mixture into flour.
Knead about 3 minutes.
Remove any leftover flour. Grease the bowl and dough.
Let rise to double the amount; knead down.
Let rise again.
Make into light rolls.
Also makes delicious cinnamon rolls.
Will keep a week in refrigerator.
Just knead down each day and bake as desired.

title: meaty cheese dip
directions: Brown ground chuck and sausage in a large skillet, stirring until it crumbles.
Drain and return to skillet.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until cheese melts.
Serve warm with tortilla chips.

title: bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease loaf pan.
Mix the 3 tablespoons sugar, dash of salt, whole wheat flour and wheat germ. Add the baking soda and baking powder.
Blend.
Knead in the 3 tablespoons of butter.
Stir in the milk; mix well.
Turn into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Mix butter, sugar, eggs, vanilla and sour cream; mix well, then add flour.
Mix together.
Bake at 250° to 275° for 2 hours.

title: hypocrite pie
directions: Spread cooked apples to cover bottom of pie shell. To beaten eggs, add milk, sugar and vanilla. Blend well. Pour over apples. Bake in a 425° oven for 10 minutes. Reduce heat to 350° and bake for about 40 minutes or until topping is set.

title: apple squares
directions: Use own pie dough on cobbler pan (15 x 10 x 1-inch).
Mix first four ingredients thoroughly and spread over pie dough.
Bake 20 minutes at 425°.
Cool.

title: crab pate
directions: Heat soup in a medium saucepan over low heat.
Remove from heat.
Dissolve gelatin in cold water.
Add to soup, stirring well.
Add next 5 ingredients and mix well.
Spoon into an oiled 4 cup mold.
Chill until firm.
Unmold and garnish with parsley sprigs.
Serve with assorted crackers.
Yields about 4 cups.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown steak and drain.
Add onions, mushrooms and seasonings; cook 5 minutes or until onions are tender.
Add sour cream, stir over low heat until thoroughly heated.
Place noodles on serving platter and top with meat mixture.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix and roll into balls.
Cook at 350° until light brown.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan and let set.

title: never fail rolls
directions: Mix together water, sugar and yeast.
Add 2 cups flour and salt, then add eggs, oil and remaining flour.
Mix well; let rise about 2 hours.
Knead dough and put in pans.
Let rise again and bake at 450° for 12 minutes or until done.

title: percolator punch
directions: Place all liquid into an electric percolator.
Place brown sugar, cloves and cinnamon sticks in basket.
Turn on and heat. Great for Fall/Winter get togethers!

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl.
Pour into pie crust and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: miss maude's soft molasses cookies
directions: Blend eggs, sugar, Crisco and molasses. Sift in flour, ginger, baking soda and salt. Stir in boiling water and mix well. Drop mixture by spoonfuls onto greased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Yields 4 to 5 dozen.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions on the box; drain.
Add the cucumber, green pepper, celery, onion and eggs.
Stir.
Make a dressing using the mayonnaise, milk, mustard, vinegar and sugar. Pour over macaroni.
Stir well.
Chill.

title: sauerkraut balls
directions: Saute 1 onion, finely chopped in 3 tablespoons butter.
Add meat and garlic.
Heat all well.
Stir in 6 tablespoons flour and egg; continue to cook, stirring until mixture is well blended.
Add sauerkraut, thoroughly drained and ground in food chopper.
Add seasoning and beef stock and cook until the mixture forms a thick paste.
Spread the paste on a platter to cool and chill well. Shape the mixture into 1-inch balls.
Dip the balls into a batter made of 2 cups milk and 2 1/2 cups flour.
Roll them in fine dry bread crumbs.
Fry the balls in deep hot fat, 375°, to a rich brown.

title: joyce's fudge
directions: Mix.
Heat in microwave on High for 2 minutes.
Stir.
Spread in lightly greased 8 x 8-inch pan until set.
Makes 12 pieces.

title: lemon tart
directions: Cream together. Put in pan. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Cool.

title: raw salad
directions: Mix the cleaned and
prepared
vegetables together in a large bowl.
Add the
Italian
dressing and toss well.
Better to let stand overnight.
Lasts for days.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Peel and slice eggplant.
Dip into flour and egg.
Fry on both sides until golden brown.
Set aside on paper towels to drain. Brown hamburg and drain grease.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients in a medium mixing bowl.
Cook in microwave for 4 minutes on High, then stir good.
Continue cooking for 3 more minutes.
Add the oleo; mix well.
Cook on High for 3 minutes.
Take out and add the vanilla and baking soda; mix together.
Pour onto greased cookie sheet; spread out thin.
Cool 20 minutes, then break up.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Beat well oleo, oil, sugar and salt.
Add eggs, soda, cream of tartar, vanilla, lemon flavor and flour.
Chill.
Roll in small balls.
Press down tops with glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350°. These are delicious and store well.

title: joyce's chocolate cake
directions: Bake German chocolate cake according to package directions. Cool completely.
After cake is cool, drizzle can of Eagle Brand milk over top and then drizzle jar of butterscotch topping over that.
Frost with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with Heath bar crumbs.

title: cereal clusters
directions: Melt butter in heavy pan.
Stir in sugar 4 or 5 minutes until sugar melts.
Mixture may separate.
Cook an additional 1 to 2 minutes.
Add cereal.
Mix to coat quickly.
Spread on ungreased cookie sheet.
Cool completely.
Break into bite size pieces. Store in airtight container.

title: chocolate spiders
directions: Melt chips in double boiler or in microwave; add nuts and noodles.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper.
Let set, then store in airtight container.

title: cherry spice cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into 2 greased and floured pans.

title: apple pudding with nutmeg sauce
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg, beating well.
Combine dry ingredients and apples.
Add to creamed mixture, mixing well. Stir in nuts.
Pour mixture into a lightly greased, shallow 1-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Serve with Nutmeg Sauce.

title: no crust coconut pie
directions: Melt butter, add sugar and flour.
Beat in eggs, then milk and flavoring; mix well.
Add coconut and mix well.
Pour into 2 well-greased pie pans and bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: bailey's irish cream
directions: Mix Kahlua, vanilla, cocoa and coconut extract.
Make sure all dissolves.
Mix in rest of the ingredients using wire whip.
Do not beat or use blender.
Chill well and enjoy.

title: avocado pie
directions: Combine avocados, milk and lemon juice in a blender.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Refrigerate about 3 hours.
Top with whipped cream.
Top with grated chocolate or chocolate pieces.

title: dandelion wine
directions: Pick flowers only.
Wash well and drain.
In crock or wine making container, put a layer of flowers, then oranges and lemon. Repeat until all are used up.
Boil the water and pour over all. Let stand, covered for 36 hours, stirring each day.
Strain and return to crock.
Add sugar and yeast, mixing well.
Stir 3 or 4 times a day until it stops fermenting.
Keep covered well at all times.
Let wine sit for 3 or 4 weeks and strain again.
Discard the sediment in the bottom of crock and return wine to crock. Cover.
Let sit for 2 more weeks.
Strain and discard sediment. You may now put wine in bottles, loosely corked at first.

title: darlene's shrimp mousse
directions: Heat soup to boiling.
Take 2 tablespoons of hot soup and dissolve gelatin.
Mix onion, celery, cheese and mayonnaise.
Add soup and mix.
Add shrimp.
Pour into well oiled mold. Refrigerate.
Good served with Triscuits.
Can be made 2 to 3 days in advance.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients, then add oil, egg and milk.
Mix well. Put 1/2 teaspoon oil in iron skillet and get hot, then put mix in. Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: crunchy cheese sandwiches
directions: Measure Rice Krispies cereal.
Crunch to 1 1/2 cups.
Place in shallow dish or pan.
Set aside.
Make 4 sandwiches using 1 slice cheese and 2 slices bread for each.
Set aside.
In a second shallow dish or pan, beat eggs, milk and salt until foamy.
Dip sandwiches quickly in egg mixture, turning once.
Coat with crushed cereal.
Place in single layer on well-greased baking sheet.
Drizzle with melted margarine.
Bake in oven at 450° for about 15 minutes or until crisp and golden brown.
Yield: 4 servings.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Cream the first 3 ingredients together.
Add last 3 ingredients.
Beat all together until smooth.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: maggie's chocolate cake
directions: Cream margarine and add sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time. Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Add dry ingredients and syrup alternately.
Add vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or 325° for 40 minutes.

title: ma jones' pork chops
directions: Place the pork chops in a single layer in a baking dish.
Salt and pepper.
Chop onion and green pepper and put over chops.
Pour juice over and cover.
Bake at 350° until tender, approximately 1 1/2 to 2 hours, depending on size of chops.
Uncover the last half hour.

title: no crust coconut pie
directions: Mix together and pour into a 10-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: strawberry french toast
directions: Spread 1 tablespoon cream cheese on each of 6 slices of bread; spread 1 1/2 teaspoons jam over cream cheese.
Top with remaining bread.

title: chicken salad
directions: Toss together the chicken, celery, lemon juice and seasoning. Mix in mayonnaise.
Carefully fold in eggs.
Chill thoroughly.

title: best ever chicken pie
directions: Cook chicken until real tender.
Remove from bones and save broth.
Cut chicken into bite size pieces and put in 3-quart oblong baking dish.
Put soup and broth in pot and bring to a boil.
In bowl, combine melted margarine, pepper, flour and buttermilk.
Mix real well into a real good batter.
Pour broth over chicken.
Spoon batter over top and spread over chicken.
Bake at 400° to 425° for 25 to 30 minutes (uncovered) until brown.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Pour into a greased and floured pan. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: beefy baked beans
directions: Cook ground beef until browned, stirring to crumble meat. Drain well.

title: carrot bars
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool and frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: west virginia biscuits
directions: Combine water, sugar, yeast and shortening.
Mix in flour to make a workable dough.
Turn out on floured surface and roll to biscuit height, about 1/2 inch.
Cut out biscuits and place on greased sheet.
Let rise for 1 hour in warm place.
Bake in 425° oven for about 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Brown sausage and large onion.
Drain that.
Add cheese and hot peppers.
Mix corn bread mix, eggs and corn.
Pour 1/2 of corn bread mixture in greased pan.
Spread sausage mixture over top of that.
Add rest of remaining bread mixture.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: pickled eggs
directions: Heat ingredients to boiling and add eggs.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Place eggs in jars.
Pour hot mixture over and seal.

title: snowballs hawaiian style
directions: Combine baking mix, cinnamon, egg, baby food, and brown sugar. Mix well. Heat oil to 375 degrees. Drop batter form teaspoon into oil. Fry until brown and drain on absorbent paper. Cool for about 15 to 20 minutes and then coat with confectioners' sugar. These are a cross between fritters and doughnuts.

title: fruit cake
directions: Cube fruit and chop nuts (not fine) and place in a very large bowl or pan.
Cover with 2 cups self-rising flour.
Dredge or mix with hands to cover all fruit and nuts with flour.
Melt the butter or margarine.
Beat the eggs and sugar into the butter. Pour over the fruit.
Mix thoroughly until all is covered with butter mixture.
Grease and line 2 tube pans or 3 to 4 loaf pans with wax paper. Bake 3 hours at 250°.
Wrap in foil or plastic bags.
Store in cake tins in refrigerator.
Will keep indefinitely.
Freezes well.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake in loaf pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: pineapple icebox pie
directions: Mix together and put in 2 graham cracker crusts and chill.

title: eclair cake
directions: Layer 1/3 graham crackers in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine pudding and 3 cups milk; beat at low speed until well blended. Fold in Cool Whip.
Spoon 1/2 of mixture onto crackers.
Repeat layer of crackers and pudding, then end with crackers on top.

title: fig cake
directions: Mix well, starting with liquids.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Mix together.
Put on top of cream cheese mixture.
Top with cheese and olives.
I used 4 ounce package shredded Mozzarella cheese and salad olives.

title: beef and bacon shish kabobs
directions: In small bowl, blend steak sauce, sherry and honey. Place beef cubes into non-metal dish; coat with 1/4 cup steak mixture. Cover, chill 1 hour, stirring occasionally.

title: toll house pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In large bowl, beat eggs until foamy. Add flour, sugar and brown sugar.
Beat until well blended.
Blend in melted butter.
Stir in chocolate morsels.
Cook 1 hour.

title: frozen salad
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Fold in Cool Whip and chopped pecans.
Place into long casserole dish and put in freezer.
Remove 20 minutes before serving.

title: venison swiss steak
directions: Salt, pepper and cover steak in flour.
Put cooking oil in large skillet.
Sear meat on both sides until skillet is coated with brown flour.
Add Worcestershire sauce and sprinkle with garlic salt.
Now add onion, green pepper and water to cover meat. Simmer until meat is tender.
May need to add more water to keep the gravy from getting too thick.

title: swedish cookies
directions: Roll in small balls and press down with a fork.
Bake at 350° to 375°.

title: caramel icing
directions: Combine sugars, soda and cream.
Cook stirring constantly, to 238° or until a small amount forms a soft ball when dropped in cold water.
Cool to lukewarm without stirring.
Beat until creamy, add unbeaten egg white and beat until thick enough to spread.
Will frost 3 (8-inch) layers.

title: peanut butter fudge(microwave)
directions: Microwave Parkay and peanut butter for 3 minutes on High. Stir well. Add powdered sugar. Keep stirring well.
Work onto a lightly greased cookie sheet.
Let set up for 1 1/2 to 2 hours and cut.

title: potato skins
directions: Toss together ingredients in bowl with lid and shake. Spread on baking sheet. Bake at 400 degrees for 25 minutes. In the last 5 minutes add shredded cheese and crumbled bacon. Continue to heat until cheese is melted. Serve with sour cream.

title: mother's tea cakes
directions: Have all ingredients at room temperature.
Cream together butter, shortening, sugar and flavoring.
Add eggs and cream until fluffy.
Sift together dry ingredients. Stir into mixture until smooth.
Blend in buttermilk.
Drop by teaspoonful onto greased cookie sheet. Flatten with bottom of glass dipped in sugar. Bake at 400° for about 12 minutes. Cool.
This will make about 5 dozen cookies.

title: baked beans
directions: Fry onions; add hamburg.
Drain fat.
Simmer 20 minutes with seasonings.
Add 12 ounce can of beans.
Bake in oven until bubbles.

title: quick n' chewy crescent roll bars
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Unroll crescent rolls and place in 10 x 15-inch ungreased pan.
Press on bottom.
Pour condensed milk over.
Sprinkle with frosting mix.
Drizzle with margarine.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes.
Cool.
Cut in bars.

title: watermelon cake
directions: Mix angel food cake mix, using directions on box.
Put a small amount of white cake around sides and bottom of angel food cake pan.
Mix red food coloring with rest of mixture.
Pour rest in pan.
Add chocolate chips to make seeds.
Bake.
Frost with green frosting when cool.

title: flavor craver dip
directions: Blend Heinz chili sauce gradually into cream cheese.
Mix in mayonnaise, onion and horseradish. Fold in shrimp. Cover and chill at least 1 hour.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.
Serve with ridged potato chips.

title: mud slide pie
directions: Bottom Layer:
Combine butter, flour and pecans until well blended.
Spread mixture over bottom of a 3-quart casserole pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes and cool.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar and oil and mix well.
Mix dry ingredients and add to egg mixture.
Add nuts.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes.

title: souffle
directions: Mix ingredients. Cook at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: creamy coconut pie
directions: Combine cream cheese, sugar, milk and coconut in blender at low speed for 30 seconds.
Fold in whipped cream; add vanilla. Spoon into crust.
Freeze until firm, about 4 hours.
Store leftovers in freezer.

title: meat balls and spaghetti
directions: Mix all together.
Form into balls.
Fry in olive oil.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix well and cook until thickens the first 5 ingredients, then add butter, vanilla and coconut.
Beat well.
Pour into prebaked 9-inch pie shell.
Cover with meringue or Cool Whip.

title: johnny marzetti
directions: Cook and drain noodles.
Brown and drain beef and onions.
Mix tomato ingredients and spices.
Layer in a greased casserole, tomato mixture, noodles, beef and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: shredded wheat bread
directions: Crumble Shredded Wheat biscuits and pour over them milk and water.
Add 1/2 cup molasses.
Add lard and salt; let stand until cool.
Add yeast dissolved in warm water.
Stir in flour, knead and let rise double; poke down and shape into 2 large or 3 small loaves.
Bake for 50 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: cranberry-apple salad
directions: Using a large boiler or saucepan, melt cranberry sauce over medium heat.
Once the sauce has liquified, stir well and reduce heat.
Mix into the sauce liquid, 1 cup boiling water and the jello.
Stir until gelatin is completely dissolved.
Add lemon juice and salt.
Add to this mixture, the mayonnaise.
Beat with hand beater, not electric mixer, until all ingredients are smooth. Fold in the diced apple and chopped pecans.
Pour into a greased mold.
(Use a dapple of mayonnaise to coat inside of mold.)
Chill overnight, covered.
This is great with Thanksgiving dressing.

title: jewish apple cake
directions: Mix 5 tablespoons sugar, cinnamon and apples and set aside. Sift together salt, flour, baking powder and sugar.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix oil, vanilla, eggs and orange juice in bowl.
Add flour mixture and mix until blended.
Layer mix and apples in greased and floured pan (3 layers of each, beginning with mix and ending with apples).
Bake 1 hour or longer, if necessary.

title: magnificent macaroni salad
directions: Boil macaroni according to package directions.
Drain and rinse in cold water to help chill.
Dice tomato, pepper and onion. In large mixing bowl, add macaroni, diced vegetables, pickle relish and spices.
Toss until spices are distributed evenly.
Add mayonnaise and mix thoroughly.
Chill in refrigerator at least 1 hour before serving.

title: salsa chicken
directions: In large skillet, brown chicken in oil; pour off fat.
Add salsa and heat to a boil.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes or until done, turning chicken (six boneless chicken breasts may be substituted).
Simmer for 15 minutes or until done.
Makes 6 servings.

title: helen's potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes just until soft (cook with skins on).
Let cool. Then grate potatoes and raw onion.
In separate bowl, mix sour cream, mayo, milk and lemon juice.
Mix potato and onion with sour cream mixture, adding seasonings to taste.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: peach cake
directions: Mix peaches, sugar and fruit protector; set aside.
Mix cake mix, pudding mix, water, eggs and oil; beat 2 minutes.
Drain peaches.
Grease and flour a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Put half the batter in pan.
Place peaches on batter; add rest of batter.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Cool 15 minutes before removing from pan.
When cool, frost.

title: christmas morning italian strata
directions: Night Before Serving:
Grease a 13 x 9-inch glass baking pan. In a 10-inch skillet, over medium heat, cook sausage, stirring frequently to break up meat, until done.
Drain on paper towels. Cut French bread into 1/2-inch cubes.
Drain and chop mushrooms. In a baking dish, combine sausage, bread cubes and mushrooms.
In a large bowl, whisk together eggs, milk, Italian seasonings, garlic powder and pepper.
Pour egg mixture over sausage mixture.
Cover with wrap and refrigerate overnight.

title: "no-peeky" chicken(one dish casserole)
directions: Grease a large cake pan.
Put dry rice, mushroom soup and chicken soup into the greased pan and stir enough to mix.
Place chicken pieces on top.
Sprinkle with dry onion soup mix.
Cover with foil and don't peek!
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: black forest cake
directions: Mix cake mix, baking soda, eggs and oil for 2 minutes on medium speed.
Fold in pie filling.
Bake in 325° oven for 45 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan or a Bundt pan.

title: do nothing cake
directions: Put all ingredients in a bowl, one at a time.
Mix with a spoon.
Bake in
a	9 x 13 x 2-inch pan at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes or until done.

title: peggy's biscuits
directions: Mix flour and shortening by cutting shortening into flour.
Do this by using two table knives and moving them back and forth until mixture is crumbly.
Add milk; mix well.
Roll onto floured surface.
Cut with biscuit cutter.
Place into greased pan.
Bake at 450° until the biscuits rise and turn brown, about 10 minutes.

title: blueberry-orange bread
directions: Boil together the orange peel, salt, sugar and 1 cup water to make a thin syrup, about 20 minutes.
Cool and remove peel. Measure and add enough water to make 1 1/2 cups.
Add melted shortening and eggs.
Add flour with baking powder.
Mix thoroughly.
Gently fold in blueberries.
Put into a well-greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake in a preheated oven at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Turn out and cool on a rack.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Place chicken in single layer in 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Mix the dressing, preserves and onion soup mix together.
Spread evenly over chicken.
Cover and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Remove cover during last 20 minutes of baking time.
Add pineapple and green pepper at this time if you wish.

title: english toffee candy
directions: Melt butter in heavy saucepan over high heat.
Add sugar and stir until dissolved, then add water.
Continue cooking over high heat for 10 minutes or until mixture starts to change color.
Stir constantly with a wooden spoon.
At color turn, add 2 cups of nuts. Cook about 5 minutes.
Butter may separate; remove from heat and mix until consistency returns.
Pour into large buttered cookie sheet; spread to make thin.
Cool.
Melt chips.
Spread 1/2 mixture over cooled candy and dust with 1/2 nuts.
Turn pan over and do the same.
Break into bite size pieces after dry.

title: butter cookies(approximately 4 dozen)
directions: Cream butter, sugar and vanilla well.
Mix flour.
Add about three drops yellow color.
Drop 1/2 teaspoonful on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten with fork.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: happy husband cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Melt butter in 2-quart baking dish. Mix dry ingredients; add milk.
Pour into pan.
Pour peaches on top.
Bake for 45 minutes.
The batter will rise to the top when done.

title: summer salad
directions: Mix all together and chill until Jell-O is set.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Melt marshmallows in double boiler; add milk and stir.
Then pour over other ingredients.
Mix well.
Place a round Tupperware glass in the middle of wax paper.
Pour mixture around cup; shape with whole pecans, then remove cup.
Wrap cake in aluminum foil and refrigerate.

title: sausage balls
directions: Melt cheese and mix with Bisquick and sausage.
Shape into balls and bake 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: sunny fruit salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Blend in remaining ingredients.
Pour into a large slightly greased salad bowl or 10-inch square dish.
Chill until set.
Unmold onto serving platter.

title: one dish meal
directions: Brown turkey, celery and onion, then add remaining ingredients.
Place in casserole and bake at 350°
for 45 minutes.

title: easy toffee
directions: Line jelly roll pan with foil; butter well.
Arrange 35 saltines in single layer in bottom of pan.
In saucepan, bring to a boil the oleo and brown sugar.
Boil 4 minutes, stirring constantly.
Pour over crackers immediately; spread smoothly. Bake 5 minutes in 350° to 400° oven.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips.
When chips are soft, spread evenly and allow to cool. Break into pieces and serve.

title: banana nugget cookies
directions: Sift flour, sugar, baking soda, salt, nutmeg and cinnamon into a bowl.
Cream in shortening; blend well.
Add eggs, bananas, oatmeal and chocolate chips.
Bake on an ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into a large loaf pan. Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes at 325°.

title: hamburger stew
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; drain.
Add water, carrots, potatoes, celery, tomatoes, salt and pepper.
Cook until tender, about 1 to 2 hours.
Add brown sugar during last 15 minutes of cooking.

title: german chocolate cake icing
directions: Cook on low heat. Do not let stick. Cook for 15 or 20 minutes, or until thick.

title: old fashioned salmon patties
directions: Mix salmon with juice in bowl with crushed crackers.
Add onions and eggs, then salt and pepper.
Mix thoroughly.
Make into patties and fry in small amount of grease until done (medium heat).

title: justin's hot nacho dip
directions: Microwave on Full power until melted.
Add rest of ingredients; stir occasionally until smooth.
Dip with corn chips and enjoy.

title: hermits
directions: Thoroughly cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with sour milk.
Add fruit and nuts.
Drop from teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet. Bake in moderately hot oven at 375° about 15 minutes.
Dates may be omitted and raisins increased to 2 cups.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients; place in a baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until brown.

title: fruit salad
directions: Cut fresh fruit.
Cook pudding in reserved juice of peaches and pineapple until thick (about 3 minutes).
Pour over fruit.
Cover and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: cheese stuffed baked potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes well and bake in 450° oven for 40 to 60 minutes, or until soft.
Cool slightly.
Cut into halves lengthwise.
Scoop out pulp and mash well.
Add other ingredients.
Beat until light. Pile lightly in shells and sprinkle with paprika.
These can be frozen and used as needed.
Heat in 375° oven until thoroughly heated.

title: diane's spinach lasagna
directions: Cook and drain noodles (Diane does not precook her noodles). Saute onion and green pepper in little olive oil.
Stir in tomato sauce, oregano and basil.
In separate bowl, combine spinach, Ricotta, egg, Parmesan cheese and green pepper.
Stir into smooth mixture.
Layer tomato sauce, noodles, spinach and Mozzarella in baking dish.
End with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: quick chili
directions: Saute onion; brown ground chuck (salt and pepper to taste, Praise Allah is also good to use on ground chuck).
Drain drippings.
Add chili and tomato cans of soup.
Add water as desired.
Simmer and serve.

title: 30 minute cake
directions: Sift together first 2 ingredients.
Put in a large mixing bowl.
In saucepan, put next 4 ingredients; bring to a rapid boil. Pour over flour and sugar mixture and stir well.
Now, add remaining ingredients.
Bake in greased pan at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: rice and beans
directions: In saucepan, cook onion, thyme and oleo until tender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat, cover and cook 25 minutes or until done.
Stir occasionally.

title: tex-mex meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Heat oil in medium skillet over medium heat.
Add onions and red pepper; cook, stirring occasionally, until tender, 5 to 10 minutes.
Stir in chili powder, cumin, ground red pepper and garlic; cook 30 seconds more.
Transfer to large bowl and cool.
Add beef, bread crumbs, corn, 1/3 cup ketchup and the milk, egg and egg white, salt and pepper; mix well.
Pat into 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Spread remaining 2 tablespoons ketchup on top.
Bake 75 to 80 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before slicing.
Makes 8 servings.

title: frikadeller(makes approximately 32)
directions: Thoroughly mix chicken, veal, bread crumbs, unbeaten eggs, 2 tablespoons cream, salt and pepper.
Using 1 tablespoon, make into meatballs.
In a large saucepan, bring chicken broth to a boil. Add meatballs, a few at a time.
Cook about 15 minutes.
Remove with a slotted spoon.
When all meatballs are cooked, strain broth. Remove 1 1/2 cups broth for gravy.
Reserve any for another use. Gradually whisk broth with flour, keeping smooth, then whisk in cream, sugar and lemon juice.
Cook over moderate heat, stirring constantly, until thickened and boiling.
Reheat the meatballs in the sauce.
Sauce will be on the thin side and delicately flavored. Best when served over wide noodles.

title: sticky buns
directions: Melt butter in an 8 x 11 1/2-inch round pan.
Add brown sugar and corn syrup.
Heat until sugar dissolves.
Scatter pecans on bottom.
Place biscuits on top in single layer.
Place in hot oven (425°) for about 15 minutes or until done.
Let stand about 5 minutes.
Invert and serve warm.

title: yellow squash souffle
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease casserole or souffle dish.
In small amount of water, cook squash, 10 to 20 minutes; drain.
Mash squash; blend in cheese and butter.
Add remaining ingredients. Place in greased casserole and bake for 30 minutes to 1 hour. Knife in center should come out clean if done.
Sprinkle with tiny green peas and serve immediately, hot.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: hot taco dip
directions: Heat together and serve hot.

title: lemon crumb squares
directions: Mix milk, lemon juice and rind.
Set aside.
Cream brown sugar and butter.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to creamed mixture.
Add oatmeal.
Mixture will be crumbly.
Press half the crumb mixture into an 8 x 12-inch baking dish to form crust. Spread milk mixture over crust.
Crumble remaining mixture over top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: crab salad
directions: Layer lettuce, crab meat, seasoning, sliced eggs, water chestnuts, onions, celery and peas in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine mayo and Durkee sauce; spread over salad to seal.
Cover tightly with foil and refrigerate overnight.
Just before serving, toss in large bowl (add more mayo, if needed).
Sprinkle with almonds. Makes 8 generous servings.

title: corn bread skillet casserole
directions: Crumble ground beef into large skillet and brown.
Stir eggs, corn
meal,
corn,	milk
and oil together.
Pour 1/2 of batter into greased cast-iron skillet.
Top with ground beef; follow with cheese, onions and peppers.
Pour remaining batter over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions on package.
Drain. Pour drained broccoli back into cooking pan.
Stir in cheese and half of the margarine until melted.

title: chop suey cake
directions: Mix by hand in above order.
Pour into an oblong greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Ice with following icing.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix dry ingredients; sift and add beaten egg, buttermilk and chopped onion and mix.
Drop into hot fat and fry to golden brown. Drain on absorbent paper.
Serve hot.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Boil water and add bouillon.
Mix flour and milk; add to water. Stir constantly.
Cook broccoli; drain well and add to soup. Simmer 1 hour.
Add undiluted cheese soup and pepper just before serving.

title: deluxe chocolate marshmallow bars
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat until fluffy.
Combine flour, baking powder, salt and cocoa; add to creamed mixture.
Stir in nuts.
Spread in a greased jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes.
Sprinkle marshmallows evenly over cake.
Cool.

title: clabbered chicken
directions: Cook hen covered with water until tender (I use pressure cooker).
Remove chicken from broth and pick off the bone.
De-fat the broth by cooling in refrigerator overnight.
Simmer the broth with the celery, green peppers and onions for 10 minutes.
Add the noodles and cook until tender.
Add chicken taken from bone, Worcestershire sauce, mushrooms, celery soup and cheese. Mix all well and pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 30 minutes.

title: marinated onions
directions: Marinate overnight.
Drain and put 1/2 cup mayonnaise and 1 teaspoon celery salt.

title: food for the angels
directions: Beat egg whites.
Add sugar and vanilla.
Fold in crackers and nuts.
Pour into 8 x 8-inch greased pan.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Cool.
Top with Dream Whip or Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: black bean soup
directions: Cook and stir onion and garlic in oil in Dutch oven until onion is tender.
Stir in next 8 ingredients.
Heat to boiling.
Boil 2 minutes.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer until beans are tender, about 2 1/2 hours.
Remove ham butt and cut into pieces and return to soup.
Whirl 2 cups of the soup in blender or food processor until smooth and remix with remaining soup.
Serves 8.

title: crazy custard
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Heavily grease and flour a glass pie plate (9-inch), bottom and sides.
This helps to make the crust. Put all ingredients into a blender; run just until combined.
Pour into baking dish; sprinkle nutmeg all over the top.
Bake for 40 minutes.
Remove from oven; let cool slightly so pie sets. Excellent warm or cold.

title: pineapple souffle
directions: Melt 1 stick butter or margarine.
Add to 1 cup sugar and mix together.
Add crushed pineapple.
Beat eggs and add to mixture. Take crust off bread.
Break up, add and mix.
Sprinkle cinnamon on top.
Bake at 300° to 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves approximately 8.

title: pudding delight
directions: Crumble like pie dough.
Pat into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for approximately 10 minutes.
Let cool 1 hour.

title: dannon fat-free muffins(delicious)
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt. Add yogurt, milk and fruit.
Fill prepared muffin tins (spray with Pam).
Bake 18 minutes at 400°.

title: crisp sugar cookies
directions: Cream together oleo, sugar, egg, oil and vanilla.
Sift together remaining ingredients and fold into creamed mix, a little at a time.
Drop on an ungreased cookie sheet by teaspoon. Flatten with a glass dipped in sugar.
Add pecan to center of each cookie.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: zucchini salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Cover and refrigerate at least 6 hours before serving.
Will keep up to 2 weeks.

title: chicken fruit n' nut salad
directions: Arrange greens on plate, along with chicken, apple and grapes. Drizzle with dressing and top with nuts.

title: mamie eisenhower's fudge
directions: Boil sugar, salt, butter and evaporated milk for 6 minutes. Put into a large bowl the chocolate bits, sweet chocolate, marshmallow cream and nutmeats.
Pour boiling syrup over ingredients in bowl.
Beat until chocolate is melted and pour into pan.
Let stand a few hours before cutting.
Store in a tin box.

title: summer rice salad
directions: Combine and hand blend the first 7 ingredients.
Separately blend dressing, vinegar and curry powder.
Mix all ingredients together and toss well.
Cover and chill.
Serve chilled.

title: granny mac's oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream sugars, butter, eggs and vanilla until blended and fluffy.
Add flour.
Stir in oats and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 7 to 10 minutes.

title: pecan nuggets
directions: Cream together the sugar, butter, vanilla and instant coffee. Gradually add flour, mixing well.
Stir in nuts.
Chill for 1 hour. Form rounded tablespoonfuls of dough into balls.
Place 1-inch apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 12 or 15 minutes.
Remove from baking sheet and roll each ball in powdered sugar.
Makes about 20.

title: egg biscuits
directions: Mix ingredients and roll into small balls.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 10 minutes at 350°.

title: spanish rice
directions: Fry bacon until crisp; remove and add onion and green pepper. Cook slowly until onion is soft and yellow.
Add remaining ingredients and bacon.
Bake in 13 x 9-inch casserole at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: stromboli
directions: Defrost bread as per package instructions.
Brown ground beef and sausage; drain off fat.
Spread each loaf of bread dough to approximately 12 x 6.
Spread each loaf with mustard.
Add beef and sausage mixture between the two loaves.
Then add a layer of ham, salami and American cheese to each of the loaves.
Repeat layers until all ingredients are used up.
Sprinkle with a little oregano.
Overlap sides, seal and fold ends up tightly.
Brush top with oil and sprinkle with a little more oregano.
Bake for 30 minutes at 375° or until golden brown.
Serve with spaghetti sauce if desired.
Makes 2 strombolies.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Cream the margarine.
Add sugars; beat well.
Add the egg and vanilla.
Add all dry ingredients and the pumpkin.
Add 1 cup of chopped walnuts or raisins, if desired.
With teaspoon, drop dough on greased cookie sheet, spreading into desired shape.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes, until firm and lightly browned.
Cool on racks.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Brown hamburger; drain. Cook green beans according to package directions. Boil potatoes and mash. Mix hamburger, soup, green beans. Place in casserole dish. Place mashed potatoes on top and bake at 350° for 20-30 minutes. Shredded cheese could be sprinkled on top, if desired.

title: rhubarb delight
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Pat into a 9 x 9-inch pan and bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: dilly bread
directions: In large bowl, stir together 1 cup flour, sugar, onion, dill seed, salt, soda and yeast.
In a saucepan, heat cottage cheese, water and butter until very warm (120°).
Add to flour mix with the egg.
Beat at low speed until moistened.
Beat at medium speed for 3 minutes.
With a wooden spoon, stir in enough flour to make a stiff dough.
Cover with plastic film.
Let rise until doubled, about 1 hour.
With spoon, work dough enough to stir down.
Turn into a well-greased 8-inch round, 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover; let rise 30 to 45 minutes.

title: raisin bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening.
Add fruit to dry ingredients.
Add beaten egg to milk.
Combine mixture.
Shape into loaf.
Put into greased bread pans.
Let stand for 15 minutes.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: corn flake candy
directions: Mix sugar and syrup and bring to a boil.
Remove from heat; stir in peanut butter until creamy.
Add cornflakes and stir well. Press into a 9 x 13-inch buttered glass dish; let cool.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour in pan sprayed with cooking spray. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: mom's custard
directions: In bowl, beat eggs slightly.
Add salt and sugar.
Mix well. Add scalded milk slowly; add vanilla and nutmeg.
Pour custard in a well-buttered 1-quart casserole and sprinkle a little nutmeg on top.
Place in pan of hot water and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until silver knife comes out clean.

title: coconut custard pie
directions: Cream butter and cream cheese.
Add flour.
Make small balls out of dough (2 dozen) and chill for 15 minutes.
Press balls into tin.
(Use mini cupcake tin and grease.)

title: eagle brand eggnog
directions: Whip separately whites and yolks of 5 eggs.
Add 1/3 cup sugar to stiffly beaten egg whites.
Mix 1 quart milk, 1 can Eagle Brand and 2 teaspoons vanilla.
Add whipped yolks and fold in egg whites.
Serve ice cold with sprinkled nutmeg.

title: mexican wedding balls
directions: Mix ingredients in order.
Roll in small balls.
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes. When cool, roll in powdered sugar.

title: spice tea
directions: Bring water, cloves and cinnamon to a boil; add 3 tea bags and let steep, 5 to 10 minutes.
Remove tea bags.
Add sugar, orange juice and lemon juice.
Remove cloves and cinnamon before serving.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Roll crackers into fine crumbs.
Combine crumbs, melted margarine and sugar.
Press firmly into pie plate.
Chill for 45 minutes or bake at 375° for 8 minutes, until edges are browned. Cool.

title: onions for brunch
directions: Layer onions and crackers in greased casserole.
Top with sausage and salts.
Mix soup and milk and pour over meat.
Top with cheese and pimento.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: marble cheesecake
directions: Combine crumbs, sugar and margarine.
Press onto bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: beans-beans-beans
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding according to directions on box.
Fold in Eagle Brand milk and Cool Whip.
Layer wafers, bananas and pudding mix until all is used.
Refrigerate about 2 hours before serving.

title: hot cucumbers
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cucumbers, and dissolve.
Pour over cold cukes.
Keeps all winter in refrigerator.
Makes 5 quarts.
Keep adding cukes.
Keep liquid no longer than 6 months.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Add egg yolks, one at a time, mixing well after each to condensed milk.
Stir in lemon juice until mixture thickens.
Pour into graham cracker crust.

title: coconut cream dessert
directions: Mix cracker crumbs and butter.
Reserve 1/2 cup crumbs for topping; press remaining crumbs into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix ice cream, milk and instant pudding.
Pour over crust.
Chill 3 hours (or overnight).
Cover with topping; sprinkle with reserved cracker crumbs.

title: rocky road cookies
directions: In a double boiler over low heat, combine chocolate, butter and milk.
Mix together until smooth.
In a large bowl, mix marshmallows and walnuts.
Pour chocolate mixture over marshmallow-nut mixture; mix thoroughly.
Line a 10 x 9-inch dish with waxed paper.
Pour mixture into pan.
Chill for about 3 hours. Chop into pieces.

title: bacon and cauliflower salad
directions: Combine all the salad ingredients and toss with salad dressing.
Chill for several hours before serving.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: You will need a large tube pan.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix altogether and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: pasta e. fagioli (fah-zood)
directions: In a large heavy pot, fry bacon crisp and remove.
Saute onion, garlic and celery until tender, using lid.
Add water, drained beans, basil and parsley; simmer, uncovered, about 1 hour. Add tomato sauce, tomatoes, olive oil and some more water (if needed); cook until bubbly.
Add pasta and bay leaf; cook until it's done.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: reese bars
directions: Mix peanut butter, brown sugar, butter and vanilla until smooth.
Add powdered sugar a little at a time (you may not need the full pound) until smooth and spreadable.
Spread in buttered 13 x 9-inch pan.
Melt together over hot, not boiling, water the chocolate chips and butter.
Spread over peanut butter mixture. Let set, then cut into squares.

title: michigan apple pie
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Toss with apples and lemon juice. Place in pastry-lined pie plate.
Dot with margarine.
Cover with top crust.
Seal and flute edges.
Cut slits in top.
Bake at 425° for 50 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: cheesy carrots
directions: Saute onions in butter or margarine until clear.
Spoon over top of carrots.
Slice in velveeta as desired.
Cook in oven at 350° until hot and velveeta is melted.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix and refrigerate overnight.
Form into a ball and roll in chopped nuts.

title: raspberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water.
Add ice cream and stir until melted. Add other items and pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate. Great as a dessert too.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix everything together and bake at 350°.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Cream the butter. Add sugar, beaten eggs and sifted dry ingredients.
Mix well. Form dough into 3 rolls. Chill for 4 hours.
Cut in 1/4-inch slices and bake in slow oven at 300° until light brown.

title: raw cauliflower salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, onion, milk and seasonings well until smooth. Break or cut cauliflower into tiny flowerets and add with celery and peas to the dressing mixture.
Toss lightly and chill.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix jello and water; add strawberries and stir well.
Add pineapple and nuts and stir.
Pour half of mixture into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill for 2 hours or until it sets.
Then spread with sour cream.
Spoon remaining jello mixture over sour cream and chill several hours before serving.
Let second half of mixture stand at room temperature.

title: poor bread
directions: Mix yeast, sugar and water or milk together and add flour and butter.
Dough will be sticky.
Let raise 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Punch and knead 1 1/2 cups of flour.
Let raise 1 hour in loaf pan and bake until done.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Pick chicken from bones when it's cooked.
Mix melted margarine and stuffing.
Make one layer of crumbs and one layer of chicken.
Pour over top the mushroom soup, diluted with chicken broth.
Again add a layer of crumbs, chicken and cream of celery soup, also diluted with chicken broth.
Sprinkle remaining crumbs on top and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: raisin pie
directions: Heat milk; add sugar, flour and salt to beaten egg yolks, then add to milk and raisins.
Cook until thick.
Pour on baked pie shell and top with egg whites (beaten).

title: lemon lime refrigerator sheet cake
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 3/4 cup boiling water.
Add 1/2 cup cold water.
Set aside, at room temperature.
Bake cake, as directed on box, in a 2 x 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Cool cake 20 to 25 minutes. Poke holes in cake (in pan), while still warm, with a large meat fork or toothpick (holes about 1 inch apart).
Pour lime Jell-O into holes.
Refrigerate cake while making topping.

title: easy chicken
directions: Wash, salt and pepper fryer.
Put in an 8 x 12-inch baking dish.
Mix mustard, relish and margarine.
Spoon over chicken. Sprinkle with paprika.
Cook 1 hour at 350°.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Mix and cook on medium heat.
After it starts to boil, do not stir.
Bring to a soft ball.
(Use a thermometer or place a drop or two into a cup of cold water.
If it forms a soft ball, then remove from heat.)
Add butter and vanilla.
Do not stir.
Let it cool for a while, then beat with a strong spoon until consistency is thick and hard to stir.
Also, the color will turn dull.
Pour into a greased platter.
Cut into pieces when cooled.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash in salted water until tender.
Drain, then combine squash with next 5 ingredients.
Combine stuffing mix with melted oleo, breaking up larger pieces of stuffing mix, no need to pulverize.
Cover bottom of 1 1/2-quart shallow casserole with one-half of the stuffing mix.
Pour in squash mixture.
Top with remaining stuffing mix.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix ingredients together and let simmer.
This will keep in refrigerator for months.

title: won't last long cake
directions: Measure and sift all dry ingredients together.
Add bananas and pineapple last.
Stir cake mixture (don't beat).
Bake at 350° in a loaf pan until a toothpick comes out clean.

title: acilian meat roll
directions: Combine eggs, crumbs, juice, parsley, oregano, salt, pepper and garlic.
Add beef; mix well.
On wax paper or foil, pat meat to a 12 x 10-inch rectangle.
Arrange ham atop of meat, leaving a small margin around edges.
Sprinkle shredded cheese over ham.
Starting from short end, carefully roll meat, using paper to lift.
Seal edges and ends.

title: broccoli puff
directions: Cook broccoli without salt until barely tender.
Drain and place in casserole.
Mix eggs, mushroom soup, milk and mayonnaise. Pour over broccoli.
Top with cheese.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Add soup and cheese.
Pour into 8 x 10-inch greased casserole pan.
Add croutons and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chipmunk bars
directions: Pour water over dates and cool.
Cream shortening and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add alternately with date mixture to creamed mixture.

title: milk chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend all ingredients except eggs in a large mixer bowl.
Add eggs one at a time; beat 1 minute at medium speed after each addition.
Spread batter in a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes or until cake tests done with a toothpick.
Cool right side up about 25 minutes, then remove from pan.
Frost, if desired.

title: guacamole salad
directions: Combine ingredients with enough French dressing to moisten. Season to taste with salt and Gebhardt's chili powder.
Serve on crisp lettuce with additional French dressing.
Garnish with crisp bacon.

title: chocolate satin frosting
directions: Blend sugar and hot water into chocolate.
Beat half of egg into chocolate mixture, then beat in remaining half of egg.
Beat in butter, 1 tablespoon at a time.
Blend in extract.
(Frosting will be thin at this point.)
Place pan in ice water and beat until spreading consistency.
Spread on cake.
Trim by placing nut halves on top and sides.
Frosts top and sides of 2 (9-inch) layers.

title: strawberry sparkler
directions: In a small bowl, combine yogurt and sugar.
Divide strawberries between 4 individual serving dishes.
Drizzle with yogurt mixture.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: tenderloin of pork
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Heat oil in cast-iron skillet.
When sizzling, add the tenderloins and brown on all sides.
Place in the oven and roast for about 20 to 30 minutes.
This tastes good with buttermilk biscuits and gravy.

title: spicy vegetable soup
directions: Combine meat and garlic in large pot; cook over medium heat until brown, stirring to crumble meat.
Wipe pan with paper towel to remove grease.
Add tomato juice and all other ingredients except frozen vegetables.
Cover and cook until potatoes are tender.
Add frozen vegetables and cook approximately 20 minutes.

title: mom's banana pudding
directions: Stir the sugar, flour, eggs and milk together; bring to a boil.
Simmer until pudding thickens, stirring constantly.
Layer bananas and Nilla wafers in a bowl.
Pour pudding over wafers and bananas.
Chill in refrigerator.

title: sausage and egg casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain. Mix eggs, mustard and salt. Cut bread into 1/4-inch cubes.
Stir bread and sausage into mixture.
Spoon into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until brown and firm in the middle. Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: woodrow wilson hermits
directions: Cream well together the shortening and sugar.
Add molasses, beaten egg and vanilla and beat.
Add flour, spices and salt.
Add water with dissolved soda into dry mixture and mix thoroughly. Add raisins or dates.
Drop in long strips about 1/2 inch wide on greased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with sugar, if desired.
Bake 12 minutes at 375°.
Cut when cool.
Make strips thick; makes 3 1/2 strips.

title: french onion soup
directions: Peel and thinly slice onions.
In 2-quart saucepan on medium heat, melt butter, add onions and pepper.
Saute onion mixture until golden brown.
Sprinkle with flour, stirring until flour disappears. remove from heat, add beef broth, stirring constantly. Return to heat and bring to boil.
Reduce heat to low and cook, uncovered, for 30 minutes.
Discard bay leaf.
Taste.
Add salt and pepper if needed.
Toast bread.
Put soup into individual dishes; arrange toast on top of soup, sprinkle liberally with Parmesan cheese and grated Gruyere or Swiss cheese.
Place bowls 6 inches from heat, in preheated oven at 425°, until cheese turns golden brown.
Serve.
Will serve 6. Can be made ahead of time.

title: quiche
directions: Bake pie crust for 8 minutes at 400°.
Mix other ingredients except ham.
Pour into pie crust.
Put ham in.
Bake for 1 hour at 350° (until knife cut comes out clean; may take longer than an hour).

title: baked bean dip
directions: Mix together.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Before serving, spread 24 ounces of sour cream on top.
Garnish with chopped green onion tops and chopped tomato.
Serve with Tostitos.

title: linda kelley's cheese cake
directions: Mix well until moist.
Reserve 3 tablespoons.
Press remainder into bottom and sides of spring-form pan.

title: fruit dip
directions: Cook until thick.
Chill and fold into one carton of whipped cream.

title: lemon bread
directions: Cream the butter and sugar. Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Sift dry ingredients together (save 1/2 cup for dusting).
Add flour gradually. Add lemon extract, fruits and nuts by hand.
Grease and flour 4 loaf pans. Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.
Test after 40 minutes. Can be frozen and better if made 2 or 3 days in advance.

title: super fudge
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa and cream together in saucepan over medium heat.
Stir constantly.
When forms soft ball in cold water test, remove from heat.
Add Marshmallow Creme and peanut butter. Pour onto greased plate.
Cool; cut into squares.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cocoa together.
Add water and cook until thickened.
Add vanilla and butter.
Serve warm over ice cream.

title: caramel (burnt sugar) cake
directions: Grease and flour two (9-inch) pans or 13 x 9-inch oblong pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Melt sugar in heavy skillet. Remove from heat and slowly add boiling water, stirring constantly.
Stir over low heat until all lumps are dissolved. Pour into measuring cup 1/4 cup caramel mixture and enough water to make 1 cup liquid cream shortening and sugar together until fluffy.
Add eggs and beat thoroughly.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Add to shortening mixture alternately with caramel mixture.

title: pecan caramel cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Combine crumbs, sugar and butter.
Press on bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.
Reserves 10 caramels.
In heavy saucepan, combine remaining caramels and 1/2 cup half and half.
Over medium-low heat, cook and stir until melted and smooth. Stir in chopped pecans.
Spread over prepared crust.
Bake for 15 minutes.

title: lemon cake
directions: Mix and spoon on cake while warm. Place in oven at 300° to 325° for 15 minutes. Serve plain or with whipped cream.

title: russian tea
directions: Boil sugar, 1 quart water and cinnamon stick for 5 minutes. Cool.
Add remaining ingredients.
Serve hot or cold.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream
sugars and oleo.
Combine with other ingredients and roll in
balls
the
size of a walnut.
Press with a fork. Bake at 350° until done.

title: mrs. ray's sugar cookies
directions: Beat egg, add sugar, add softened oleo and cream and beat well.
Add dry ingredients, with flour until stiff dough.
Roll and cut into rounds, sprinkle with sugar.
Bake 6 to 8 minutes in 350° oven.

title: dottie's chicken file gumbo
directions: Place cut up chicken pieces in baking pan.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° about 1 hour.
Slice both sausages and bake same time as chicken but for only about 30 minutes.
Drain fat from chicken.
Drain fat from sausages and discard.

title: old fashioned pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light as a feather.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat thoroughly after each.
Add flour, slowly, beating well.
Add flavorings.
Bake in a large greased and floured tube pan for 1 hour and 15 minutes to 1 1/2 hours at 350°. Do not open door before at least 1 hour.

title: potato casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix hash brown potatoes with the margarine, soup, sour cream, milk, onions, cheese, salt and pepper.
Spoon into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix crushed cornflakes with melted margarine and spread evenly over the top of the potato mixture.
Bake for 45 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: salty-sour pickles
directions: Soak cucumbers in ice water for 3 hours, then cut into spears. Mix vinegar, sugar and salt (red pepper to taste).
Pack spears tightly in jar; boil vinegar, sugar and salt (pepper to taste). Pour over cucumbers, seal and seat in hot water bath for 5 minutes.

title: grandma's icebox fruitcake
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large bowl.
In a saucepan, melt marshmallows into Eagle Brand over very low heat until smooth.
Add to first 5 ingredients, mixing and kneading until mixed thoroughly.
Pack in the cracker box that has been lined with waxed paper.
Store in refrigerator, removing portions as needed.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line the bottom of 2 loaf pans with aluminum foil and spray with Pam.
Mix dry ingredients.
Add eggs and oil.
With slotted spoon, dip berries out of juice and add to mixture.
Bake in 7 loaf pans at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool 15 minutes in pan.
Carefully turn out of pans and cool completely.

title: spinach stuffed pizza
directions: You will also need a pizza pan or round cooking sheet.

title: crescent surprises
directions: Unfold 8 crescent rolls.
Place cheese, ham and one asparagus spear on each piece of dough.
Roll up and spear with toothpicks. Bake 20 minutes at 375°.

title: s. o. s.
directions: Fry hamburger, stirring and separating into chunks.
Add garlic, salt and pepper while frying.
Add onion; fry until hamburger is no longer pink.
Add flour, stirring constantly until mixture is thickened.
Mix 1 cup milk and 1 cup water together. Pour milk and water mixture into hamburger mixture, stirring all the while.
If mixture is too thick, add more water until desired thickness.
Serve over rice or pasta.

title: layered lettuce salad
directions: Place 1/2 lettuce in 9 x 12-inch dish.
Cover with half of onion, celery, green pepper and frozen peas.
Repeat layers. Spread mayonnaise, mixed with sugar, over lettuce.
Top with cheese.
Place in refrigerator overnight.
Delicious.

title: van's quick southwestern chicken casserole
directions: *For a shortcut, use precooked, packaged chicken.

title: artichoke wraps
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Push wonton wrappers into bottom of mini muffin pans. Mix all ingredients. Place approximately 1 teaspoon of mixture into each wrapper. Leave wrappers open. Bake 12 to 15 minutes, until wonton wrappers have light brown edges.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream oleo, eggs and sugar. Add remaining ingredients. Mix well. Pour in angel food cake pan. Bake at 275° for 2 hours. Do not invert pan. Cool upright. When cooled, invert.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Place vegetables in shallow 3-quart baking dish.
In small bowl, combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over vegetables. Refrigerate 6 hours or overnight.
Stir occasionally.

title: red kidney bean salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Toss together lightly.
Chill well. Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: cole slaw
directions: Refrigerate and let ingredients marinate a couple of hours.

title: golden rice
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare rice according to pkg. directions.
Add margarine, stir until melted.
Add corn and soup. Put in greased 4- qt. casserole dish.
Top with cheddar cheese. Bake for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: cherry marble squares
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flavoring and flour; mix well.
Spread 3/4 of batter in greased pan.
Spread cherry filling over batter.
Drop remaining batter by spoonful over filling, leaving spaces between.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: 100 good cookies
directions: Combine sugars, butter, oil and eggs; mix with electric mixer. Add Rice Krispies, oatmeal and coconut along with raisins or chocolate chips and vanilla. Sift dry ingredients; fold into sugars and cereal mix. Mix very well. Place in refrigerator and chill 1 hour.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: mexican pot roast
directions: Brown roast on all sides in small amount of oil.
Place in crock-pot or Dutch oven, if done on stove.
Blend all ingredients in blender and cover roast.
Cook in covered crock about 5 or 6 hours (or 2 hours on low on stove).

title: fancy potatoes
directions: In large bowl, mix frozen hash browns, French onion dip, cheese, half of margarine melted and heated cream of chicken soup. Put in large casserole dish.
Crumble corn flakes.
Melt remaining margarine and mix with corn flakes.
Spread over potatoes.
Cover and bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: spiced tea(sugar free)
directions: Pour tubs of Tang in bowl.
Add tea with cloves and cinnamon. Mix well.
Store in airtight container.
Use approximately 1/2 teaspoon per cup of hot water.

title: spinach dip
directions: Cook spinach; drain and cut up fine. Mix spinach, sour cream, Miracle Whip and soup mix. Cut the center out of the bread and add dip inside.

title: mary's chicken pie
directions: In medium saucepan, mix chicken, soup, vegetables, broth and onion.
Heat.
Stir in 1 cup cheese into chicken mixture.
Pour mixture into oblong baking dish.
Mix together biscuit mix, milk and 1 cup cheese.
Drop dough by tablespoons over chicken mixture. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes or until biscuits are golden brown and done in middle.

title: barbecue brisket
directions: Mix ingredients and rub on both sides of the brisket.
Wrap in foil and let stand overnight.
Bake at 300° for 4 hours or 2 1/2 to 3 hours on grill (low heat).
Open foil and add 1 cup of barbecue sauce.
Reseal and cook for 1 hour more.

title: summer sizzle(beverage)
directions: Bring to a boil 1/2 gallon water.
Add all tea bags.
Allow to steep for 1 hour.
Add 1 1/2 cups sugar or to taste.
Stir.
Add 1/2 gallon cold water; stir.
Serve over ice with a sprig of fresh mint.

title: congealed salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water. When cool, add pineapple, mayonnaise, milk, cottage cheese and chopped nuts. Place in refrigerator to mold.

title: goulash
directions: Brown hamburger with onion.
Add remaining ingredients and stir well.
Simmer.

title: tortilla soup
directions: Saute onion, hot pepper and garlic, in oil, until soft, in a large saucepan, about 5 minutes.
Add tomato, bouillon, broth, water, tomato juice, cumin, chili powder, salt, pepper, Worcestershire sauce and steak sauce.
Bring to a boil; lower heat to simmer; simmer for 1 hour.
Add tortillas and cheese; simmer 10 minutes longer.

title: company pork chops
directions: Place pork chops in pan and season with salt and pepper. Cover with sliced carrots and potatoes.
Season as desired with salt and pepper.
Cover with sliced onion and add a layer of cheese.
Pour soup over cheese layer.
Cover pan and bake in a 400° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until done.

title: quick rolls
directions: Stir all until mixed well (with hands or spoon).
Put in muffin pans or you can roll out and cut into small biscuits.
Let stand 1 hour in warm place.
Bake at 450° until rolls begin to brown; rub tops with butter or butter flavor Crisco.
Finish baking until brown.
Serve hot.

title: baked cabbage
directions: Put cabbage in pan that is cut in 3/4-inch width.
Cook in salt water for 10 minutes.
Drain and place cabbage in greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle with flour, salt and pepper.
Dot with butter.
Add hot milk and top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: rhonda's city chicken
directions: Put City Chicken on sticks.
Whisk 2 eggs.
Roll City Chicken in eggs then in bread crumbs.
Season with garlic powder.

title: party potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes 1 day ahead.
Grate potatoes in 1 direction with onion, salt and pepper.
Layer potatoes, onion, salt and pepper. Over top, pour heavy cream.
Grate mild Cheddar cheese over top. Bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.

title: white star cookies
directions: Melt stars on low heat.
Add the peanut butter and mix well. Take off the stove and add peanuts, Rice Krispies and marshmallows.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper.

title: katie's mom's chocolate trifle
directions: Bake cake in 9 x 13-inch pan; cool overnight.
Cut into small pieces.
Make instant pudding and chill overnight.
In a trifle bowl or glass bowl, place 1 layer of cake pieces.
Dribble 1/2 of the Kahlua over cake.
Place 1/2 pudding on top.
Place 1/2 Cool Whip on top.
Sprinkle with Heath bits.
Repeat all layers once more.

title: cole slaw
directions: Combine cabbage, pepper and oil in mixing bowl.
Make dressing by mixing oil, vinegar, sugar and salt.
Make hole in center of vegetable mixture and pour dressing in hole.
Let stand 3 hours in the refrigerator.
Toss before serving.
Yields 8 servings.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Layer salad in order listed, beginning with lettuce and ending with parsley.

title: easy tortilla dip
directions: Brown and drain ground beef and sausage.
Mix all ingredients in a crock-pot.
Simmer 1 hour before serving.
Serve with tortillas.

title: raspberry tartlets
directions: Cream the butter until light and fluffy.
Add flour, 1/2 cup at a time, along with cinnamon.
Beat until mixture becomes a slightly stiff dough.
Shape the dough into a ball and wrap in plastic wrap.
Refrigerate for 1/2 hour.
Divide the dough in half.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Beat together shortening, sugars, egg, water and vanilla until fluffy.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Yields approximately 50 to 60 cookies.

title: chicken croquettes(yields 70 servings)
directions: Boil chickens; bone and grind.
Add celery, onions, rice and cracker crumbs.
Beat eggs.
Add to other ingredients.
Roll in cracker crumbs and bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Bake on cookie sheet or shallow pan.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Boil macaroni according to package directions; drain and set aside.
Meanwhile, melt butter in a medium saucepan over low heat.
Blend in flour, stirring constantly.
Gradually stir in milk and cream.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture boils and thickens, about 2 to 3 minutes.
Remove from heat and add paprika, pepper and 2 cups of the cheese; stir until cheese is melted.
Gently stir in macaroni and salt to taste.
Place in a buttered 1-quart casserole dish. Garnish top with remaining 1/2 cup of cheese and dot with additional butter.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.

title: lamb spareribs (navajo)(modern)
directions: Heat butter; add honey, lemon juice, onion, garlic and seasonings.
Rub mixture of flour, salt and pepper into ribs. Grill ribs 5 minutes over hot coals.
Baste with sauce and turn often while cooking for additional 20 minutes.

title: tomato, onion and zucchini salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill for several hours before serving.
This looks pretty mounded on a bed of lettuce on a platter to pass or on individual salad plates.

title: creamy mashed potato casserole
directions: Boil potatoes in water.
Drain, cool, peel and mash.
Combine all other ingredients.
Mix well and add mashed potatoes.
Blend and put into a 3-quart casserole.
Dot with additional butter and lightly sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serves 10 to 12.

title: rigatoni
directions: Brown ground beef, onion, and garlic.
Add Prego and simmer 30 minutes.
Put half of noodles in bottom of sprayed 9 x 13 pan. Top with provolone and sour cream.
Cover with 1/2
of sauce mixture.
Put rest of noodles, mozzarella, and rest of sauce mixture in the pan.
Top with parmesan.
Bake uncovered at 350 degrees for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: sizzled shrimp
directions: In a large nonstick skillet over high heat, stir
olive oil, cloves of garlic, bay leaf and crushed red pepper until garlic just begins to color, about 30 seconds.
Add shrimp.
Season with salt.
Stir until shrimp turns pink, 2 to 3 minutes.
Stir in dry white wine and fresh lemon juice.
Adjust seasonings; transfer to a platter and sprinkle with chopped parsley.
Serve immediately. Can be an appetizer or main dish.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine mayonnaise, sour cream and Italian dressing mix.
Toss with remaining ingredients.
Serve on a cantaloupe ring.

title: sandy's crab dip
directions: Mix above ingredients together.
Spread out onto plate.
Top with one jar of cocktail sauce.
Serve with crackers.

title: bob's chocolate cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and eggs, then add all other ingredients, except chocolate chips and walnuts.
Mix thoroughly, then add chips and nuts and mix.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes. Makes about 6 dozen.

title: bologna gravy
directions: Fry bologna in oil until lightly browned.
Add flour, salt and pepper.
Stir until slightly brown.
Add milk gradually, stirring constantly, until thick.
Cook 1 to 2 minutes.
Serve over bread.
