title: christmas pudding cake
directions: Grind the entire orange and the raisins (use the orange peel too).
Mix the ground mixture with the sugar, butter, egg, flour, soda, salt, and milk.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Peel eggplant.
Slice and soak in cold water for 30 minutes. Drain.
Drop in boiling water and cook until tender.
Drain.
In skillet, put onions, pepper and margarine.
Cook slowly for 10 minutes.
Add flour, sugar and tomatoes.
Cook until thickened.
In baking dish, add part of vegetable mixture.
Add layer of eggplant, then rest of vegetables.
Cover the top with bread crumbs.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven the last few minutes of baking time.
Sprinkle top with cheese.
Return to oven to melt cheese.

title: great crowd pleaser pasta salad
directions: Slice cheese, salami, pepperoni and olives into small bite size pieces.
Mix all of the ingredients into a large bowl and add salt, pepper and oregano.
Sprinkle grated cheese over mixture. Add salad dressing and toss to coat all ingredients.
Refrigerate overnight.
Serves about 15 people.

title: tuna-vegetable pilaf
directions: In heavy 1 1/2-quart saucepan (with tight lid) combine rice, chicken stock, water, lemon juice, dill, salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Bring to a boil, cover and reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes.
Stir in vegetables, cover and continue cooking 5 more minutes or until all the liquid is absorbed.
Blend in sour cream and tuna.
Serve hot or cold.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: brown jug soup
directions: Boil water, celery, onion and bouillon for 20 minutes.
Add potatoes, carrots, cauliflower and broccoli; boil 30 more minutes. Add Velveeta cheese and soup; simmer until cheese melts and is creamy.
Add water to make consistency right.

title: dirty rice
directions: Put last six ingredients in skillet and cover; cook slowly until tender. Add rice, livers, and gizzards; blend together. Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: lucille's frozen fruit salad
directions: Drain juice from pineapple and fruit cocktail; add to jello (which has been dissolved in small amount of water).
Chill until a small amount will mold when dropped from spoon.
Add other ingredients.
Fold in whipped cream and freeze.
After frozen, you may mix mayonnaise and whipped cream with small amount of confectioners sugar to taste and spread on top.
Sprinkle with pecans and return to freezer.
To serve, cut into blocks and serve on lettuce.
This last procedure will require another 1/2 cup of whipped cream.

title: impossible pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour. Add beaten eggs.
Mix and add remaining ingredients.
Makes its own crust.
Pour in a Pyrex dish and bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until done.
You can use a pie shell if you like a thicker crust.

title: chicken wiggle
directions: Boil hen until tender. Cool and cut in bite size pieces.
Cook noodles in chicken broth until tender. Cook butter, onions, peppers, pimento and mushrooms on simmer.
Mix noodles and remaining ingredients. This mixture should not be soupy, but moist.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Mix together the cucumber, onion and green pepper.
Mix salt and celery seed.
Pour over the cucumber.
Add sugar and vinegar. Put in container and refrigerate.

title: cabbage stuff
directions: Brown hamburger and sausage; drain.
Put small amount of grease in large pan.
Add everything, except soup and green peppers.
Add green peppers and soup 20 minutes before you remove it from the stove.
Cook and stir over medium heat for about 1 hour.
Serve with chow mein noodles dry on top.

title: garbanzo florentine soup
directions: Saute garlic and onion in olive oil.
Add bread crumbs.
Next, add beans and spinach; heat thoroughly.

title: butterfinger candy
directions: Mix together sugar, syrup and water; cook to 300°.
Stir in the peanut butter; stir quickly and pour onto buttered cookie sheet.
Cut into long rolls, then into smaller pieces.
Dip into melted chocolate.

title: quiche
directions: Beat eggs, cream, salt and sugar.
Put crumbled bacon, cheese and onion into baked pie shell.
Pour mixture over.
Bake 15 minutes at 425°.
Reduce to 300° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: scalloped cabbage casserole
directions: Cook and drain cabbage.
Make a sauce by melting butter.
Add flour, salt and pepper.
Cook until blended; add milk.
Cook until it's a thin white sauce.
Line bottom of buttered casserole dish with crushed crackers.
Alternate cabbage and white sauce.
Top with crushed crackers and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fish chowder(an oldie)
directions: Fry out salt pork until crisp.
Remove from pan.
Add minced onions to drippings and saute until golden brown.
Meantime, start halibut in cold water (just enough to cover, plus a pinch of salt).
Simmer until fish turns white.
Don't overcook.
When onions are ready, add potatoes (in cubes) and the water from fish. Flake fish; add to potatoes and onions and bring just to a boil. Add as much milk as you desire.
Add salt and pepper and bring just to the boiling point, but do not boil.
Best make ahead, even day before serving; of course, reheat.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Wash chicken and pat dry.
Mix eggs and milk, beat to uniformity.
In a separate dish, mix cornflakes, salt and pepper. Dip chicken in flour, then into egg mixture.
Coat evenly.
Then dip in cornflakes to coat with this mixture.
Place in well-greased baking pan.
Drizzle with melted butter.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour at 350° to desired doneness.

title: rice pudding
directions: Combine rice, milk, sugar, butter and egg.
Cook over medium heat until thickened, about 30 minutes, stirring often.
Add vanilla and pour into serving dishes.
Serve hot or cold.

title: hot chicken or turkey salad
directions: Combine all ingredients
except potato chips and cheese. Turn into a greased 3
quart
casserole
dish.
Sprinkle
with cheese and chips.
Bake at 350°
for 25 minutes or until cheese melts and casserole is bubbly.

title: skillet sausage rice
directions: Brown sausage in skillet or Dutch oven; pour out all but 1 tablespoon fat.
Add rice and stir-fry for 5 minutes; add onion, celery and green pepper.
Saute, stirring for 10 minutes.
Add mushrooms, soup, bouillon mixed in water, and water chestnuts. Cover and simmer an additional 15 to 20 minutes or until rice is cooked. Serve directly from skillet.

title: poodles
directions: Boil frankfurters 10 minutes and drain.
Split lengthwise nearly through.
Spread cut surfaces with prepared mustard and lay a half inch strip of cheese in each.
Fasten together with toothpicks.
Make a fritter batter.
Coat dogs with this and fry golden brown in 1 inch of Crisco oil in skillet.
Serve hot.

title: fresh cranberry salad
directions: Place orange squares and cranberries in blender.
Blend. Remove from blender.
Place in a bowl.
Add sugar; let set 2 hours.
Mix jello and water until dissolved.
Set aside to cool. Chop nuts, apple and celery; add pineapple.
Fold together.

title: dirty rice
directions: Cook rice as per directions on box.
Put gizzards and livers in another pot.
Cover with water.
Add chopped onions, salt and pepper.
Cook about 35 minutes.
Put ground beef in pot.
Cook until done.
Stir in rice.
Serves 10.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients except vanilla, peanut butter and quick oats in saucepan; bring to a boil.
Boil for five minutes.
Remove from heat and add vanilla and peanut butter, then add quick oats. Spoon on wax paper and let cool.

title: chocolate clusters
directions: Melt chocolate chip pieces slowly (low heat) in pot or double boiler.
Stir constantly.
Remove from heat and stir in chow mein noodles.
Mix quickly to coat evenly.
Dip out by teaspoon onto waxed paper to cool.

title: krazy korn
directions: Place corn on a 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan.
In a saucepan combine brown sugar, margarine and corn syrup.
Bring to boil. Stir in baking soda and vanilla.
Pour mixture evenly over popcorn. Mix well.
Bake at 250° for 30 minutes.
Stir twice during baking. Remove from pan immediately.
Cool on waxed paper or greased foil. Store in tightly sealed container.
Makes 8 cups.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Bake cake according to package directions. Allow to cool.
Mix large package of Jell-O with 3 cups water.
Put in refrigerator until it starts to
set. Remove center of cake, starting about 1-inch from the outer edge and cutting down about 1-inch of the cake's thickness.
Fill center with sliced strawberries.
Pour Jell-O over top.
Refrigerate until Jell-O is set. Top with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with nuts, if desired.

title: rolled molasses cookies
directions: Cream the sugar and shortening. Add egg and molasses. Dissolve soda in sour cream.
Add flour and spices alternately with cream. Roll out and cut.
Place on cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.
Stays soft even after baked.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine chicken and chopped onions.
Combine soup and milk in bowl.
Cook macaroni until tender.
Combine chicken and onions with soup mixture, noodles and cheese.
Put mixture in greased casserole pan.
Toss cracker crumbs in melted margarine and over casserole.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: spicy rice salad
directions: Combine water and salt in a saucepan; bring to a boil over medium-high heat.
Stir in rice and ginger; return to a boil. Cover, reduce heat to low and simmer for 45 minutes, or until tender.
Place currants in a small bowl; cover with boiling water. Let sit for 20 minutes, then drain.
In a large, nonreactive bowl, combine rice, currants, red onion, pistachios, olive oil, vinegar, allspice, nutmeg, cinnamon, salt and pepper.
Toss until all ingredients are coated.
Cover; refrigerate for several hours before serving to allow flavors to blend.
Serves 4.

title: country coleslaw
directions: Shred cabbage fine.
Wash; drain.
Set aside.
Combine all other ingredients except cream and cook until thick in double boiler.
When cold, add cream and pour over cabbage.

title: tomato salad
directions: Layer sliced tomatoes, green pepper, chopped onion and chopped celery in serving dish.
Sprinkle each layer with confectioners sugar.
Mix vinegar and salad oil and pour over tomatoes. Marinate for at least 1 hour before serving.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugars and butter; blend in egg and vanilla.
Combine flour, soda and salt; add nuts.
Add to sugar mixture.
Chill 20 minutes.
Form balls size of quarters, roll in sugar and press flat on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°. Cool.
Ice with chocolate dribblings.

title: mexican sunrise punch
directions: Put frozen juices in a medium size punch bowl or large pitcher. Stir in water.
Add tequila, ginger ale and about 1/4 cup grenadine.
Add ice.
Stir.
Garnish with lime slices.

title: fabulous fruit dip
directions: Combine Marshmallow Creme and softened cream cheese, mixing until blended.
Serve with assorted fresh fruits.
Makes 2 cups.

title: tunnel of fudge
directions: Mix butter and eggs (adding 1 or 2 eggs at a time) with the sugar; stir in flour and frosting mix by hand. Add nuts and bake at 350° for 1 hour in a Bundt pan. Leave in pan for 30 minutes before taking out.

title: easy sausage roll
directions: Defrost pastry according to directions.
Roll onto a floured surface and cut into a strip approximately 3-inches wide.
Roll the sausage meat with floured hands into a long thin sausage (the same length as the pastry strip).
Place on the pastry near the edge.
Roll up the pastry to enclose the meat.
Dampen the long edges with water and seal well.
Cut the roll into 2 1/2-inch pieces and place on cookie sheet.
Neaten shapes and brush with beaten egg or milk.
Make 3 diagonal slits in the top.
Bake at 400° for about 20 minutes or until golden.
Serve hot or cold.

title: sour cream banana pudding
directions: Combine milk and pudding mix in a large bowl of electric mixer.
Beat at low speed until thickened.
Add sour cream and beat 2 minutes. Fold in whipped topping.

title: white beans and brown rice with sage
directions: Spray large saucepan with nonstick spray.
Saute onions and garlic over medium heat 5 minutes.
Drain some liquid from beans. Add beans and tomatoes with juice in pan.
Add half tomato sauce can of water.
Bring to a boil.
Add rice, reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Add olives, sage and salt, if desired.
Heat through.
Makes 3 servings.

title: punsit
directions: Stir fry the meat until cooked, remove from pan. Stir fry the vegetables and rice sticks for 2-3 minutes. Add cooked meat and coat with soy sauce, add accent and pepper to taste. Serve immediately.

title: baked banana
directions: Grease small baking dish with margarine.
Peel banana.
Cut in half lengthwise.
Place cut side down in baking dish.
Brush with melted margarine.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with brown sugar.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Roll out in small balls. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: ham roll-ups
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and spread on boiled ham.
Roll up jelly roll fashion.
Wrap in foil.
Chill well.
Slice.
Serve on round crackers.

title: rice custard
directions: Wash rice well, then drain.
Add to milk in top of double boiler.
Cook, covered, over boiling water until rice is tender, about 1 hour.
Beat egg yolks thoroughly.
Add 3 tablespoons sugar and the salt, then stir in some of the hot rice mixture.
Return to rest of rice mixture in doubler boiler; cook 2 minutes longer, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and partially cool, then stir in vanilla.
Beat egg whites until quite stiff, then gradually add remaining 3 tablespoons sugar while continuing to beat until stiff.
Fold into rice custard.
Chill and serve. Serves 6.

title: nina's 60 minute rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm milk; add other ingredients in order given.
Let rise in warm place for 30 minutes.
Roll out on lightly floured board and spread top with soft butter.
Cut with biscuit cutter, fold over and butter tops.
Place on baking sheet. Let rise 30 minutes.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: crock-pot grouse
directions: Wash grouse and pat dry. Brush with butter. Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Place in crock-pot and sprinkle with dry salad mix. Cover and cook on low 5 to 6 hours.

title: cheesy cauliflower tomato scallop
directions: Break cauliflower into flowerets; cook in salted water about 5 minutes or until crisp-tender.
Drain.
Melt butter in saucepan, add celery, onion and green pepper; saute until limp and transparent.
Blend in salt and flour.
Stir in milk gradually over low heat until thickened.
Add cheese and oregano; stir until cheese melts.
Layer in baking dish cauliflower, then cheese sauce, tomatoes, cauliflower and remaining sauce.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: pumpkin puff
directions: Mix together pumpkin, sugar, butter, salt and spices.
Add eggs and cream.
Thoroughly combine.
Spoon mixture into baking dish. Drizzle with honey and sprinkle with pecans.
Bake at 375° for 50 minutes or until slightly puffed.
Serve at once.

title: macaroni and cheese deluxe
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions; drain, rinse and set aside.
Combine next 6 ingredients; add macaroni and stir well.

title: walnut coconut crisp
directions: Mix together with hands.
Pat tightly in cookie pan.
Roll with rolling pin to flatten out.
Bake at 300° for 35 minutes. (Preheat oven and raise grate 1 notch.)
Cut in squares while still warm.

title: breakfast bread casserole(makes 22 servings)
directions: Mix well egg and milk in a bowl.
Butter bread on both sides; dip in egg/milk mixture.
Place 8 slices on bottom of 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Spread 2 cups ham over bread, then layer 1/2 of cheese over ham.
Place remaining 8 slices soaked bread, then sprinkle remaining 1 cup cheese on top.
Pour any remaining milk/egg mixture over all.
Refrigerate for 24 hours.
Remove from refrigerator 1 hour before baking.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve with fresh fruit and pastry for brunch.

title: turnips with dill and shallots
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Lightly oil a 9-inch pie plate.
Arrange turnips in the
pie plate.

title: chocolate cookies
directions: Cream oleo and sugar in large bowl.
Add eggs and vanilla. Blend well.
Combine flour, cocoa, soda and salt. Blend into creamed mixture.
Stir in nuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 9 minutes.
Do not overcook. Cool on cookie sheet until set, about 1 minute.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour, spice and salt.
Stir in pumpkin, milk and egg.
Pour into pie crusts.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until set.
After they cool, top with whipped topping.

title: myrtle's hamburger soup
directions: Cook onions and ground beef in large saucepan until brown. Add remaining ingredients.
Cook slowly for 1 hour.

title: watermelon rind pickles
directions: Select firm watermelon rind.
Cut off green skin and all pink from rind.
Cut rind into triangular pieces. Weigh 5 pounds (about 3 1/2 quarts).
Place in a large kettle.
Cover with water; boil until rind is easily pierced with a fork.
Add measured alum to rind.
Remove from heat.
Let stand overnight.

title: marinated flank steak
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a flat container large enough for steak; mix well.
Place steak in marinade and marinate for several hours in the refrigerator.
Broil or grill.
Slice thinly across the grain.
You can put the slices in heavy-duty foil; cover with reserved marinade and place back on the grill to keep it hot.

title: key lime pie
directions: In medium bowl, stir together the sweetened condensed milk, ReaLime and food coloring, if desired.
Fold in whipped cream or Cool Whip; pour into crust.
Chill for 3 hours, or until set. Garnish as desired.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: pear bean pots
directions: Combine baked beans, 1 tablespoon brown sugar, onion and orange peel.
Place in 1 1/2-quart casserole or 4 individual baking dishes.
Arrange pear halves over beans.

title: cool carrots
directions: Peel and slice carrots.
Cook in salted water until just tender.
Mix all other ingredients and bring to a boil, stirring. Drain cooked carrots and pour other mixture over carrots.
Cover and refrigerate 24 hours before serving.
Keeps up to 6 weeks in refrigerator.

title: baked corn
directions: Melt fat and add flour.
Add milk gradually and bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Add corn, sugar, salt and pepper and heat thoroughly.
Remove from heat and add beaten eggs.
Pour in a greased baking dish and sprinkle with buttered bread crumbs.

title: lemon tea bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch loaf pan; set aside.
In large bowl, combine milk, eggs, sugar, butter or margarine and lemon peel.
Beat at medium speed until well blended.
Add dry ingredients; beat at low speed just until they are moistened and mixture is smooth.
Fold in pecans.
Pour into loaf pan.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: mexican casserole
directions: In skillet, brown ground chuck.
Then add the remaining ingredients.
Pour in casserole dish and bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar and salt.
In saucepan, bring to boil butter, water and cocoa.
Pour over flour mixture.
Blend eggs, soda, buttermilk and vanilla.
Add to flour mixture.
Mix well. Bake in greased and floured 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch pan for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: quick homestyle spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown first 5 ingredients, then add all ingredients. Heat to boil. Cover and simmer about 20 minutes. Add 1/2 cup white Zin; cook another 10 minutes. Serve over noodles.

title: pig in the ground
directions: Mix together all spices, etc. and rub on pig.
In the ground, start a fire with charcoal and lava rocks.
Burn wood pieces on top.
When coals and fire are smoldering, add the pig wrapped in a wet burlap bag.
Cover with dirt and let roast for 5 to 6 hours. Dig up pig, unwrap bags and serve with chutney of a fruity nature.

title: sukyaki
directions: Brown hamburger; drain grease.
Cube potatoes; quarter onions and cabbage.
Put vegetables on top of burger, then pour mixture of water,
soy sauce and sugar over top.
Cover and boil for about 30 minutes, or until vegetables are tender.
Serve over rice.

title: american pate(yields 1 servings)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large mixing bowl, combine meats with garlic, onion and bread crumbs.
Add tomato paste, egg and spinach to meat mix and mix well.
Transfer mixture to an 8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch loaf pan.
Cover with aluminum foil and seal tightly. Bake for 45 minutes, then remove foil and bake for 30 minutes longer.
Let meat loaf sit for 15 minutes before cutting.
Enjoy!

title: cheese rounds
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Combine flour and salt.
Cut in corn oil margarine until mixture is crumbly.
Add cheese until blended.
Add water and lightly mix until forms a ball.
Roll on floured board.
Cut into rounds with biscuit cutter.
Place on baking sheet.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Slice cucumbers; chop onion and pepper.
Add sour cream, salad dressing, salt and pepper.
Mix all together.
Refrigerate.

title: swiss steak
directions: Cut meat in serving pieces.
Combine flour, salt and pepper. Lay meat on bread board.
Pound flour mixture into meat with the edge of saucer or meat mallet.
Add meat to hot oil and brown well, turn as necessary.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bring liquid to boil.
Cover and simmer 1 1/2 to 2 hours until meat is tender. Serve over rice.

title: stuffed round steak
directions: Pound round steak real good on both sides to tenderize. Marinate with Italian dressing.
Let set for 1 hour or more.
Mix ground chuck, bread crumbs, 1/2 cup milk, salt and red pepper.
Put ground chuck mixture on round steak and roll.
Pin with toothpicks or tie with strings (4).
Bake in oven at 400° for 1 hour.
Remove from oven, pour 1 can mushroom brown gravy and heat until thick. Remove rolled steak out of pot; cut into slices.

title: chipped ham or beef barbecue
directions: Simmer ingredients together for 15 minutes.
Add chipped ham or beef and simmer 1 1/2 hours.

title: beef and cheese casserole
directions: In large bowl, gradually stir milk into soup until blended. Add macaroni, beef, cheese, eggs and onions.
Toss to coat well. Spoon into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Cover and refrigerate at least 8 hours or overnight.
Cover casserole with foil and bake in 375°
oven, stirring once, 45 minutes or until macaroni is tender. Remove from oven and let stand 10 minutes.

title: wilted lettuce
directions: Combine first
three ingredients in a large bowl.
In a skillet fry bacon until crisp. Remove bacon and crumble. Remove all
bacon drippings from skillet except 4 or 5 Tbsp.
Add sugar, salt, pepper, vinegar and bring to a boil. You may want to add a Tbsp. water. Pour over lettuce mixture and toss.

title: deviled ham cheese ball
directions: Blend together all ingredients except nuts.
Press into a 2-cup bowl.
Chill 3 to 4 hours or overnight in refrigerator.
Unmold on serving plate.
Garnish with nuts.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: pastry frosting
directions: Combine sugars and milk.
Cook until sugar has dissolved and boils.
Stir constantly.
Immediately add chocolate chips or peanut butter chips.

title: shoepeg casserole
directions: Mix the above ingredients in a casserole dish.

title: lime jell-o salad ii
directions: Pour 2 cups boiling water over Jell-O in a large bowl.
Add cream cheese.
Stir until well dissolved.
Add 1 2/3 c. cold water and other ingredients.
Place in refrigerator until set.

title: cheesy eggplant pie
directions: Heat broiler.
Arrange eggplant slices in a single layer on a baking sheet.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Broil 6-inches from heat source for 8 minutes or until lightly browned.
Heat oven to 375°.
Line a 10-inch pie plate with eggplant slices, browned side down, overlapping.
Arrange alternating slices of tomato, peppers and onion atop the eggplant.
Sprinkle with oil, garlic powder, remaining salt and Italian seasonings.
Bake for 25 minutes.
Top with cheese and bake an additional 15 minutes.
Serves 2.

title: west virginia reunion beans
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Cut onion and green pepper in small pieces.
Put all ingredients in slow cooker and cook for 3 to 4 hours.

title: barley and corn salad with jalapeno and lime dressing
directions: Bring water to a boil in a medium saucepan.
Gradually stir in barley.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 40 minutes or until barley is tender and water is absorbed.
Let cool.

title: champagne punch
directions: Ahead
of time, chill champagne and ginger ale.
Reconstitute frozen
orange juice and freeze in six to eight ounce containers to be used as a stir/float in the punch bowl during a party.

title: quick chicken pot pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Line the bottom of a 9-inch pie pan with one crust. Pour in entire mixture. Place the other pie crust on top; poke a few holes for air. Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes (or until crust browns). Serves 4 people. (Preparation: 15 minutes. Cook time: 30 minutes.)

title: chicken, beef or lamb biryani
directions: Cut into pieces chicken or beef; mash and set aside.
Pour the 1/4 cup oil in a deep pan; season with 2 cloves, a small piece cinnamon stick and 1/4 teaspoon aniseed powder.
Then add 2 tablespoons sliced onions and fry until brown.
Then add 1/4 teaspoon of turmeric powder and 1 teaspoon of chili powder.
Fry a little and add the meat; mix well and let cook with about 1/2 cup water.
When 3/4 done, remove from stove.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water.
Put cranberry sauce and sour cream into the jello.
Mix until it is smooth.
Pour into a bowl and congeal.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Mix together in large mixing bowl.
Pour into rectangular Pyrex
pan.
Sprinkle the 1 cup cheese on top.
Cover with foil and
bake
1 hour at 350°.
Remove foil 20 minutes before finished baking.
Yields 6 servings.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Mix all together.
Pour over chicken.
Cover until last 15 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until chicken is done. Serve with rice or noodles.

title: marvelous pineapple cake
directions: Mix cake according to directions on box and bake until done. As soon as your cake is removed from oven, punch holes in cake; go over entire top of cake.
While cake is still hot, spoon pineapple and juice over cake.
Spread evenly and let set until cake is cooled.
Then, mix pudding with 1 cup milk by hand.
Fold in container of Cool Whip.
Frost cooled cake with mixture.
Over top of frosting, put a layer of nuts and a layer of coconut.

title: poppy seed cake and icing
directions: Scald milk; pour over poppy seed.
Cool and refrigerate overnight. Cream butter and sugar.
Sift together dry ingredients. Add flour mixture alternately with poppy seed mixture to creamed mixture.
Add vanilla and fold in egg whites.
Bake in two greased and floured 8-inch pans or 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Fill and frost.

title: raspberry jam bars
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Melt butter and combine cake mix, oatmeal and butter.
Stir until crumbly.
Press 1/2 of crumbs into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Combine the jam and water and spoon over the crumbs.
Pat remaining crumbs over jam.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool completely before cutting into bars.

title: escalloped tomatoes
directions: Combine all ingredients; pour in greased casserole.
Let stand 5 or 10 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken ole
directions: Line bottom of 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish with tortillas. Cut chicken into bite size pieces; mix with sour cream, soup and peppers.
Spread mixture on top of tortillas.
Top with shredded cheeses.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to an hour.

title: quick barbecue sauce
directions: In small saucepan, cook onion and garlic in margarine until tender.
Add remaining ingredients; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer uncovered 15 minutes.
Use as basting sauce for pork, chicken or beef.
Makes about 1 cup.

title: butterfinger cake
directions: Whip eggs, sugar and margarine.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pinch 1/2 cake in pieces and put in dish.
Pour 1/2 Cool Whip mixture over this.
Sprinkle 3 bars candy over this and repeat.
Refrigerate.

title: apricot chicken
directions: Place chicken breasts in a baking dish and brush with melted margarine.
Sprinkle with seasoned salt substitute and garlic powder.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Drain the excess fat and juice from the chicken and brush the apricot jam on each piece of chicken with a pastry brush.
Return to the oven and bake an additional 15 minutes.
Serves 6. Contains 288 calories, 10.7 gm. fat, 73 mg. cholesterol, 142 mg. sodium and 270 mg. potassium per serving.

title: grandma ruth's christmas ham
directions: Wash ham and score. Combine mustard and brown sugar. Rub all over ham. Press cloves into ham. Wrap in foil. Pour cider in pan around ham. Cook 2 hours and 15 minutes.

title: fudge
directions: Add sugar, salt and cocoa.
Mix.
Pour in milk.
Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Cook on medium heat until mixture reaches soft ball stage.
Remove from heat.
Add butter and vanilla.
Stir until mixture begins to stiffen.
Pour into buttered pans.
Let cool.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Microwave cook ground beef on High for 2 to 3 minutes.
Mix beef, water and spaghetti sauce.
In oblong baking dish, spoon 1/2 cup sauce.
Layer noodles, cottage cheese, Mozzarella and meat sauce.
Repeat layers, saving sauce to pour over top of casserole. Top with Parmesan cheese.
Cover with 2 layers of plastic wrap, sealing completely.
Microwave on High for 8 minutes, then medium-low or 4 power level for 32 minutes or until noodles are tender.
Let stand 15 minutes before serving.

title: ranch cheese spread
directions: Mix cream cheese and Ranch dressing.
Add nuts and shape into a ball.
Serve with crackers.
Kids can make this in a snap!

title: hungry jack casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Add barbecue sauce, brown sugar and pork and beans.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Pour in casserole dish.
Put biscuits on top of mixture and sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: peach bitch(from the rose tattoo, philadelphia, pa)
directions: Blenderize all ingredients with ice.
Serve as a frozen drink.

title: microwave easy meat loaf
directions: Mix ingredients except ketchup in a casserole dish.
Spread meat out in pan leaving an opening in the center.
Place a small glass in the center of the meat.
This allows the meat loaf to cook better.
Spread ketchup over the top of the meat.
Cook on High for 20 minutes.
Let stand for about 5 minutes.
If not done, cook another 5 minutes.

title: apple roll
directions: Mix flour, 1/2 cup water and oil like biscuit dough.
Roll out into a rectangle.
Mix apples, milk, 1 1/2 cups sugar and cinnamon and let soak for awhile.
Put apple mixture on top of biscuit dough and roll up.
Put in a baking pan.
In a pan, melt butter, 1/2 cup sugar and 1/2 cup water.
Pour over apple roll and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: lemonade pie
directions: With mixer on medium speed, mix lemonade, condensed milk and dessert topping until well blended.
Pour into crust and refrigerate for several hours.

title: seven-up pound cake
directions: Have ingredients at
room temperature.
Cream sugar with butter and Crisco at high speed.
Add
eggs,
one
at
a
time. Continue beating at high speed
and
add
flour and 7-Up alternately.
Add flavoring.
Bake in a greased tube pan at 325° for about 1 1/2 hours.

title: special k cookies
directions: Bring the first 3 ingredients to a boil.
Remove from stove. Add remaining ingredients.
Pour in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Cut in squares.

title: fluffy stuff
directions: Mix together and put in dish.
Bake at 350 degrees for 20 minutes.
Let cool.

title: baked beans
directions: Drain off water from beans and add fresh water with 1/2 teaspoon baking soda.
Simmer until beans are tender.
Drain off soda water and add fresh water to cover with remaining ingredients.
Simmer for 20 minutes to 1/2 hour.
Bake in bean pot or roaster at 375° for 4 hours, covered, then let brown.
Add water, if needed, and stir every 1/2 hour.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown the ground meat with onions and celery.
Add Tater Tots and soups.
Fold in cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. You can just sprinkle cheese on top.

title: old-fashioned potato salad
directions: Combine potatoes, onion, celery, eggs, salt, celery seed, and pepper in a large bowl.
Blend mayonnaise, mustard, and pickle relish.
Gently stir into potato mixture. Chill thoroughly before serving.
Garnish with slices of hard-cooked eggs and pickles. Yield:
about 8 servings.

title: cheddar squash bake
directions: Cook squash in small amount of water until tender.
Drain well.
Sprinkle with salt.
Reserve a few slices for garnish.
Mix sour cream, egg yolks and flour.
Fold in egg whites.
In a 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish, layer half the squash, half egg mixture, half the cheese and sprinkle bacon on top.
Repeat layers. Combine crumbs and butter and sprinkle on top.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Top with bacon and parsley.

title: lemon chicken(sweetheart social 1994)
directions: Make a marinade with first 4 ingredients and refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Melt margarine in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Coat 10 chicken pieces (thighs and breasts) with flour and arrange in the pan.
Do not stir.
Slowly pour marinade evenly over chicken.
Sprinkle lightly with salt, pepper and paprika to taste (no salt used at the banquet).
Bake for 1 hour or until fairly brown at 350°.
Adjust time if you are doing boneless breasts to about 30 to 40 minutes.

title: yogurt pound cake
directions: Place flour, sugar,
salt
and	soda
into large mixing bowl. Stir to blend.
Add butter, yogurt, eggs and vanilla to dry ingredients.
Beat	at slow speed until moistened, then at medium speed 4
minutes, scraping sides of bowl often.
Remove beaters and stir in lemon peel.
Turn into well-greased 12-cup Bundt pan. Place in
preheated
oven
and bake 40 to 45 minutes or until done.
Cool
in
pan	5 minutes.
Turn out on rack and cool. Dust with powdered sugar or glaze.

title: pistachio coffee cake
directions: Mix cake mix, pudding, eggs, oil, water and sour cream until smooth.
Combine in a separate bowl: sugar, brown sugar, cinnamon and nuts.
Pour 1/3 of batter into a 9 x 13 inch pan.
Sprinkle half of the sugar mixture on batter, then repeat with remaining batter and sugar mixture.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for about 35 minutes or until cake tests done.

title: aunt catherine's chicken(from hyme andrews)
directions: Season
and boil chicken until tender, 1 1/2 to 2 hours (celery
salt,
thyme
and sage).
Reserve liquid;
strain, if necessary.
Using chicken stock, cook pasta (you're using less liquid
than
usual
for
cooking
pasta).
Drain pasta; don't rinse, and place in large shallow dish.
Sprinkle about 3/4ths cheese
on
pasta or layer pasta and cheese.
Break up chicken in large chunks, removing skin and bones.
Lay chicken on top of pasta and sprinkle on remaining cheese.
Serves 6.

title: yellow summer squash
directions: Mix all together and fry in butter, tossing together as it cooks, until brown.

title: old-fashioned molasses cookies(daddy's favorite)
directions: Melt shortening over low heat.
Cool; then add all other ingredients.
Mix well.
Chill.
Form 1-inch balls.
Roll in granulated sugar.
Place on a greased cookie sheet, 2 inches apart.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: homemade vegetable soup
directions: Mix vegetables and stock.
Cook slowly until thick.
You can add diced chicken, leftover beef or pork roast, if desired.

title: dump salad
directions: Cream cheese.
Make Jell-O and add to cream cheese.
Add Cool Whip and oranges.
Refrigerate.

title: squash pickles
directions: Drain and rinse squash mixture.
Add to boiling vinegar. Remove from heat and put in pint jars.
Makes 5 pints.

title: sweet potatoes
directions: Bring to boil juice from pineapple and oleo.
Mix sugar and cornstarch and add to mixture.
Cook until clear and a little thick.
Cut potatoes and arrange with cherries and pineapple in baking dish.
Pour mixture over this and bake in oven at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: cheese puffs
directions: Melt cheeses together in the top of a double boiler (keep warm for ease in spreading).
Remove crusts from the bread.
With a rolling pin, flatten each slice as thin as possible.
Spread cheese mixture thinly on each slice, then roll up with filling inside.
Cut each roll in half.
Dip in melted butter or margarine, coating on all sides.
Heat under broiler until golden brown, 5 to 10 minutes.
These can be easily prepared and frozen for future use.
Do not toast before freezing.

title: peaches and cream delight
directions: Mix cake mix with eggs, pudding, oil and water.
Put into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread drained peaches over mixture.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and peach juice.
Spread on top of peaches.
Bake in a preheated oven at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: marinated chickpea and vegetable salad
directions: In medium bowl, combine chickpeas, oregano, salt, black pepper, oil and vinegar.
Stir in tomato and green pepper; toss to coat.
Cover and refrigerate 2 to 3 hours or overnight.

title: crock-pot macaroni and cheese
directions: Grease crock-pot with Pam.
Mix all ingredients together. Pour into crock-pot
and cover with thin strips of cheese.
Cook 3 to 4 hours on low. Sprinkle paprika on top before cooking.

title: cherry soup
directions: Combine cherries, cinnamon and cloves with the water in a large saucepan.
Bring to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes.
If desired, puree fruits by pressing through sieve or use an electric blender.
Add sugar and stir until it dissolves. Cool thoroughly.
Beat in sour cream.
Serve with noodles or croutons.
Makes 8 servings.

title: ma's potato rusks
directions: At night, dissolve the yeast in warm water.
Add sugar and mashed potatoes.
Mix.
Let set at room temperature.

title: easy "homemade taste" chocolate pie
directions: Mix pudding according to package directions.
Stir in cocoa, sugar, salt and cinnamon.
Cook according to package directions. When done, remove from heat and stir in vanilla.
Pour into baked pie crust.
Top with Cool Whip or whipped cream. Sprinkle nutmeg or cocoa on top and serve.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Fold dry pudding mix into Cool Whip.
Add pineapple, juice, marshmallows and pecans.
Refrigerate.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Beat butter at medium speed with electric beater for 2 minutes until light and creamy.
Gradually add sugar, beating at medium speed 5 to 7 minutes.
Add eggs one at a time, beating until yellow disappears.
Combine flour and baking soda and add to creamed mixture, alternating with sour cream, beginning and ending with flour.
Mix at lowest speed.
Stir in flavorings.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Cool in pan for 10-15 minutes.

title: raw apple nut cake
directions: Sift together flour, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Add dry ingredients to sugar and oil mixture.
Fold in apples and nuts. Bake in greased and floured tube pan at 325° for 1 hour.

title: carob brownies
directions: Combine butter, honey,	milk
and
carob in a saucepan; simmer for 5
minutes, stirring constantly.
Sift dry ingredients.
Beat eggs
and
vanilla; add to saucepan mixture.
Pour into dry ingredients and
mix.
Pour
into
an 8 x 8-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool on a wire rack.

title: shredded beef chimichangas
directions: In a skillet, saute onion in oil until tender.
Reduce heat to medium.
Sprinkle gravy mix over onion.
Stir in water until blended.
Add the beef, chilies and pepper.
Cook until gravy thickens and mixture is heated through, stirring occasionally. Spoon about 1/4 cup off-center onto each tortilla.
Fold up edge nearest filling; fold in both sides and roll up.
Secure with toothpicks.

title: indonesian chicken saute
directions: Pound chicken breasts to 1/2-inch thickness between wax paper. Cut into 1-inch strips.
Mix chicken and seasonings in bowl. Refrigerate 2 hours (for spicier chicken, marinate longer).
Thread chicken on skewers.
Brush with marinade.
Broil on grill 3 to 4 minutes on each side.

title: master baking mix
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cut in shortening until mixture is crumbly.
Store in tightly covered container in cupboard.
This mix may be substituted in any recipe calling for Bisquick.

title: pink stuff
directions: Mix well and refrigerate in a large glass bowl, or in individual serving dishes.

title: pickled shrimp
directions: Cover shrimp with boiling water. Add celery, spices and salt. Cover. Simmer 5 minutes. Drain. Cool. Peel shrimp and devein. Alternate shrimp and onion in a shallow dish. Add bay leaves. Marinate 24 hours in Pickling Marinade.

title: grandmother gladys' peach pie
directions: Mix flour with sugar.
Add to melted margarine.
Add other ingredients and pour into uncooked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Top with meringue (3 egg whites and 6 tablespoons sugar).

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Mix all ingredients. Spread on tortillas. Roll up and wrap in wax paper or foil and chill overnight.

title: bunuelos(fried cinnamon sugar tortillas)
directions: In saucepan, heat milk and butter to boiling; cool.
Stir in beaten eggs.
Stir together the flour, baking powder and salt. Add egg mixture and mix well.
Knead dough on lightly floured surface 2 to 3 minutes, until smooth.
Shape into 20 balls.
Let rest 5 minutes.
Roll each ball into a 4-inch circle.
Fry in hot oil about 4 minutes or until brown, turning once.
Drain on paper towels.
Sprinkle with cinnamon-sugar mixture, while still warm.

title: crabmeat dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together in casserole.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Double for 20 people.

title: pina colada mocktail
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender; process until smooth.

title: rice consomme
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Combine consomme, rice, mushrooms and onion in a casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: cheese spread
directions: Melt Velveeta in saucepan over low heat.
Place in mixing bowl and add remaining ingredients.
Beat at low speed for 2 minutes, high speed for 5 minutes.
Place in crocks or containers. Refrigerate.
Serve on crackers.

title: spiced tea mix
directions: Mix well together in an airtight container.
(Makes great holiday gifts.)

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown and drain hamburger meat (add onion, if desired.)

title: chili relleno casserole
directions: Spray 9 x 9-inch pan with cooking spray.
Open up chilies and layer chilies and cheese in bottom of pan.
Beat together eggs flour and milk.
Pour over chilies and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: oyster snack crackers
directions: Mix all together and put on cookie sheet.
Bake in low oven at 250° for 5 to 10 minutes.

title: date and rice bubble tart(heritage:  australia)
directions: Melt the butter.
Add the dates and sugar.
Simmer 5 minutes. Pour over the rice bubbles and mix.
Press into greased pie dish and refrigerate until firm. Slice the bananas over the top and cover with whipped cream.

title: bran muffins
directions: Pour 1 cup boiling water over oatmeal, wheat and bran.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Store in covered bowl in refrigerator and bake as desired.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
You may add raisins, nuts or blueberries to batter for variation in your muffins.
Muffin mix may be kept 2 to 3 weeks.

title: carrot cake (with pineapple)
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Add carrots, oil, pineapple and eggs.
If desired, add orange rind or coconut.
Bake in oiled and floured tube pan for 1 hour at 350° or until set.
Cool and serve or wrap for freezing.
Best after about 3 weeks.

title: raisin bran cookies
directions: Cream shortening; add sugar.
Cream this.
Add well beaten eggs; cream this.
Add flour mixed with baking powder.
Shape in a roll.
Wrap with wax paper and chill.
Cut in thin slices.
Bake on well floured cookie sheet at 450° for 12 minutes.
Makes 40 cookies.

title: apricot thumbprint cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add next ingredients in order given, then chill.
Use small amounts to form balls or flatten with thumb.
Make thumbprint in each and fill with very small amount of apricot jam.
Use egg white and 1/4 cup sugar, beaten together and spread over each cookie.
Bake 12 1/2 minutes in 350° oven.
Makes 2 dozen cookies.

title: amish friendship bread
directions: In a small bowl, dissolve yeast in water.

Let stand 10 minutes. In a 2-quart container glass, plastic or ceramic container, combine 1 cup flour and 1 cup sugar. Mix thoroughly or flour will lump when milk is added. Slowly stir in 1 cup milk and dissolved yeast mixture. Cover loosely and let stand at room temperature until bubbly. Consider this day 1 of the 10 day cycle. On days 2 through 4, stir starter with a spoon.

title: taco salad
directions: Blend together sour cream, cream cheese and taco seasoning mix.
Spread in pizza pan.
Top with lettuce, tomatoes and onions. Sprinkle on salsa.
Finally, sprinkle on shredded cheese and serve with tortilla chips.

title: fried rice
directions: Start by cooking Spam and vegetables in oil and butter over mild heat until done.
Next, add rice, eggs and all other ingredients.
More soy sauce may be added to suit your taste. Usual cooking time is 5 to 10 minutes.
Makes enough for 4 adults.

title: cheese veggie soup
directions: Cook potatoes and veggies in water until tender.
Add all other ingredients and simmer.

title: simple tennessee cheesecake
directions: Mix cream cheese and sugar.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Place mixture in pie crust.
Chill for half an hour.
Add topping.

title: nacho dip
directions: Combine the following to form mixture for Layer 2:
sour cream, bean dip and taco seasoning.
Stir until well blended.

title: jello cottage cheese salad
directions: Put in a large bowl the cottage cheese; sprinkle jello over cottage cheese and mix well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Ready to serve.

title: giardinara salad
directions: Use whatever amounts of each vegetable you desire.
Wash and slice them.
Cut celery on the diagonal.
Slice carrots about 1/4-inch thick.
Hot peppers to taste.
Put them in quart jars tightly.
For each quart, use 1/4 teaspoon alum melted in some vinegar and 1 teaspoon salt.
Fill jar with vinegar and cover with lid.
Keep in refrigerator.
Will keep for about 6 months.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Place crushed pineapple with juice in a large bowl.
Add pudding mix and blend thoroughly.
Fold in Cool Whip, marshmallows and pecans.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight.

title: hot hoagie sandwiches
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together. Slice bread lengthwise. Butter bread and spread with meat mixture. Cover with cheese and garnish with green peppers and olives. Broil until cheese is bubbly. Serves 6 to 8.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash, ground pepper and onion 10 minutes. Drain.
Mix egg, mayonnaise, cheese and chili peppers. Add to squash mixture. Place in casserole dish. Dot with butter and top with cracker crumbs. Bake for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: shrimp salad a la martie
directions: Combine the first five ingredients in a bowl.
Combine mayonnaise, dill weed, vinegar, salt and pepper.
Toss mayonnaise mixture with shrimp, cucumber, tomato, olive and onion mixture. Let marinate for awhile.
When ready to serve, toss with the romaine lettuce.
Enjoy!

title: grandma parmenter's strawberry dumplings
directions: Into a large mixing bowl, place butter and sugar.
Mash together with potato masher.
Add strawberries and mash again. Set aside to juice out. Combine Bisquick and water.
Make into biscuit texture.
Form into 4 equal patties. Grease one side of a 12-inch square of aluminum foil.
Place biscuits on the greased side, bring the 4 corners of foil together and seal. Place the foil package of biscuits in a blancher or steamer over simmering water.
Steam slowly for 30 minutes. Remove from heat and tip the steamed biscuits onto the strawberry mixture.
Carefully spoon berries around and over the biscuits.
Let stand for 5 minutes to allow the butter and sugar to melt into the biscuits.
Serves 4.

title: toby's sweet tea
directions: Boil tea bags on stove on high heat with 1 pint of water. When it starts to boil, turn off heat. Let set for 10 minutes. Put sugar in a gallon jug. Pour hot tea over sugar. Stir until sugar is gone.
Fill jug with cold water. Stir and serve with ice.

title: orange glazed cranberry pumpkin bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients in large bowl.
Mix remaining ingredients in another bowl.
Combine all ingredients and pour into 2 loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 65 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes, then glaze.

title: broccoli and cauliflower walnut casserole
directions: Break vegetables into flowerets.
Steam 3 to 4 minutes separately. Drain.
Combine sour cream, cheese, flour, bouillon and mustard. Spread over vegetables in casserole, a shallow baking dish.
Mix remaining ingredients and sprinkle over top. Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: california apple cake
directions: Break eggs over diced apples.
Add sugar, salt, cinnamon, oil and nuts.
Mix with a fork.
Mix flour and soda.
Add and mix well. Bake at 350° in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 55 minutes or Bundt pan for 1 hour plus.
Grease and flour pan.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Remove skin from chicken before boiling.
After chicken is completely cooked, remove from water.
Save the water for broth. Remove meat from bones and cut chicken in a dish that can be put into hot oven.
Drain liquid from peas and carrots.
Place vegetables over chicken in dish.
Mix together flour and 3/4 cup of broth until smooth.
Pour into remaining broth.
Cook over medium heat until thickened.
Pour broth over vegetables.
Bake at 400° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: cherry or apple supreme
directions: Mix oleo and cake mix
in
bowl.
Put
in
baking dish, keeping out 3/4 to 1
cup.	Pour
fruit over and sprinkle with the pecans.
Then dot top
with the cake mixture you held out. (If you
use
apple
pie
filling, sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.) Bake about 45 minutes at 350°.

title: pineapple-banana delight
directions: Mix Jell-O, boiling water and marshmallows and set aside to thicken.
Add pineapple and bananas.
Pour into large Pyrex dish.

title: cream cheese cake
directions: Mix
cake according to package directions.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch baking dish;
set aside.

title: tea cakes
directions: Cream together shortening, margarine, etc., and sugar, then add eggs, salt, milk, baking powder and vanilla.
Mix all ingredients; knead in flour.
Roll out 1/2-inch thick and cut.
Bake at 350° until light brown (10 to 15 minutes).
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into graham cracker crust or regular cooked pie shell.
Chill several hours.

title: homemade soup
directions: Cook meat in pan with water.
Boil potatoes, carrots and onions.
In separate pan, boil noodles.
When all ingredients are cooked, mix everything together.
Season as desired.

title: marshall field's cinnamon crunch muffins
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, cream the butter and margarine.
Add the sugar and cream until fluffy; blend in the eggs.
In a bowl, combine the sour cream and baking soda; set aside.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix
ingredients,
adding nuts and apples last.
Batter will be	very stiff and may have to be completed by mixing by hand. Bake in tube pan at 325° until medium brown.

title: donnas zucchini fruit bars
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Bake in oven for 35 minutes 10 x 15 pan.

title: peach cream pie
directions: Combine 3/4 cup sugar, 2 tablespoons flour and salt.
Beat in sour cream, egg and vanilla.
Add peaches.
Pour into pie pan. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Turn down heat to 350°, bake 1/2 hour.
Remove from heat.

title: japanese fruit cake(3 layers)
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add well beaten egg yolks.
Beat well. Sift baking powder with flour and add alternately with milk.
Add vanilla.
Fold in well beaten egg whites.
To 1/3 of batter, add cloves, allspice, cinnamon and raisins.
Put 3 layers into a preheated 300° oven and then set oven at 350°.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Stir all ingredients together; bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Wash broccoli and cut off flowerets.
Set flowerets aside. Peel stems and chop coarsely.
Place chopped stems in a large saucepan and cover with chicken broth.
Bring to a boil and simmer 1/2 hour.
Drain, reserving stock.
Put broccoli stems through blender with 1 cup stock.
Set puree aside.

title: hamburg and pot pie bows
directions: Put water in pan.
Add ground beef, onion, celery and onion soup.
Cook about 15 minutes.
Add cooked potatoes, cooked pot pie bows and chicken broth.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and parsley flakes.

title: french torte
directions: Combine sugar and beaten egg yolks.
Add 4 tablespoons flour, salt and baking powder. Mix remainder of flour with dates or raisins and nuts. To the batter, fold in stiffly beaten egg whites and vanilla.
Fold in dates or raisins and nuts.
Bake in greased and floured pan for 20 minutes at 375°.
While still warm, cut into squares.
Roll in granulated sugar.
Makes 24 squares.

title: salad dressing chocolate cake
directions: Beat all ingredients together for 2 minutes.
Pour into greased 9 x 13 inch pan or two round layer pans.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix well with electric mixer.
Spread onto pie plate.
Top with shredded lettuce, chopped tomatoes, peppers, olives and shredded Cheddar cheese.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: angel pie
directions: Beat egg whites until quite stiff.
Add cream of tartar and beat until stiff.
Fold in 1 cup sugar and pour into greased 10-inch pie pan.
Spread over and up the sides of pan.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 15 minutes.
Turn down heat to 250° for 45 minutes.
While the meringue is baking, stir up egg yolks and add juice and rind of lemon and the remaining sugar.
Cook in double boiler until thick.
Cool.
Whip cream and spread 1/2 of it on cooled meringue shell.
Spread lemon filling over this and top with remaining whipped cream.
Refrigerate 3 or 4 hours before serving.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients and place in large baking dish.
Top with 1 cup corn flakes and drizzle with 1/4 cup melted butter. Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Remove foil and bake another 15 minutes.

title: barbecued franks
directions: Slice hot dogs diagonally in 1-inch pieces.
Combine all ingredients except hot dogs and simmer 15 minutes.
Add hot dogs and cook slowly 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: cookie wafer tarts
directions: Mix cream cheese until smooth, then
add
sugar.
Blend well. Add beaten eggs, lemon juice and
vanilla; blend again. Place wafer of your choice in 2 1/2-inch	diameter
foil laminated bake cups;
half fill with cream
cheese mixture.
Place cups on cookie sheet.
Bake in oven for 15
minutes
at
350°. Cool.
Top with blueberry or cherry pie filling.
Refrigerate. Serves 24 or 1 person who can eat 24 tarts!

title: hearty beef 'n cheese crescent pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In large skillet brown beef, onion and green pepper; drain.
Stir in tomato sauce, beans and garlic salt. Simmer while preparing crust.
Place triangles (8) in ungreased 9-inch pie pan; press over bottom and up sides to form crust. Combine egg and 1 cup cheese.
Spread over crust.
Spoon hot meat mixture into crust.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese and paprika. Bake at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes. Cut in wedges to serve.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Combine sour dressing and mayonnaise.
Add other ingredients and mix well. Great dip for green peppers, cucumbers and cauliflower. Only 50 calories per serving.

title: butter rolls
directions: Mix together first 3 ingredients, then crumble in yeast.
Stir until dissolved.
Add eggs and vegetable oil.
Mix with spoon. Then add flour and mix by hand.
Store in refrigerator until ready to bake.

title: cheese thins
directions: Sift flour; add salt, paprika, cheese and nuts.
Add creamed butter and make into 2 rolls.
Put in refrigerator overnight. Slice and bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes, until brown.

title: corn bread fritters
directions: Mix together the cornmeal, salt, baking powder and flour.
Add the egg and enough of the milk to make a stiff batter.
Drop the batter from a spoon into deep fat and fry until golden brown, turning once.
Drain the fritters on paper towels.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together.
Place crumbled crackers on top.
Pour melted margarine over crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: foolproof fudge* * * * *
directions: To crush items (like corn flakes), place in a Ziploc bag. Seal (let out air).
Take a glass and roll back and forth over the bag.
You will have crushed flakes and no mess.

title: hash brown patties
directions: Line a greased baking dish with potatoes.
Mix soup, sour cream, butter and Cheddar cheese with mixer.
(Reserve some of cheese for top.)
Spread mixture over potatoes and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mother's devil food cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add yolks of eggs.
Add mashed sweet potatoes.
Add cocoa and nuts.
Stir well.
Add milk and dry ingredients (which have been sifted together) alternately.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Bake at 350° in two 9-inch square pans lined with wax paper for 25 to 30 minutes. Check for doneness when cake pulls away from sides of pan.
Frost with a confectioners sugar icing or cream cheese icing.

title: chocolate chip platter cookies
directions: Cream or beat together oil, butter, brown & white sugar.
Then add eggs, vanilla, and oats.
Fold in chocolate chips and frosted flakes.
Let stand awhile (even overnight in refrigerator).
Drop by teaspoonful onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 7 - 10 minutes. Makes approx. 4 dozen cookies

title: tortellini salad
directions: In a large pot of boiling salted water, cook tortellini until just tender, 8 to 10 minutes.
Drain well and allow to cool 5 minutes.
Return pasta to pot.
Add oil, vinegar, garlic, parsley and Parmesan cheese, tossing gently until well mixed.
Stir in ham, turkey, Mozzarella cheese, pea pods, carrots and bell pepper; tossing until well mixed.
Serve immediately, or cover and refrigerate until well chilled.
Serve on a bed of lettuce leaves.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Saute onion in butter until tender.
Add broth, broccoli and salt.
Cook
to
30 minutes on low heat.
Add milk, stirring constantly.
Add
a
little
water	to cornstarch and make a thick paste.
Gradually add this to soup while stirring until soup thickens.

title: crock-pot veggies
directions: Layer ingredients in crock-pot until all are used up.
Set crock-pot on high until veggies are heated.
Then reduce heat to low and simmer 3 1/2 to 4 hours.

title: tuna salad
directions: Get all the juice you can out of the tuna; then add each ingredient in order and stir.
Wah-lah!

title: old fashioned peanut brittle
directions: Melt butter or margarine in small saucepan over very low heat. Add peanuts and salt; allow to warm.
Place sugar in large, thick skillet over medium heat.
Stir continuously until sugar caramelizes into golden brown syrup.
Stir peanuts into syrup quickly.

title: mrs. fields cookies
directions: Cream together butter and both sugars.
Add eggs, vanilla, flour, oats, salt baking powder and soda; mix well.
Add chocolate chips, Hershey bar and nuts.
Put on a cookie sheet about 2 inches apart.
Bake at 375° for 6 to 8 minutes.
Yield 5 dozen cookies.

title: chili con carne(american)
directions: Cut beef into small cubes.
Melt oleo in frying pan.
Saute meat and onions in oleo until browned.
Put in kettle.
Add tomatoes, beans, celery, salt and pepper; simmer for 1 1/2 hours. Add chili powder; simmer 30 minutes more.

title: carrot ring
directions: Cream Crisco, sugar and egg yolk.
Add carrot, salt and lemon juice.
Add baking soda with water, then flour with baking powder. Mix well and add beaten egg white.
Pour into greased 6 cup mold (a Bundt cake pan).
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve hot; can be frozen, unbaked.
Serves 6; can be doubled.

title: cocoa-cola cake
directions: Mix sugar, flour and marshmallows. Bring oleo, shortening, cocoa and Coke to a boil.
Pour over dry ingredients and stir. Do not beat.
Add buttermilk, soda and eggs.
Bake in greased and floured sheet pan at 350° for about 30 to 35 minutes.

title: sangria slush
directions: Place all ingredients in blender.
Blend on high speed for 5 seconds.
Pour mixture into a 9-inch square pan and freeze. Before serving, let stand 5 minutes at room temperature.
Stir with spoon until semi-thawed.
Spoon into 8 wine glasses.
Garnish with orange slices.

title: german potato salad
directions: Cook bacon until crisp; drain (reserve 1/2 cup fat) and crumble.
Cook onion and celery in fat until just tender.
Blend in flour, sugar, salt, celery seed and pepper.
Add vinegar and water.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Add bacon and potatoes; heat thoroughly, tossing lightly so as not to break up the potato slices.
Garnish with parsley.
Can be served warm or chilled, but you taste the bacon fat a bit more when it is chilled.

title: mulled cider
directions: Combine all ingredients in large pot.
Set on stove to simmer for 20 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: seven layer bars
directions: Mix graham crackers and melted butter and pat into 9 x 13 pan. Layer the rest of the ingredients and pour Eagle Brand milk over the top. Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: easy cheese cake
directions: Combine in a bowl Cool Whip, cream cheese, and sugar.
Blend until creamy with no lumps.
Place in a graham cracker pie crust. Refrigerate for four hours.
Remove from the refrigerator and it is ready to serve.

title: rabbit stefado
directions: Brown the meat in olive oil in a Dutch oven.
Arrange onions over the meat.
Mix tomato paste and wine and pour over onions and meat.
Add bay leaves and seasonings.
Cover and simmer 2 1/2 hours until meat is tender and liquid is reduced.
Add water if needed to keep contents from scorching.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: vanilla bars
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients; mixture will be very stiff. Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan sprayed with Pam.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mush all together and roll in chopped walnuts.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Mix all together and pour into a large Pyrex pie plate or 8 x 8-inch Pyrex casserole.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes (preheat oven).

title: easy coffee cake
directions: Combine 1 1/2 cups of cake mix with yeast, flour, eggs and water.
Beat 2 minutes.
Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Spoon filling over dough.
Combine remaining cake mix and butter until crumbly.
Sprinkle over filling.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: roz's lasagna
directions: Cook lasagna pasta in boiling salted water following directions on package.
Drain, but do not rinse in cold water. Brown sausage, beef, onion and garlic.
Drain drippings.
Add tomatoes, breaking them up with wooden spoon.
Add tomato paste, basil and baking soda.
Add meat; stir well.
Cook over low heat for 40 minutes or until sauce thickens.
Preheat oven to 350°. Lightly grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Pour 3/4 cup sauce in baking dish.
Top with 1/3 of noodles.
Dot with 1/2 Ricotta and Mozzarella.
Top with more sauce; add remaining pasta.
Top with remaining sauce and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes, or until well heated.
Remove from oven and serve. Serves six.

title: pepper relish dip
directions: Chop and drain the first 5 ingredients.
Mix with small amount of Italian dressing, garlic powder, cilantro and hot sauce (to own taste).
Store refrigerated for a couple of hours before serving.

title: kyle's mexican cornbread
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and pepper.
Mix corn meal, milk, salt, creamed corn, Crisco oil, eggs and soda.
Pour corn meal mixture in iron skillet.
Add hamburger mixture.
Pour 1/2 corn meal mixture on top with Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: oatmeal refrigerator cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars together.
Add eggs and vanilla. Sift soda, salt and flour together and add to first mixture.
Add oatmeal and nuts.
Roll in wax paper and chill overnight or for several hours.
Slice and bake at 375° until brown.

title: aunt brenda's chicken and stuffing casserole
directions: Cook celery, onion and chicken until done.
Remove chicken and cut up.
Prepare stuffing mix according to package using broth with onion and celery.
Combine chicken, soup mixed with milk, stuffing mix, mushrooms and salt and pepper.
Place in casserole dish.
Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour.

title: lime mold
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Drain pineapple.
Measure pineapple liquid and add enough cold water to make 2 cups; add to gelatin.
Refrigerate gelatin until slightly thickened.
Into the whipped topping gradually beat chunks of cream cheese and beat until smooth.
Beat gelatin until frothy.
Beat in cream cheese mixture.
Fold in pineapple and nuts.
Turn into oiled 2-quart mold and refrigerate until firm.

title: aunt frances' breakfast casserole
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Put in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan. Refrigerate overnight.
Place in cold oven. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until nicely browned.
Let set for 10 minutes before serving.

title: chicken nuggets
directions: Cube chicken.
Mix cubes in egg, then coat with bread crumbs. Fry in electric fry pan, in oil, 3 to 8 minutes.

title: brownie mix cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Drop on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for about 8 to 10 minutes.

title: a peach of a cobbler
directions: Mix together the first 5 ingredients to form a batter.
Melt the two sticks of shortening and pour into the batter.
Add the peaches and juice.
Sprinkle another cup of sugar over the top and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until brown on top.

title: freezer pickles
directions: Combine salt and water.
Let set 2 hours, then drain.
Combine sugar and vinegar; stir until well dissolved.
Pour over cucumbers.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Place into freezer container and freeze.
If you heat solution, let cool before pouring over cucumbers.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown pork chops in small amount of fat.
Sprinkle uncooked rice in the bottom of a greased casserole.
Place browned chops on top of the rice and add pork drippings.
Place an onion slice and pepper slice on top of each chop.
Pour tomatoes, sauce and water over all.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: beet salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add remaining ingredients, except beets and celery.
Mix.
Chill until partially set.
Add celery and beets. Place in ring mold.
Chill until set. Serve.

title: jew's cake
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well with each addition.
Stir in flavoring and flour. Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake 1 hour at around 325°.
Do not open oven while baking!

title: orange apricot nectar
directions: Blend all ingredients until smooth.
Makes 4 servings. Contains ninety calories per drink.
Extremely high in vitamins A and C.

title: baked minestrone
directions: Cut beef into bite-size cubes.
Mix together beef, garlic, onions, salt, pepper and olive oil.
Toss together.
Put into a large heavy Dutch oven and brown in a 400° oven for 1 hour, uncovered.
Reduce heat to 350° after 1 hour.
Add broth, water, Italian herbs, chopped tomato, kidney beans, carrots and zucchini. Bake for another hour, covered, then add macaroni.
Bake for 30 minutes more, covered, or until macaroni is tender.
Serve with Parmesan cheese.

title: chocolate cherry bars
directions: Mix by hand.
Pour into 15 x 10-inch pan.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Put yeast in warm water.
Add shortening, sugar, eggs, salt and 4 cups flour. Beat until smooth. Add rest of flour. This will soften dough. Cover and refrigerate until needed.

title: sausage cheese biscuits
directions: Grate cheese in large bowl.
Mix above ingredients thoroughly with hands.
Shape into balls and bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes or until brown.
Can be frozen and reheated.

title: marinated fiddlehead ferns
directions: Wrap the coriander, fennel and peppercorns together in 2 squares of clean cheesecloth to form a bouquet garni.
In a 3 or 4-quart enamel or stainless steel saucepan, combine the water, vinegar, lemon juice, oil, celery and cheesecloth bag of seasonings and salt.
Bring to boil, then reduce heat to low. Stir in fiddleheads and simmer partially covered for 15 to 20 minutes until ferns are tender.
Remove and discard the bouquet garni.
Drain fiddleheads and celery in colander and place in salad bowl.
Cool to room temperature.

title: apricot salad
directions: Add boiling water to jellos.
Add cream cheese.
Add crushed pineapple with juice and apricots that have been lightly crushed. Mix Dream Whip as directed on box and add to jello mixture.
Let set in refrigerator.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apples in bottom of pan.
Sprinkle 1 tablespoon sugar over apples.
Combine flour, sugar, margarine and cinnamon together.
Sprinkle over apples.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: butter melts
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add remaining ingredients and beat until well blended.
Divide dough into 4 parts and roll each separately in waxed paper.
Refrigerate or freeze and bake as needed on ungreased cookie sheet at 375°, until edges are brown (or to bake immediately, drop on cookie sheet in balls and flatten with fork).

title: chip beef dip
directions: Microwave on Medium (50%) 7 to 8 minutes.
Serve warm with chips or crackers.

title: broccoli-cauliflower casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all the ingredients well. Place in a casserole dish and bake covered for 1/2 hour.
Uncover, stir, and bake uncovered for an additional 1/2 hour.

title: bessie's lime pickles
directions: Soak cucumbers in water and lime.
Mix in crock or plastic container 12 hours or overnight.
Wash 3 times until water is clean.
Soak in fresh ice water for 3 hours.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni well and drain.
After macaroni cools well, add ingredients.
Add salt, pepper and celery seed to taste.
Serves 6.

title: rich turkey gravy
directions: In medium skillet, over medium heat, stir flour into drippings.
Cook and stir until thickened and bouillon is dissolved.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Makes about 1 1/2 cups.

title: deep sea delight
directions: Cook noodles as directed on package.
Mix all ingredients in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: dressing
directions: Saute celery and onions in butter or margarine.
Remove chicken from bones.
Mix all ingredients in large mixing bowl. Put in baking dish and bake until nicely browned.

title: coconut pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add ingredients in order given.
Stir to mix.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake in preheated oven (300°) for 45 minutes.
Quick, simple and so delicious.

title: sausage squares
directions: Cook
sausage
and
onion
over
low heat until meat is browned.
Drain.
Add
cheese,
egg,
liquid hot pepper sauce, salt and parsley.
Make a dough by mixing the biscuit mix with the milk
and mayonnaise.
This makes a sticky dough.	Spread half of	the
dough
over the bottom of a well-greased 8-inch square pan.
Cover the dough with the sausage mixture.
Spread the remaining
dough
over the sausage mixture.
Bake at 350° for
25 minutes
or
until done.
(Cut into squares and serve hot.) Yields
servings.
This	is
good for breakfast or a light lunch.
Can be made in advance and frozen.

title: creamy baked chicken
directions: Arrange chicken in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish.
Top with Swiss cheese.
Combine soup and wine; stir well.
Spoon over chicken and sprinkle with stuffing mix.
Drizzle butter over crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: special tortilla dip
directions: Spread cream cheese in pie plate; add chili.
Sprinkle Mozzarella on top.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Heat in microwave for 3 minutes on High.
Serve hot with tortilla chips.

title: debbie's chocolate pie
directions: Melt margarine and chips.
Add all other ingredients.
Pour into pie shells.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: creamy pasta salad
directions: Cook and drain noodles.
Cut off 1-inch of broccoli stalk and peel remaining broccoli; cut remaining vegetables.
Combine all vegetables and noodles in a medium-large bowl.
Pour in marinade sauce from artichoke hearts or mushrooms.
Pour in both bottles of dressing.
Pour in Parmesan cheese.
Mix together well.
Cover and chill.
If desired turkey, ham or chicken would taste wonderful and make a light 1 dish meal for those hot summer nights.

title: chicken fried steak
directions: Beat egg with milk.
Season flour with salt and pepper.
Pour oil in skillet and heat to 375°.
Dredge steak in flour and dip in egg and milk mixture; dredge again in flour.
Brown meat on both sides.
Turn heat down and fry again for 5 minutes on each side. Remove from skillet and place on platter.
Cover with paper towel to keep warm.

title: molasses cake
directions: Mix the
sugar,
flour,
soda,	spices	and shortening. Blend in boiling	water;	beat eggs and stir into batter.
Add molasses. Bake in
tube
pan
in moderate oven.
Leave in pan until cool. Real good!

title: chocolate icing
directions: Combine all ingredients with the exception of vanilla.
Boil fast 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Beat until cool and creamy.
Spread on cake.
If icing begins to get stiff while spreading on cake, add a few drops of milk and beat for a minute.

title: appetizer spread
directions: Blend all ingredients together well.
Spread on crackers or small rounds of French bread and toast under the broiler until bubbly.

title: oven potatoes
directions: Cut up and arrange potatoes in oblong pan with about 1/2 cup of water in bottom of pan.
Cut up onion on top of potatoes. Drain mushrooms and arrange on top of onion.
Sprinkle with seasonings.
Arrange slices of green peppers and top with pats of butter.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Bake in 350° oven for about 45 minutes or until potatoes are tender.

title: pig pickin' cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large mixer, blend all ingredients well.
Pour into 3 round cake pans.
Bake for 20 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean when inserted.
When cool frost.

title: creamed peas
directions: Heat butter and water to boiling; add remaining ingredients except cream.
Season with salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer until peas are tender, 8 to 15 minutes.
Don't drain.
Add cream. Serves 4.

title: broccoli muffins
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients.
Add cottage cheese, broccoli and onion.
Spoon into small size muffin pans and bake in 400° oven until done, about 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: sugar-free cherry pie
directions: Cook and cool slightly.
Bake at 425° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: easy chocolate truffles
directions: Beat cream cheese; add sugar and beat well.
Add melted chocolate and vanilla.
Refrigerate.
Shape into 1-inch balls. Roll in walnuts, cocoa or coconut.
Makes 5 dozen.
Keep refrigerated.

title: ham casserole
directions: Cook macaroni noodles.
Combine all ingredients.
Pour into 2-quart casserole dish.
Top with 1 cup cheese.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: croissants toast
directions: Beat eggs, milk, sugar and vanilla in a wide shallow bowl. Add croissants, cut-side down;
let stand to coat, then turn to coat other side.
Heat 2 Tbsp. butter in a large skillet over medium-low heat.
Add croissant halves; cook until brown.
Turn and cook other side. Remove and keep warm.
Repeat with remaining butter and croissants.
Serve warm with syrup.
Makes four servings.

title: peanut chewies
directions: In large saucepan, combine sugar and corn syrup; bring to boiling.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter, stirring until melted.
Stir in cereal, coconut and peanuts.
Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper; cool thoroughly.
Do not refrigerate!!
Makes 6 to 7 dozen.

title: hamburger cupcakes
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Trim crusts off 16 to 18 slices buttered bread.
Place slices buttered side down in cupcake tins and shape in.
Fill with meat mixture (full) and bake in a 350° oven for 40 minutes.
Freeze well and are good in lunches.

title: mustard green dumplings
directions: Cook a big pot of mustard greens (tender ones) with small portions of salt meat.
Move some of the juice and set aside.
Put the excess juice in your cornbread.
Stir good.
(When making regular cornbread, leave out the baking powder, to limit the rise of the cornbread.)
Roll in balls and put on top of the greens. Do not stir.
Cook slow until cornbread is done.
Now eat. Delicious.

title: basic biscuits
directions: Cut shortening into flour until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Add milk to make a soft dough.
Turn dough onto a lightly floured surface.
Knead gently 30 seconds.
Roll or pat 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with floured biscuit cutter.
Bake in a hot 425° oven for 10 to 15 minutes or until brown.
Brush tops with butter before baking.
Yields twelve 2-inch biscuits.

title: myra's meat balls
directions: Mix all ingredients well and shape into balls.
Brown well on all sides.
Pour sauce over meat balls.
Cover and simmer at least 30 minutes, basting occasionally.
Makes 6 servings.

title: lasagna
directions: Mix together in a medium bowl Ricotta cheese, parsley, Parmesan, basil and garlic powder.
In a 7 x 12-inch baking dish, spread evenly 1/3 of spaghetti sauce.
Top with 4 uncooked noodles.
Over noodles spread 1/2 of Ricotta cheese mixture. Repeat layers.
Top second layer of Ricotta with spaghetti sauce. Sprinkle Mozzarella over top. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Let lasagna cool for 15 minutes before cutting.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Put hash browns in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix all ingredients except corn flakes and butter.
Pour over hash browns.
Top with corn flakes mixed with butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: grilled jumbo shrimp with prosciutto and basil
directions: Combine the wine, oil, lemon juice, mustard, chopped basil and peppercorns and pour over the shrimp in a shallow bowl.
Marinate in the refrigerator at least 3 hours, turning the shrimp occasionally.
Prepare hot coals for grilling the shrimp.
Remove the shrimp from the marinade; reserve the marinade.
Wrap the middle of each shrimp first with a basil leaf and then with a slice of prosciutto.
Thread 4 shrimp lengthwise, starting at the head on each of 6 metal skewers.
Grill the shrimp, basting with the reserved marinade, for several minutes on each side.
Serve immediately.

title: pull apart coffee cake
directions: Shake biscuits, sugar and 1 tsp. cinnamon in bag. Place biscuits in greased bundt pan. Boil brown sugar, 1 1/2 tsp. cinnamon and butter and pour over biscuits. Bake for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°. Glaze with 1/4 c. of milk and 1 c. confectioners sugar.

title: spaghetti bake
directions: Cook ground chuck in Dutch oven with onion and garlic until brown.
Drain ground chuck.
