Add all other ingredients except spaghetti and cheese.
Bring this to a gentle boil.
Continue boiling for 20 minutes uncovered.
Remove from heat and stir in cooked spaghetti.
Place half of mixture in 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.
Top with remaining mixture and sprinkle remaining Mozzarella cheese on top.
Bake 10 minutes (or until cheese is melted) at 375°.
Serve with Parmesan cheese.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Peel cucumber and onion; slice thin.
Put them in a small bowl and sprinkle with salt.
Put in refrigerator for 30 minutes.
Mix vinegar, sugar and pepper until sugar dissolves.
Add to the cucumbers.
Serve very cold.

title: dirt cake
directions: Mix pudding according to pkg directions, mix in the Cool Whip.
Put aside about 1 inch of crushed cookies for top.
In an 8 inch Planter line the bottom with crushed cookies.
Make layers of pudding mixture and then crushed cookies.
Topping with the crushed cookies.
Add silk flowers and a hand spade.

title: shrimp and lobster casserole
directions: Cut lobster into pieces.
Combine lobster and shrimp with next 6 ingredients and 1/2 teaspoon salt and pepper.
Spoon into 1-quart casserole dish.
Combine 1 cup bread crumbs with butter, then sprinkle onto casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: chocolate kiss cookies
directions: Beat Eagle Brand and peanut butter until smooth.
Add Bisquick and vanilla and mix.
Form 1-inch balls.
Roll in granulated sugar. Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 6 to 8 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Press chocolate kiss into center of each cookie immediately.
Remove from pan and allow to cool.

title: mrs. reba hart's pineapple cake
directions: Heat sugar and water to boil.
Pour this over layers as you stack the cake.

title: fruit cake
directions: Cream sugar and oleo; add all ingredients.
Bake in tube pan at 325° for 1 1/2 hours; cool 20 minutes in pan.

title: fresh coconut cream pie
directions: Bring 1/2 cup milk to boil.
Add sugar and cornstarch to egg yolk mixture and rest of milk.
Add this to hot milk and cook until thick in top of double boiler, stirring constantly.
Add the butter, salt and vanilla.
Pour in a prebaked and cooled pie shell.
Cool and cover with whipped cream and sprinkle with coconut.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Brown hamburger. Add vegetables. Add water and tomatoes. Bring to boil. Sprinkle in rice. Simmer at least 1 hour.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Combine the remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil, then simmer for 1 hour or until thick.

title: easy chocolate fudge
directions: Combine chocolate chips and milk; heat until chips melt and mixture is smooth.
Stir in walnuts and vanilla.
Spread into foil lined 8-inch square pan.
Chill until firm, about 2 hours.
Yields 1 1/4 pounds.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Mix condensed milk with lemon juice.
Add crushed pineapple and nuts.
Stir in whipped topping.

title: milky way cake
directions: Melt the first 3 ingredients and set aside.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs; beat well.
Add rest of ingredients.
Beat well.
Pour in melted mixture and put in 3 layers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Bottom:
Beat egg with melted oleo and add to remaining cake mix.
Press in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: banana nut loaf
directions: Prepare oven to 450°.
Line pie pan with rolled out dough. Prick dough all over with fork and cover with pie weights or snug pieces of foil.
Bake 5 minutes.
Remove foil and bake 3 to 4 minutes more, until it begins to brown.
Take from oven and reduce heat to 375°.

title: greek country salad
directions: Line a large shallow bowl with lettuce leaves.
Break the remainder of the lettuce into bite-sized pieces and place in the bowl.
Arrange tomatoes, cucumbers, radishes, cheese, sardines, olives and green onions over the lettuce.
Sprinkle with parsley. Combine oil, lemon juice, oregano, salt and pepper in a screw-top jar and shake well to mix.
Just before serving, shake salad dressing and drizzle over salad.
Toss lightly before serving.

title: coast guard chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients together. Then sift in remaining ingredients. Stir in chocolate chips. Add more flour until the dough is stiff and manageable. Roll out and cut cookies. Bake at 350° for 15 to 17 minutes.

title: rich crescent dinner rolls
directions: Scald milk; stir in sugar, salt and margarine.
Cool to lukewarm.
Measure warm water into large bowl.
Sprinkle in yeast, stir until dissolved.
Add lukewarm milk mixture, eggs and 2 cups flour.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in enough flour to make soft dough.
Turn out on floured board.
Knead for 8 to 10 minutes. Place in greased bowl and turn once.
Cover, let rise until double, 30 minutes.
Punch down.
Turn onto floured surface.
Divide dough into 3 pieces.
Roll each piece into 12-inch circles.
Cut into 12 to 16 pie shaped pieces.
Roll up tight, beginning at wide end. Seal points.
Place on greased baking sheet.
Curve to form crescents.
Cover.
Let rise until double, 30 minutes.
Bake in hot oven (400°) about 12 minutes.
Makes 36 to 48.

title: baked chicken breasts
directions: Place chicken in 9 x 13. Top each breast with slice of Swiss cheese. Spread soup over cheese. Top with slice tomato. Sprinkle stuffing mix that was mixed with margarine. Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 35 minutes. Serve with rice pilaf or mashed potatoes.

title: orange tea
directions: Boil water and sugar 15 minutes, then cool. Add the orange juice and lemon juice. Place in freezer.
When mushy, remove and beat thoroughly; refreeze.
If you used fresh squeezed oranges, scoop out the leftover pulp and serve frozen juice in shell. Very refreshing.

title: nutmeg feather cake
directions: Cream together butter and shortening; gradually add sugar, creaming until light.
Add vanilla; add eggs one at a time, beating well after each.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture; alternate with buttermilk, beating well.
Pour creamed mixture into greased and floured 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool completely in pan.

title: koulourakia(easter cookies)
directions: Cream
butter
with
sugar.
Add
yolks
and
remaining ingredients.
As
you
beat, add the baking soda with the warm milk.
By hand, roll out small pieces of dough, 5-inches long. Shape in desired shape.
Place on greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and top with 1/2 cup grated cheese. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Layer bread, then layer browned sausage and cheese in baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour mixture over bread. Cover and let set in refrigerator for at least 8 hours.
Bake at 350° uncovered for 45 minutes.

title: jello cake icing
directions: Melt butter.
Add milk just to warm.
Add dry jello.
Mix well.
Pour into mixer bowl and add powdered sugar to spreading consistency.
Beat well.

title: play dough
directions: Mix everything in a large pot.
Stir; cook over low heat.
Will become stiff and pull away from the sides of pan.
Remove from heat and cool.
Knead.
Store in plastic bags.

title: reagan's magic cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (325° for glass dish).
In 13 x 9-inch pan, melt butter.
Sprinkle with crumbs.
Pour milk evenly over crumbs.
Top evenly with remaining ingredients.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: cream cheese brownies
directions: Beat cream cheese, sugar, egg and vanilla until creamy.
Set aside.
Prepare brownie mix as directed on box.
Pour into a 13 x 9 pan that has been sprayed with Pam, except save 1/2 cup.
Spread cream cheese mixture on top of brownie mix.
Use the 1/2 cup of brownie mix to put on top of cream cheese by 1 teaspoon drops. Swirl several times with knife.

title: red beet chocolate cake
directions: Cream thoroughly sugar and eggs in a large bowl of mixer.
Add oil, beets and melted chocolate; blend well.
Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Add to beet mixture; mix well.
Pour into 2 well-greased and floured 9-inch cake pans.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool.
Ice with Creamy Chocolate Frosting.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Mix jello with boiling water and cool.
Stir in other ingredients.
Place in salad mold and refrigerate.

title: strawberry buttermilk salad
directions: Mix gelatin and pineapple in large pan.
Heat until gelatin dissolves.
(Do not boil!)
Allow to cool.
Add rest of ingredients.
Stir together.
Refrigerate in your choice of container.

title: ne-ne's christmas sausage quiche
directions: Cook sausage and crumble; drain.
Line pie crusts with sausage.
Sprinkle cheese over sausage.
Beat together
eggs, milk, salt, and sour cream.
Pour over sausage.
Bake at 350 degrees for one hour.

title: white chocolate haystacks
directions: Line a cookie sheet with wax paper; stir vanilla chips in a 2-quart saucepan over very lot heat until smooth.
Remove from heat and stir in almonds, cherries and raisins.
Drop by tablespoons onto prepared cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with coconut. Refrigerate until hard.
Store airtight.

title: dill pickles
directions: Wash cukes and put into jars.
Add garlic, hot pepper and dill.
Mix together vinegar, salt and water and boil.
Pour over cukes in jar.
Put into hot water bath for 10 minutes.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Cook water, sugar and cornstarch until clear.
Add jello.
Put in refrigerator until partly jelled.
Put 1/2 in pie crust.
Add strawberries and top with second half.
Add Cool Whip to top.

title: shortcut baked beans
directions: On top of range in a medium saucepan, combine onion, pork and beans, catsup, brown sugar, mustard and Worcestershire sauce. Cook over low heat about 15 minutes.
Top with bacon.

title: apple coffee cake
directions: Sift flour, salt and soda together; set aside.
Place apples in medium bowl.
Break eggs over apples; add oil, sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg and nuts.
Blend well.
Stir dry mixture into apple mixture; stir until moist.
(The mixture will seem dry.)
Spread into two greased 9-inch cake pans.
Bake in a 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cut in wedges.

title: cream cheese danish
directions: Preheat oven- 350 degrees. Spray a 9 x 13 baking dish. Lay 1 pkg of crescent roll on the bottom of the dish. Pinch to seal edges.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Cover the first 5 ingredients with water and let stand overnight. Drain well.
Add the remaining ingredients and cook for 30 minutes. Stir often. Seal in jars.

title: angel food cake
directions: Sift sugar and set 1 cup aside.
Combine flour, salt and remaining sugar and sift together 3 times. Beat egg whites until foamy, then beat in cream of tartar.
Continue beating until soft and fluffy.
Beat in vanilla. When satiny peaks are formed, gradually beat in remaining sugar.
Sift in a little of the flour mixture and fold to blend.
Continue until all of the mixture is incorporated.
Pour batter into clean, ungreased 10-inch tube pan. Run spatula through batter to dispel any air pockets.
Bake 45 minutes until cake springs back to touch.
Cool inverted over a bottle for several hours.
Run knife around edge to loosen, then invert cake onto plate. Serve each slice topped with fruit or hot fudge sauce.

title: chicken in sherry
directions: Season chicken with salt, pepper, sesame and celery seed; brown in very small amount of oil in hot iron skillet.
Remove from heat; add mushrooms and 1/2 cup sherry.
Cover and simmer on very low fire for about 20 to 30 minutes.
Remove chicken from skillet and make sauce in skillet with Tabasco, cream and 1/4 cup sherry.
Pour over chicken and serve immediately or put in double boiler until ready to serve.

title: company casserole
directions: Cook noodles.
Cook onion in margarine, stirring until browned at edges.
In a buttered baking dish (3 to 4-quart), spread half the noodles, then half the chicken or turkey, sprinkling lightly with pepper and seasoning salt.
Add in layers, half the onion, chili peppers, soup and cheese.
Repeat.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: old fashioned gingerbread
directions: Cream butter, eggs and sugar well.
Add syrup and spices. If you like highly spiced gingerbread, double the spices.
Add milk and flour alternately.
Bake in a loaf pan.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: american potage
directions: Brown ground beef with onion. Add soup and water. Add potatoes, carrots, salt and pepper. Cover and simmer 35 minutes. Add peas and cook 10 minutes more. This is really good!

title: sand balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together. With hands, roll into small balls or logs. Bake in slow oven for 1 hour at 350°.
Roll in confectioners sugar while warm.

title: rhubarb upside-down cake
directions: Put rhubarb in well-greased oblong cake pan.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Then sprinkle on the dry jello.
Cover with marshmallows. Then pour on the prepared cake mix.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.

title: green corn pudding(heritage)
directions: With a sharp knife, make cuts down center of kernels on each row.
Scrape cob.
Measure 1 3/4 cups corn.
Beat egg yolks until thick and lemon-colored.
Stir in corn, butter, sugar and salt. Slowly beat in milk.
Fold in egg whites.
Bake in an 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Mix well and chill.

title: honey dressing for fruit salad
directions: Mix vinegar, sugar, honey, celery seed and paprika.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and add oil gradually, beating constantly.
Chill.
Yields 2 cups.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Stir in pecans, bananas and pineapple.
Do not beat.
Grease and flour loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 or 30 minutes.
Let cool 10 minutes, remove from pans, let cool on wire rack.

title: patty's kansas city beef brisket
directions: Place brisket, liquid smoke and water in roaster pan.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours, uncovered.
Mix other ingredients and pour over brisket.
Bake 2 more hours, covered.
Baste occasionally.
Mix another recipe of sauce to serve with the sliced brisket, if desired.

title: beef tenderloin
directions: Trim tenderloin closely.
Sprinkle with dry mustard and rub surface well.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Place in shallow roasting pan.
Brush steak sauce over tenderloin.
Roast in preheated very hot oven (450°) for 30 to 40 minutes (rare) or 45 to 60 minutes (medium) being careful not to overbake.
Slice 1 to 1 1/2-inches thicker as desired.
Serve hot plain or with mushrooms and sauteed onions.

title: wine cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a Bundt pan.
Combine all ingredients in a large bowl; beat according to cake package directions.
Pour batter into pan.
Bake 45 minutes or until done.

title: unleavened bread
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Roll out on floured surface.
Cut into 6-inch circles or biscuit cutter.
Bake 20 minutes at 250°.

title: pistachio cake
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine the first five ingredients.
Beat on medium speed for 2 minutes; stir in walnuts.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13 x 2 baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until a toothpick inserted near the center comes out clean. Cool on a wire rack.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Press into a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 250° for 10 minutes; let cool.

title: banana split pudding
directions: To reserved pineapple liquid, add enough water to make 1 1/2 c. In large bowl, combine Eagle Brand milk and pudding mix. Beat well. Add pineapple. Chill 10 minutes. Fold in whipped cream. Spoon 1 1/2 c. pudding into 3-4 qt. glass serving bowl. Top with 1/3 each of the chocolate wafers, bananas and pudding. repeat layering twice, ending with pudding. Garnish with nuts and cherries if desired. Chill and keep refrigerated after serving.

title: microwave apple crisp
directions: Arrange apples in ungreased 2-quart glass casserole or square baking dish, 8 x 8 x 2-inches.
Mix remaining ingredients; sprinkle over apples.

title: super hot fajitas
directions: Marinate fajita meat in marinade overnight.
Grill meat for 20 minutes.
Serve with fried onions and tortillas.

title: everyday waffles
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Combine egg yolks and milk; stir into dry ingredients.
Stir in oil.
Fold in egg whites, leaving a few little fluffs; don't overmix.
Bake in preheated waffle baker.
Makes about 8 waffles.

title: georgia bulldog bourbon balls
directions: Cut hot dogs in bite size pieces.
Parboil 3 minutes and drain.
Mix a sauce with remaining ingredients.
Cook until sugar melts.
Add hot dog pieces.
Serve in fondue pot or chafing dish. Makes about 60.

title: molasses oatmeal bread
directions: Mix all together.
Knead.
Let rise for 3 hours.
Put in pan and let rise.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: little yellow squares
directions: Mix the cake mix, margarine and 1 egg together and pour on cookie sheet.
Mix 2 eggs, cream cheese and powdered sugar together until creamy.
Pour over first mixture on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cut into squares.
(Grease the cookie sheet and flour it.)

title: surprise corn muffins
directions: In a bowl, blend soup and eggs.
Add muffin mix, stirring until just blended (batter will be slightly lumpy). Spoon batter into 18 greased muffin cups filling about 3/4 full.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until done.
Remove from pan. Cool.

title: betty's chicken and broccoli
directions: Layer 1/2 broccoli, 1/2 chicken, 1/2 soup mixture, 1/2 bread crumbs and 1/2 cheese, then layer again.
End with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Cover with foil.

title: fantasy fudge
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients in saucepan.
Bring to boil over medium heat stirring frequently until it reaches soft ball stage (approximately 5 to 7 minutes).
Add chocolate chips stirring until melted.
Blend in marshmallow cream.
Add nuts and vanilla. Pour into buttered 9 x 13 pan.
Cool.
Cut into squares.

title: carrot copper pennies
directions: Bring mustard, Worcestershire sauce, tomato soup, oil, vinegar and salt and pepper to a boil.
Pour this mixture over the cooked carrots, raw onion and green pepper.
Serve warm or cold. Refrigerate up to two weeks.

title: orange cooler
directions: Beat whipping cream in medium bowl until stiff.
Blend juice, sugar, peel and liqueur in small bowl.
Fold mixture into whipped cream.
Spoon into parfait glasses.
Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours before serving.
Garnish with orange peel.

title: hot pepper butter
directions: Boil mixture. Mix 1 1/2 cups flour and 1 1/2 cups water. Pour flour mixture into pepper mixture "slowly." Bring to boil 5 minutes, stirring constantly. Pour into jar. Cap and turn upside down to set. Great with pretzels.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Melt butter in skillet (I use iron skillet). Spread brown sugar evenly over the butter. Place 1 slice of pineapple in center of the skillet and arrange other slices around this center slice. Place a cherry in center of each pineapple slice. Cover with the following batter.

title: chicken saltimbocca
directions: Halve chicken breasts.
Cover with plastic wrap and flatten with mallet to 5 x 5 inches.
Place slice of ham and 1/2 slice cheese on each piece of chicken.
Top with tomato and dash of sage.
Tuck in sides, roll and press to seal.
Combine crumbs, cheese and parsley.
Dip chicken in crumb mixture after dipping in oleo.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Cook hamburger in skillet until golden brown. Drain well.
Add onion and bell pepper and continue cooking until onion and bell pepper are soft. Add all other ingredients, pork and beans last. Put all in baking dish. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: dump fruit cake
directions: Sift together
the
flour,
soda and salt.
Add all the other ingredients
and
mix well.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes in a 9
x 13-inch
pan.
While
cake is still hot, frost with cream cheese frosting.

title: mexican dip
directions: Spread cream cheese in bottom of 8 x 8-inch square pan.
Put chili on top.
Sprinkle with shredded cheese.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Serve with Doritos.

title: saucy chicken and pasta dinner
directions: In a large skillet, over medium-high heat, melt 1/4 cup margarine.
Add chicken and garlic powder.
Cook, stirring occasionally for 4 minutes.
Stir in remaining margarine, mushrooms and peas.
Cook 2 minutes or until chicken is cooked through.
Stir in hot cooked noodles and cheese.
Toss and cook until cheese is melted.
Season with salt and pepper.
Serve.

title: sponge cake
directions: Mix sugar and yolks of eggs.
Beat egg whites until stiff. Add to mixture; add hot water and lastly flour, baking powder and flavoring.
Bake at 350° for about 50 minutes in tube pan.

title: fruit cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs (one at a time), vanilla, lemon, rum, 3 cups flour and blackberry wine.
Use remaining cup of flour and mix with fruit and nuts.
Add fruit and nuts to batter.

title: squash balls
directions: Grate raw squash; set aside.
Beat the egg, onion and seasonings; add to squash.
Blend a little flour at a time until stiff enough to spoon out.
Fry in hot oil until brown.

title: chess pie
directions: Stir only to mix (don't beat).
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: glazed sweet potatoes and apples
directions: Cook potatoes in jacket, in enough water to cover until tender.
Cool, peel and slice lengthwise
in
1/2-inch slices. Layer
one-half
of the potatoes in a
1/2-quart
casserole dish.
Cover with apples and top with second
layer
of
potatoes. Melt butter in a small saucepan.
Add
sugar
and water and bring to a boil.	Pour over potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until apples are tender, basting occasionally.

title: orange honey butter
directions: Beat ingredients together until mixture is light and fluffy. Store in refrigerator.

title: barbecue meat balls
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients; shape into meat balls.
Brown in skillet; drain.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Preheat oven to 275°.
Combine bourbon with hot coffee.
Melt chocolate in this mixture.
Add sugar and salt.
Combine flour, baking soda and powder and gradually beat into chocolate mixture. Do not overbeat.
Lightly mix eggs and vanilla into batter.
Pour into a buttered and floured tube pan and bake at 275° for about 1 1/2 hours.
The cake is done when a toothpick inserted comes out clean.
May frost if desired.

title: shrimp fried rice
directions: Fry shrimp in oil in deep frying pan for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Add eggs, mushrooms, salt and pepper.
Fry over medium heat for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add rice and soy sauce.
Fry for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Mix with green onion, fry for 3 minutes, stirring while frying.
Serves 6.

title: buttermilk pralines
directions: Combine sugar, buttermilk, soda and corn syrup in large, heavy saucepan.
Bring to a boil (soft ball stage).
Just before removing from heat, add pecans, margarine and vanilla.
Beat by hand with wooden spoon until mixture loses its gloss and holds its shape. This takes several minutes.
Drop in mounds on wax paper.
These firm up as they cool down.

title: crock-pot chicken and dressing
directions: Cook hen and debone. (Save broth.) Add salt, bouillon cubes and margarine. Combine cornbread, biscuits, onion, eggs, sage, pepper and soup. Add broth until mixture is thin as you desire. Refrigerate overnight. Cook in crock-pot 4 or 5 hours on high.

title: swiss steak(chicken fried steak)
directions: Put some flour on a piece of wax paper.
Put the beef on it and put flour on top of the beef.
Pound the flour into the meat with the edge of a saucer to break down the tough fibers of the meat. Turn it over and do the same.
It will grow in size.
Cut into serving size pieces.

title: mexican-style chili
directions: Saute onion, green pepper and garlic in oil for 5 minutes. Add ground beef and brown.
Drain excess fat.
Add remaining ingredients, including liquid from cans.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Add additional seasoning, if desired.
Simmer another 30 minutes or refrigerate and reheat later.

title: egg in the hole
directions: Take a small glass and press the bread's center to cut circle out.
Melt butter in pan on low heat.
Place bread in pan.
Take egg and break open in center hole.
Fry on both sides.
Makes 1 serving.

title: sticky buns
directions: Melt 1/4 cup margarine and pour into a 9 or 10-inch Bundt pan. Sprinkle in the brown sugar and pecans.
Melt remaining 1/2 cup margarine and place in bowl.
Combine sugar and cinnamon.
Roll each unbaked roll in the margarine and then in cinnamon and sugar. Arrange the balls in pan. Drizzle remaining sugar-cinnamon over rolls.
Leave out overnight, covered with a cloth.

title: banana bread
directions: In large bowl, stir together flour, sugar, baking soda and salt. In another bowl, combine eggs, bananas, oil, buttermilk and vanilla; add to flour mixture, stirring until combined. Fold in nuts. Pour into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch baking pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes or until bread tests done.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cranberry apple relish
directions: Grind cranberries, apples, oranges and lemon.
Stir in sugar or honey.
Refrigerate several hours or up to several days.

title: monkey bread
directions: Put sugar and cinnamon in plastic bag and mix well.
Cut each biscuit into 4 pieces and shape into balls.
Drop balls of dough into bag of mixture and coat well.
Spray tube or Bundt pan with Pam and drop 1/2 of dough balls into sprayed pan.
Sprinkle 1/2 nuts, then add remainder of balls and sprinkle in remaining nuts. Melt margarine with brown sugar and let almost boil.
Pour over biscuit balls.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.
Let stand 5 minutes after taking from oven.
Walnuts may be substituted for pecans.

title: el gato gordo's mexican rice
directions: Melt margarine in large skillet.
Add rice and cook until golden brown.
Add tomato sauce and cook until dry.
Add garlic salt, chicken base, chili powder and water.
Cover and steam for 20 minutes.
Add tomato, green pepper, onion and celery; steam 25 minutes longer, until rice is tender, but not dry.
Makes 8 servings.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Take crescent rolls, lay flat and pinch together.
Bake in a jelly roll pan at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Cool slightly; mix cream cheese, sour cream, mayo and Ranch dressing.
Then spread on crust.
Top with fresh vegetables.
Whatever you like best.
Serve as appetizers.

title: pear honey
directions: Cook the pears and sugar until tender, then add lemon juice and crushed pineapple.
Cook to honey consistency.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Drop on greased cookie sheet. Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: panko chicken
directions: Cut
chicken into 1-inch strips.
Whisk until thickened the Dijon
mustard,
butter
and
garlic.
This
mixture will thicken, you
may
need
to
warm in microwave.
Roll in, then chill 10 minutes, parsley,
Parmesan
cheese and bread crumbs. Lightly spray cookie sheets and place chicken on sheets.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15
minutes.
Serve
with ketchup or 4 parts mayonnaise to 1 part mustard.

title: homemade tomato soup
directions: Put into kettle chopped onions, chopped celery and chopped tomatoes.
Cook until ready to put through food mill or sieve.
To the pulp, add sugar and canning salt.
Cream butter and flour until well blended.
Add to boiling pulp and stir.
Cook until thick.
Put into canning jars, seal and process for 20 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Add heated soup.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Top with slivered almonds and Ritz cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350°
for about 30 minutes.

title: green chili-corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except chilies and cheese, together
in a
medium
bowl.
Beat
with a spoon until well mixed. Pour half of mixture into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle the chilies evenly
over
the
mixture.
Sprinkle half the cheese over	the chilies,
then
add
the
rest of the corn mixture. Sprinkle
the remaining cheese over the top.
Bake 45 minutes to	1
hour at 350°.
Bake until just set.
Do not overbake or it will be dry. Serves 4 to 5.

title: canadian bars
directions: Crust:
Melt 3/4 cup butter and 6 ounces chocolate chips.
Add 2 cups graham cracker crumbs, 1/2 cup nuts and 1 cup coconut. Press in a 9 x 13-inch pan and chill.

title: bubble bread
directions: Grease and flour pan, place frozen rolls.
Mix brown sugar and pudding mix.
Sprinkle over rolls.
Mix sugar and cinnamon and sprinkle.
Spread pecans, pour melted butter over pecans.
Place on cabinet overnight, uncovered.
Next morning, bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes, turn out on plate.

title: shake and bake(enough for 6 chickens)
directions: Stir well.
Keep in a sealed bag.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: fried apples
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Add peeled and sliced apples. Sprinkle with brown sugar and cinnamon.
Cover and cook over low heat until done, stirring occasionally.

title: sour cream sugared nuts
directions: Mix sour cream and brown sugar in medium saucepan.
Heat to 223° on a candy thermometer, stirring constantly.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Stir rapidly until mixture has coated the nuts. Spread on wax paper lined tray and separate the nuts. Cool thoroughly. Store in an airtight container.

title: potato delight
directions: Mix all together.
Pepper and salt to taste.
Place in 9 1/2 x 13 1/2-inch glass baking dish.
Sprinkle with chips.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: scallop and green bean fettuccini
directions: Cook green beans for 6 minutes, drain and rinse under cool water.
Cook fettuccini and drain.
In pan, saute scallops in 1 tablespoon butter for 3 minutes until opaque, stirring them.
Add beans and fettuccini, stirring as dinner sautes until hot enough to serve.
Melt butter.
Mix with lemon juice.
Pour over dinner and serve.

title: soy sauce chicken
directions: Combine soy sauce, water, sugar, star anise seed and ginger in a large saucepan and bring to a boil. Simmer for 15 minutes. Rinse chicken and put in pan and cook on low for 25 minutes. Turn chicken and simmer for 30 minutes or until done.
Let chicken cool slightly. Cut up into small pieces and arrange on platter.
Spoon 2 or 3 tablespoons over chicken and serve with rice. Save rest of sauce in covered jar in refrigerator for use another time.

title: sparkling dessert
directions: Dissolve jello, any flavor, in 1 cup boiling water.
Add 1 cup cold ginger ale.
Chill until thickened and add 1 cup diced canned fruit.
Chill until set.

title: lemon dessert
directions: Mix the flour, oleo and chopped pecans; press into a 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes; do not brown.

title: hot cakes
directions: Mix eggs, oil and milk together and add the dry ingredients; then fold in the egg whites.
Brush the griddle with oil and fry very slowly.

title: beef ball dip
directions: Cut beef up into small pieces.
Add chopped onion.
Mix in cream cheese.
Shape into a ball and serve with crackers or corn chips.

title: scallop chowder
directions: Fry salt pork; saute onion.
Boil potatoes in shallow water. Add margarine; mix all ingredients.
Add scallops and fish.
Add milk and bring to boil.
Turn off.
Cover and let set for 3 hours.

title: caramel pie
directions: In mixing bowl, blend cream cheese and milk.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spread half of mixture into pie crust. Drizzle half the caramel topping on top of mixture.
Repeat layers.
Freeze for several hours.

title: burger frittini
directions: Cook beef and onion until brown.
Add tomato sauce and next seven ingredients.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes or until thickened, stirring often. Squeeze liquid from spinach.

title: boone's 5 mi. blueberry pie
directions: Combine sugar and cornstarch.
Stir in water.
Add 2 cups blueberries; cook until thick.
Let cool.
Add to cooled baked pie shell after adding 2 cups uncooked berries to shell.
Top with whipped cream.

title: cherry dessert
directions: Heat first 3 ingredients together until glazed.
Cool in refrigerator; don't let it set.
Chop up.
Add next 3 ingredients to cooled mixture.
Fold in whipped cream.
Refrigerate 1 to 1 1/2 hours to set.

title: maple cream
directions: Blend milk, water, sugar and syrup.
Dissolve thoroughly. Heat slowly to boiling point.
Cook slowly so soft ball stage when tested in cold water.

title: chicken breast fillets
directions: Lightly coat chicken in flour and saute in a non-stick pan with oil until lightly browned.
Allow to continue cooking on low heat while preparing sauce.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Press cookie dough evenly into a lightly greased 12-inch pizza pan.
Prick with tines of a fork.
Bake at 375°
for 10 to 12 minutes. Cool.

title: patrician potatoes
directions: Combine cream cheese and sour cream, beating until fluffy. While beating, add hot potatoes.
Beat constantly until fluffy. Add seasoning and chives.
Spoon into baking dish.
Top with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fruitful muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Line 12 muffin cups with paper baking cups. Combine oats, flour, baking powder and cinnamon. Add combined remaining ingredients.
Mix just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Fill prepared muffin cups 3/4 full.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown. Makes 1 dozen muffins.

title: pickled carrots
directions: Cook carrots until just tender, about 12 to 15 minutes.
Cool. Mix all other ingredients together.
Put cool carrots into a container and pour other ingredients over the carrots.
Place cover on container and refrigerate overnight or until ready to serve.

title: baked beans
directions: Boil beans until they crack. Combine all other ingredient in a pan over low heat.
Pour together in oven safe pan and bake at 350 degrees for 4 hours until done.

title: hot, hot potato wedges
directions: Whisk first 5 ingredients in small bowl to blend.
Season with salt.
Arrange potatoes in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch glass baking dish (or iron skillet or casserole).
Season with salt and pepper.
Pour dressing over and toss to coat.
Marinate for 30 minutes.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Roast potatoes until crisp and brown, turning occasionally, about 1 hour.
Makes 4 servings.
Delicious with roast chicken or lamb or anything else.

title: rotel dip
directions: In a medium saucepan, place Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Dice cheese; add to tomatoes.
Simmer until cheese is completely melted.
Serve hot with chips or over baked potatoes.

title: fried apple pies
directions: Mix flour, shortening and sugar until like meal.
Add egg and milk.
Work dough until rubbery.
Refrigerate overnight.
Roll dough out thin; cut out pies, using a small saucer.
Add desired amount of applesauce to the center of each pie.
Fold in half and seal edges with a fork.
Fry in hot oil, until brown.

title: hello dollie
directions: You can also add other ingredients (coconut, M&M's, etc.).

title: monkey bread
directions: With kitchen scissors, cut the biscuits into quarters.

title: jack's cheap chicken
directions: Preheat oven
to
Pour
soup and water into pan, mix well.
Salt chicken and put into soup.
Bake at 350° until done. Serve soup as gravy over rice or potatoes.

title: dill pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers; cut in lengthwise halves.
Put in jars. Combine salt, vinegar and water; heat to boil.
Pack cucumbers into clean, hot 1-pint jars.
Add about 2 tablespoons dill seed to each jar.
Fill the pickling syrup to within 1/2 inch of jar top. Immediately adjust lids.
Process in boiling water bath for 10 minutes.
Remove from canner; complete seals unless closures are self-sealing type.
Makes 7 pints.

title: pistachio dessert
directions: Mix flour, 2 tablespoons sugar, 1 stick butter and pecans (save some of the pecans for topping).
Spread in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan for crust.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Let cool.
Mix cream cheese and 2/3 cup sugar.
Add half of 12 ounce carton Cool Whip. Spread over crust.
Combine pudding and milk.
Beat 2 minutes and spread over cream cheese mixture.
Spread remaining Cool Whip on top and sprinkle with left over pecans.

title: applesauce cookies
directions: Mix together well and drop by teaspoonfuls on cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: outrageous cookie bars(cookies)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in 13 x 9 inch baking pan in oven; remove from oven.
Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs over butter.
Stir well; press onto bottom of pan.
Pour sweetened condensed milk evenly over crumbs.
Sprinkle with morsels, coconut and nuts; press down firmly.
Bake for 25-30 minutes or until light golden brown.
Cool completely in pan on wire rack.
Cut into bars.

title: rhubarb custard pie
directions: Line pie pan with rich pastry.
Mix sugar and cornstarch and stir into well beaten egg yolks.
Fill crust with rhubarb.
Pour sugar mixture over it.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake in a 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes.
Use egg whites to make the meringue.
Cover the pie with meringue and brown in oven.

title: pickled okra
directions: Cold pack okra in about 6 pint jars.
Heat the ingredients, bring to a rolling boil.
Pour over okra and seal, hot bath for 5 minutes in holding water.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Brown sausage with onions.
Drain well.
Press 1 can crescent rolls into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer on crust:
sausage, hash browns, and Cheddar cheese.
Whip eggs; add milk, salt and pepper. Pour on top of pizza layers.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: broccoli-cauliflower salad
directions: Cut all up in bite-size pieces.

title: reuben casserole
directions: Layer corned beef, sauerkraut and cheese; top with tomatoes and Miracle Whip.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or microwave 8 minutes.

title: salad dressing(12 calories per tablespoon)
directions: Mix together and store in refrigerator.
Keeps a long time!

title: sausage pinwheels
directions: Make dough of biscuit mix and water or used canned biscuits. Roll out on floured board as thin as possible.
Spread sausage over dough.
Roll into long roll.
Chill in refrigerator until firm. Slice in about 3/4 to 1-inch slices and place on greased cookie sheet like you would biscuits.
Bake at 375° for about 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: royal holiday spiced punch
directions: In a saucepan, combine water, sugar and spices.
Bring to a boil, stirring until sugar dissolves.
Reduce heat; simmer 5 minutes.
Chill; remove spices.
To serve in punch bowl, combine all ingredients.
For garnish, float lemon cartwheel slice in punch, if desired.
Makes about 12 cups (Sixteen 6 ounce servings).

title: applesauce
directions: Arrange apple slices in 1 1/2-quart microwave baking dish. Mix sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle over apples.
Cover, cook 6 minutes.
Transfer to blender or processor and blend.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Boil sweet potatoes for 30 to 40 minutes.
Peel and beat potatoes, butter and salt with mixer.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until firm.

title: drop cookies
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Drop onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 10 to 15 minutes.
These are best if covered with chocolate or candy sprinkles before cooking.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Using a skillet, saute the onions, celery and garlic until tender, but not brown.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce, salt, sugar, Worcestershire, chili powder and Tabasco.
Blend well and simmer, uncovered, for 45 minutes.
Mix cornstarch with 1 tablespoon cold water and stir into sauce.
Cook and stir until mixture thickens and bubbles.
Add shrimp and green pepper.
Cover and simmer about 8 minutes or until shrimp is cooked.
Serve over a bed of rice. Serves 6.

title: 24 hour macaroni salad
directions: Mix vegetables with cooked macaroni. Mix vinegar and sugar very well. Then add oil, mixing well. Pour dressing over macaroni salad and mix well. Cover and refrigerate overnight, stirring occasionally.

title: jiffy corn casserole
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° until center is done and golden brown.
It will not get dry.
It will be moist like spoon cornbread.
Cook about 45 minutes to 1 hour, or until golden brown on top.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Bring first 4 ingredients to a boil on top of stove.
Turn burner down to medium for 5 minutes stirring constantly.
Remove from stove and add vanilla, peanut butter and marshmallow cream. Stir until mixed together.
Pour into buttered 9 x 9 or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Let stand several hours before cutting.

title: maggie's scalloped green peppers
directions: Grind peppers.
Cover with boiling water and boil 3 minutes. Drain.

title: seven-up pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter together.
Beat until light and fluffy. Add eggs.
Add flour and beat well.
Add lemon flavoring and 7-Up.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until finished.

title: pizza fondue
directions: Melt margarine.
Add onion and hamburger.
Cook until browned. Add seasonings and sauce.
Stir well until it starts to bubble. Add cheese by thirds.
Keep stirring.
Keep warm in a fondue pot or crock-pot.
Use garlic bread to dip.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Mix and make into oblong patties.
Brown in skillet and steam for 20 minutes.
I always add some peeled and cut up potatoes and carrots during the steaming time.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Melt oleo, water and cocoa.
Add sugar, salt, soda and eggs. Add sour cream and vanilla.
Bake in sheet pan 20 minutes at 350°. While cake is baking, make icing.

title: turkey chili
directions: Heat a large nonstick skillet over medium heat.
Add ground turkey and diced white part of scallions.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes, until turkey is no longer pink, breaking up clumps with a spoon. Stir in chili style tomatoes, frozen lima beans, vacuum-packed corn kernels and 1/2 cup water.
Simmer 15 to 17 minutes to develop flavor.
Sprinkle with scallion greens.

title: chocolate fudge(microwave cooking)
directions: In 4-quart bowl, mix sugar, milk and butter.
Cook on High for 20 to 22 minutes or until a few drops of mixture in cold water forms a soft ball (234° on candy thermometer).
(Don't leave thermometer in while cooking.)
Stir in chocolate bits and Marshmallow Creme until mixture is well blended.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Mix. Pour into 12 x 7 x 2-inch dish.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Dissolve in 1 cup hot water the Jell-O and cream cheese.
Add pineapple.
Chill until stiff.
Whip Jell-O.
Fold in 3/4 of Dream Whip as directed on box.
Top with remaining Dream Whip.
Sprinkle with nuts.

title: pineapple angel torte
directions: In a bowl, stir together pineapple and pudding mix.
Allow to stand about 5 minutes or until slightly thickened.
Whip the cream until stiff; fold into pineapple mixture.
Cut cake in 3 equal layers. Fill and frost with pineapple and whipped cream mixture. Chill at least 1 hour. Can use 1 cup whipping cream and 1 cup Cool Whip.

title: beef and rice
directions: Toast almonds in oil in heavy skillet and set aside.
Saute ground beef with chopped onions.
When browned slightly, add grated carrots, cooked rice and soy sauce.
Cook just until carrots are tender, approximately 10 minutes.
Serve with toasted almonds.
Simple but good.

title: pineapple cream cheese dip
directions: Mix and pour over 8 ounces of cream cheese.
Serve with crackers.

title: banana muffins
directions: Heat oven to
Grease bottoms only of 12 medium muffin cups or line with paper baking cups.
Beat egg slightly. Stir in remaining ingredients just until moistened. Divide batter evenly among cups. Bake until golden brown, 15 to 17 minutes.

title: quick yeast rolls
directions: Combine flour, yeast, sugar and salt.
Heat water and milk together in microwave until they are hot, but not boiling (about 3 minutes).
Heat shortening until soft or partially melted.
Fold water, milk and shortening into flour mixture.
Let rise 30 minutes.
Make into rolls and let rise again 20 minutes.
Bake at 375° for 17 minutes or until light brown.
Brush tops with melted margarine.

title: magic margarita pie
directions: Combine crumbs, margarine and sugar; press firmly up sides of slightly buttered 9-inch pie plate.
In large bowl, combine Eagle Brand, ReaLime, tequila and Triple Sec; mix well.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pour into prepared crust.
Freeze or chill until firm (4 hours in freezer or 2 hours in refrigerator).
Garnish as desired. Refrigerate or freeze leftovers.

title: lazy lasagna
directions: Cook noodles and drain.
In large bowl, toss noodles with Ricotta, Mozzarella and Parmesan cheese.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together and set aside.

title: fried catfish
directions: Season fish with salt and pepper.
Combine eggs and milk.
Dip fish into egg mixture, then roll in cornmeal to coat.
Pour oil into frying pan, filling to the halfway point; heat to 375°.
Fry fillets for 8 minutes or until first side is golden brown, then turn and cook 8 more minutes until fish flakes easily with fork. Drain fillets on paper towels and serve.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix in large container. Refrigerate over night.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Combine sugar, water and cornstarch in a saucepan and bring to a boil, stirring until thick and clear.
Cool for 10 minutes; then add package of jello.
Put strawberries in pie shell; pour mixture over it and refrigerate until set.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: colleen's fruit salad
directions: Add Jell-O to Cool Whip and mix well.
Blend in remaining ingredients.
Pour into 6 cup mold.
Chill a few hours, then enjoy.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together; pour into greased baking dish. Bake at 350° about 35 minutes or until set.
(If skim milk is used, reduce milk to 1 cup.)

title: eggnog
directions: Separate eggs.
Beat yolks until frothy. Add 2 tablespoons sugar and beat.
In a separate bowl, beat cream with 1 tablespoon sugar and 1/2 teaspoon vanilla until thick. Stir into beaten yolks. Cream mixture.
Chill 2 to 3 hours. Stir gently before serving.
Sprinkle nutmeg.

title: cracker jacks
directions: Boil the first 4 ingredients together for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; add soda and vanilla.
Pour over popped corn.
Bake in shallow pan at 250° for 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes.
Pour out. Break apart.

title: sour cream dip florentine
directions: Combine all except parsley.
Put in a bowl and sprinkle with parsley.
Chill 24 hours for better flavor.
A great vegetable dip.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine ingredients and marinate for several hours with Italian salad dressing (use whole recipe of Good Seasons salad dressing mix).
Just before serving, add 1/2 box cherry tomatoes, cut in half.
Toss lightly.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients. Add mayonnaise, vanilla and water. Stir by hand enough to mix all ingredients. Spray two 9-inch cake pans. Bake 35 minutes at 325° or until done. Allow to cool before frosting.

title: glaze for ham
directions: Mix cornstarch and sugar.
Add the other ingredients and bring to a boil.
Spread on ham.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Layer cooked chicken, tortillas and onions.
Combine soup and tomatoes.
Pour over top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° until heated through.

title: pasta salad 1
directions: Cook pasta in salty water until done.
Cut broccoli and green onions into small pieces, slice carrots thinly; cut up ham.
Run cold water over pasta to cool.
Mix pasta and vegetables in a large bowl.
In a small bowl, mix mayonnaise, sugar, and vinegar. Pour over pasta and mix thoroughly.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Boil
broccoli	5
minutes in 1/2 cup water.
Drain and place in	bottom	of
pan.
Make	topping
with 2 beaten eggs, mayonnaise, mushroom soup, onion and cheese.
Pour over top of broccoli
and
top	with
cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: texas dump cake
directions: Preheat oven at 350°.
Grease 9 x 13 baking dish.
Dump cherries with juice into baking dish.
Pour crushed pineapple over cherries. Dump box of dry cake mix over pineapple and cherries. Add pecans to top. Dot with butter. Bake 1 hour.

title: sour cream cake
directions: Mix all ingredients very well and bake at 350° until toothpick inserted into middle of cake comes out clean.

title: banana rounds
directions: Peel the bananas and slice into rounds.
Measure spices, wheat germ and honey.
Mix with yogurt and bananas.
Chill.
Serves 8 children.

title: chocolate clusters
directions: Mix morsels and milk in a saucepan and stir until morsels are melted.
May be microwaved, stirring occasionally, on High, until morsels are melted.
Remove from heat, add nuts, cereal or raisins and stir.
Drop on wax paper by teaspoon.
Cool.

title: heavenly pie
directions: Heat oven to 275°.

Sift 1 cup of the sugar with the cream of tartar. With mixer at medium speed, beat egg whites until stiff but not dry; slowly add sugar mixture until stiff and glossy. Spread mixture over the bottom and sides of a 9-inch well-greased glass pie plate.
Make the bottom thinner than the sides. Sprinkle with 2 tablespoons of coconut.
Bake for 1 hour, until light and crisp.
Toast rest of coconut.

title: frito chili pie casserole
directions: Place 2 cups Fritos corn chips in a baking dish.
Arrange chopped onions and 1/2 of grated cheese.
Pour chili over onions and cheese.
Top with remaining corn chips and grated cheese. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: tangy barbecue dip
directions: In saucepan, combine ingredients.
Mix well.
Bring to a boil, lower heat and simmer 2 minutes.
Serve hot or cold.

title: chocolate chip cookie squares
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix sugars, margarine, shortening, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Grease bottom of 9 x 12-inch oblong baking pan.
Spread all dough in pan.
Bake for approximately 25 minutes, until light brown.
Let cool; cut into squares.

title: lo-fat sugar-free lemon cheese pie
directions: Soften cream cheese to room temperature.
Bake pie crusts according to package directions if using regular pie crusts.
Set aside to cool.
Add jello to boiling water.
Stir well until thoroughly dissolved.
Add milk to pudding mix and blend well. Add jello and cream cheese to pudding mix and beat with mixer until blended.
Pour into pie crusts and refrigerate.

title: dutch apple cake
directions: Pour sugar over apples and let stand 1/2 hour.
Sift all dry ingredients, then sift again into apple bowl.
Add remaining ingredients and mix until smooth.
Spread in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in 350° preheated oven for 40 to 45 minutes. May be served with whipped cream or Cool Whip.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook broccoli, onion and celery in butter until tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into casserole dish which has been coated with cooking spray.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream
shortening
and	sugar.	Add applesauce and well beaten eggs.
Add
water.
Stir
dry ingredients together and add to mixture
by
hand.	Fold in raisins and nuts.
Bake in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: eunices good dessert
directions: Mix pretzels, margarine and 1 tablespoon sugar.
Bake about 10 minutes in 8 x 13-inch pan.
Cool.
Beat together Cool Whip, cream cheese and 1 cup sugar.
This is the second layer.

title: turkey leftover hot dish
directions: Layer ingredients in baking pan.
Bake for 1 hour.

title: hershey's triple chocolate cookies
directions: Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Cream margarine and 1 1/2 cups sugar until light and fluffy. Add eggs and vanilla.
Stir together flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt.
Stir into creamed mixture.
Cover bowl and chill overnight or at least 2 hours.
Shape into walnut-sized balls. Roll in mixture of cinnamon and sugar.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes or until light brown.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: easy-do devil's food cake
directions: Put in bowl in order given.
Do not mix until last ingredient is added.
Then beat well and bake in 350° oven.
Can be made in loaf, layer or cupcakes.

title: shrimp spread
directions: Mix and serve on crackers or small French bread slices.

title: ramaki
directions: Cut raw livers in half and soak for 4 hours in the soy sauce and bourbon, combined. Drain on paper towels. Roll the liver in brown sugar and pack the sugar on the chicken liver. Cut the bacon strips in half and lay each liver on 1/2 strip of uncooked bacon. Roll up and put a toothpick through it. Lay on a jellyroll pan, then add a little more brown sugar. Bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes, turning once or twice.

title: ice cream float
directions: Put one scoop of ice cream in a glass.
Pour soda over ice cream.
Put sprinkles on top.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch Pyrex baking dish.
Put in rice and place chicken parts on top.
Pour in water and sprinkle soup mix on top.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll in 1-inch ball and press with fork on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes on 375°.

title: scalloped sautéed with scallions
directions: On a plate combine flour, salt and pepper. Dredge your scallops in flour mix. In a large heavy skillet, heat butter and oil and saute scallops very quickly to golden brown. Move scallops with slotted spoon and put in warm serving dish. Saute scallions in same pan, but don't brown. Saute them lightly, then remove and sprinkle over scallops and keep warm. (IT IS IMPORTANT TO KEEP THEM WARM.) Pour off excess oil from pan. Add white wine. Cook down halfway. Put sauce over scallops and scallions. Serve meal with lemon wedges.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa and flour in bowl.
Heat milk to boiling. Add enough of the hot milk to mixture to beat and add egg yolks. Beat.
Pour in rest of hot milk and cook until thick.
Pour into baked pie shell.

title: pumpkin pie(2 pies)
directions: Combine filling ingredients in given order.
Pour into pie crusts.
Bake in preheated 425° oven for 15 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 350° and bake an additional 45 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool. Serve with whipping cream or ice cream.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown and drain meat.
Add onion, salt, bell pepper, tomatoes and chili.
Simmer until mixed and hot.
Add in another pot the milk and soups.
Simmer until blended.
Mix with meat mixture. Grease a 16 x 11-inch pan or dish.
Layer tortillas and meat mixture.
Cover with cheese.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: 7 layer mexican dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and seasoning mix, spread on the bottom of a 9-inch pie plate. Layer remaining ingredients over spread. Refrigerate, Serve with chips.

title: persimmon cake
directions: Set oven temperature at 350°.
Grease and flour tube pan.
Mix and cream the shortening, eggs and sugar.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to creamed mixture.
Add persimmon; beat well. Stir in nuts.
Pour into pan; bake for 1 1/2 hours.

title: three bean salad
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and drain well.
Place in large bowl.
Combine the remaining ingredients and let marinate overnight.

title: bill's lasagna
directions: In a large pan, brown onion and ground beef. Add in tomato sauce, paste and all the seasonings. Stir in 2 cans of water. Cook sauce down for approximately 30 to 45 minutes. Or you can use your own special sauce.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Soften warm water, 1 teaspoon sugar and yeast until foamy. Scald milk.
Place in a large bowl with lard, 1/2 cup sugar and salt.
Cool.
Meanwhile, proof yeast (it will be foamy).
When ready, add 1 cup of sifted flour and stir briskly.
(Wait until mixture is lukewarm.
Stir in flour, 1 cup at a time, and stir well.
Add yeast to milk mixture, remaining flour and yeast mixture.
Batter will be thick, but still stirrable.
Cover and let raise until double, about 2 hours, in a warm place.
Turn out on floured surface.
Toss to cover; divide in 2 pieces.
Roll into a rectangle.
Place in 15 x 9-inch pan.
Spread each with 1/2 cup soft butter sprinkled on 1 cup sugar.
Mix with 2 teaspoons cinnamon.
Roll up and cut up into 18 slices.
Let raise until light, about 45 minutes.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: bailey's irish cream
directions: Blend the ingredients in a blender (will fill blender).
Chill before serving or serve over ice.
Keep refrigerated.

title: acorn squash with cranberry filling
directions: Prick squash several times with fork to allow steam to escape. Microwave on High until soft when pricked with a fork, 10 to 12 minutes.
If using other than a carousel microwave, turn squash and rotate after half of the cooking time.
Let stand 5 minutes; cut in half and remove seeds.
Place in casserole dish, cut side up.

title: white chocolate party mix
directions: Pour first 5 ingredients together and pour almond bark over. Mix until well coated.
Spread onto wax paper to dry.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Place biscuits in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Let warm enough to press biscuits together to form 1 complete circle.
Cook biscuits slightly.

title: choco dipped peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven at 350°.
In large mixer bowl beat milk, peanut butter, egg and vanilla until smooth.
Add Bisquick, mix well. Chill 1 hour.
Shape into 1 inch balls.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
(Do not overbake.) Cool.
Partially dip cookies in warm melted chocolate.
Place on wax paper.
Let stand until firm, store lightly covered (room temperature).

title: chocolate chip marble squares
directions: Sift together flour, baking soda and salt.
Blend together butter, sugars, vanilla and water.
Beat in egg.
Add flour mixture; mix well.
Stir in walnuts.
Spread in a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips on top.
Place in oven at 375° for 1 minute.
Remove from oven; run a knife through dough to marbleize.
Return to oven 12 to 14 minutes.
Cool and cut.

title: brown sugar pie
directions: Beat eggs and sugar until fluffy. Add other ingredients and mix well. Bake at 350° until blade of knife comes out clean.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Separate eggs and beat whites until stiff.
Set aside.
Cream shortening and add sugar.
Add egg yolks, beating well.
Dissolve soda in buttermilk.
Add alternately with flour.
Beat well.
Add coconut, nuts and extracts.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites. Divide batter into three 9-inch cake pans.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 minutes or until done.

title: crock-pot dressing
directions: Saute onions and celery until tender in oil. Crumble bread. Add other ingredients and mix well. Pour into crock-pot. Dab butter on top and cook on high for 4 hours (or 8 hours on low).

title: cranberry shrub
directions: Combine and pour over ice cubes in large pitcher.
Stir to chill.
Serves 6.

title: twinkie cake
directions: In 13 x 9-inch pan, slice Twinkies lengthwise and lay in bottom of pan.
Mix pudding as directed, set aside.
Spoon drained pineapple over cake.
Cover with pudding.
Spoon Cool Whip over pudding to cover.
Sprinkle with nuts.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add frozen strawberries until all is thawed. Fold in Cool Whip and pour over angel food cake in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Refrigerate and serve.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook noodles in chicken broth; salt to taste.
Drain cooked noodles; add chicken, cream and soups.
Turn into lightly greased 9 x 13-inch casserole dish and cover with bread crumbs and melted margarine.
Bake 25 minutes at 350° until brown.

title: cranberry fruit relish
directions: Use knife blade in processor and add lemon and orange until lemon and orange peel is finely chopped, 3 to 4 minutes.
Add cranberries, apple and pecans.
Pulse 4 to 6 times, scraping side of processor bowl between each pulse.
Remove cranberry mixture from processor and add sugar.
Mix well and cover and chill.
This keeps well in refrigerator.
Can also use blender.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Break angel food cake in pieces. Line bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan with pieces. Mix jello and water.
Stir until dissolved.
Add frozen berries.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix cornstarch, sugar and salt.
Add the hot milk, stirring constantly.
Cook in double boiler until mixture is thick.
Cool slightly.
Pour into baked pastry shell.
Cover with meringue made from the egg whites and bake in a slow oven (250° to 300°) until a delicate brown.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cut broccoli in small bite-size pieces and lay in lightly greased pan or dish.
Mix cream of mushroom, mayonnaise and green onion.
Pour over broccoli.
Cut Velveeta in slices and lay over top of broccoli and sauce.
Mix together melted butter and crumbled Ritz crackers.
Pour over cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: sunday salad
directions: Mix jello with boiling water.
Chill until soft set.
Cream sugar and cream cheese until smooth.
Blend with jello.
Add fruit and marshmallows; mix well.
Add Cool Whip and lightly mix.
Chill until hard set.

title: lemon macaroon torte
directions: Heat oven to 350° (moderate).
Grease an oblong pan, 13 x 9 1/2 x 2-inch or two 9-inch square pans.
Mix with hand 1 package yellow cake mix, shortening, egg, water and flaked coconut. Squeeze with finger until dough is moist enough to hold together. With hand, pat out in pan.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes, until a light golden color.
Crust will still be soft when removed from oven. Cool.

title: passover mocha brownies
directions: Melt chocolate and shortening.
Let cool.
Beat 2 eggs with sugar until light.
Blend in salt and chocolate mixture.
Stir in coffee and cake meal.
Bake in a greased square 8 x 8-inch pan for 25 minutes at 325°.

title: cherry pepsi salad
directions: Put cherries, sugar and liquid in saucepan; bring to a boil. Boil 3 or 4 minutes.
Pour over Jell-O and Pepsi.
When it cools, add pineapple and pecans.
Refrigerate to set.
Serve on lettuce leaf.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake mix as directed on box.
Pour 1/2 of cake mix into greased and floured cake pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: freezer slaw
directions: Mix cabbage and salt together.
Let stand 1 hour.
Squeeze out excess moisture, then add chopped green pepper and grated carrot.

title: betty's watergate salad
directions: Mix pudding with pineapple.
Add Cool Whip.
Stir in marshmallows and pecans.

title: fettuccine alfredo
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions.
Immediately drain.
Return pasta to the hot kettle or Dutch oven.
Add Parmesan cheese, light cream or whipping cream and margarine or butter.
Toss gently until pasta is well coated.
Transfer to a warm serving dish.
Sprinkle with pepper.
Serve immediately. Makes 4 main dish servings.

title: eclair dessert
directions: Mix pudding mix and cold milk with mixer until thick.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Layer graham crackers and pudding mixture in a long dish.
Do three layers of crackers and 2 of pudding.
Let set and ice with topping.

title: beef stew casserole
directions: Salt, pepper and flour meat.
Put in casserole. Add all ingredients.
Bake 2 hours at 300°, covered, or until meat is tender. Add a little water, if needed, about 1 cup or more.
Serve over noodles cooked in chicken broth or rice.

title: cheese ball
directions: Melt Velveeta in double boiler.
When cheese has melted, add horseradish and mayonnaise.
Refrigerate or freeze 1 week before using.

title: mom's chili
directions: Fry hamburg with onion, salt and pepper; when brown and in small pieces, add beans with juice.
Add tomato soup and chili powder.
(Small amount of water may be added if it seems too dry.) Simmer for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Mix together and pour into unbaked pie shells.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.
Makes two 9-inch pies.

title: red hot cider
directions: Put cinnamon sticks and red hots into cider and let sit 2 days before serving.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: cream cheese clouds
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla at medium speed. Gradually add heavy cream; mix well.
Whip until thickened. Using back of a spoon, shape into 3 1/2-inch shells.
Place on wax paper lined cookie sheet.
Freeze 2 hours or overnight.
Fill shells with pie filling.

title: amish corn bake
directions: Mix dressing, egg yolks, flour, sugar and pepper until smooth.
Stir in corn, cheese and onions.
Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form; fold in corn mixture.
Pour into greased 9-inch square baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Makes 6 servings.

title: leg of lamb with mustard sauce
directions: Combine first five ingredients and gradually whisk in the olive oil.
About three hours before roasting time, using a pastry brush, coat lamb with sauce and let it stand at room temperature. For medium rare, roast 30 minutes per pound at 325°.
Allow it to rest about 20 minutes before carving.

title: baked tuna-stuffed potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Wash potatoes.
Rub skins all over with margarine.
Prick with fork.
Bake on oven rack 1 1/2 hours or until tender.
Meanwhile, in medium bowl, combine tuna, onion, parsley, soup, paprika, Tabasco and salt.
Toss with fork to break up tuna and to blend well.
Remove 1-inch slice from top of each potato.
Scoop out inside of potato from each slice and from potato itself, leaving a shell.
Add potato to tuna mixture, tossing to mix well.
Spoon lightly into potato shells, mounting high.
Top each with 1/2 slice cheese.
Place in shallow baking pan.
Bake 15 minutes or until filling is hot and cheese is melted.
Makes 8 servings.

title: easy chocolate cake
directions: Sift together the flour, sugar, cocoa, soda and salt.
Add oil, vanilla and water; mix well.
Place in an ungreased 8-inch square cake pan or a 12-cupcake pan.
Bake in a moderate oven at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: hot dog relish
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients; let stand overnight and drain.
I put in a little prepared mustard and horseradish and a few whole cloves and take the cloves out before canning as they turn dark. Combine vinegar, sugar, celery seed and mustard seed.
Bring the vinegar mixture to a boil; add vegetables and cook slowly for 10 minutes.
Can.

title: chinese chicken wings
directions: Mix soy sauce, catsup, honey, peeled and chopped garlic and vodka.
Mix wings in mixture in a shallow baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, basting occasionally.

title: louisiana gumbo
directions: In a large 1 1/2-quart or 8-quart pot, half fill with water; place on back burner.
In a large skillet, brown chicken wings and smoke sausage in some shortening.
When good and brown (just before), add onion, shallots, parsley, bell pepper and bay leaves. Turn over several times, then pour in large pot of water.
Add shortening to cover bottom of skillet and thaw the frozen okra until almost all of the juice is out.
May add shrimp and white onion, if desired.
Put this all in the large pot with the rest of the ingredients.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Scald milk and let cool for 3 to 5 minutes.
Mix all ingredients and pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until set.

title: oreo treat
directions: Mix 2 cups cookie crumbs, 1/4 cup sugar and oleo.
Press firm into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Refrigerate.
Beat cream cheese and 1/4 cup sugar in bowl with 1/2 of the Cool Whip.
Spread on crust.
Mix jello with 2 cups boiling water.
Let thicken.
Spoon over cream cheese and sugar mixture.
Refrigerate 3 hours.
Spread rest of Cool Whip and cookie crumbs on top.
Keep refrigerated.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer in dish in order given.
Refrigerate 4 hours or overnight.

title: squash fluff
directions: Mash squash.
Add milk, sugar, salt, pepper and beaten egg yolks.
Beat egg whites and fold in.
Put in a baking dish and dot with marshmallows.

title: sausage balls with potatoes
directions: Cook unpeeled potatoes in boiling, salted water until tender. Drain, cool, peel and slice.
Set aside.
Shape sausage into small balls.
Pour stock into a small saucepan; bring to a boil.
Add sausage balls to boiling stock.
Reduce heat to very low.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Remove from heat; keep warm.
Skim off fat.

title: unbaked fruit cake
directions: Cut up pineapple and pecans, leave cherries whole. Add crushed wafers and coconut. Melt butter and marshmallows, then add dates. Mix all together, well, may have to use hands. Pack and chill. It's good!!! Will keep in refrigerator for a long time.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Place soup, chicken, onion, eggs, Veg-All and broth in bottom of casserole dish.
Mix flour, salt, pepper and butter in a small bowl until crumbly.
Add milk and spoon over top.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: pickled fruit
directions: Drain juice from each of the fruits.
Simmer for 5 minutes with 2 to 3 teaspoons pickling spices.
Strain, pour juice over fruit and chill.

title: barbecued spicy shrimp
directions: Mix well all ingredients except shrimp.
Add shrimp. Marinate shrimp for 1 hour at room temperature.
Spear shrimp on skewers and grill 5 minutes on each side.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil vinegar, oil, water, onion, salt and pepper together and simmer for 5 minutes.
Pour over warm potatoes.
Chill.
Add mayonnaise when ready to serve.

title: hoagie sandwiches
directions: Spread open buns with spaghetti sauce (just enough to moisten).
Cover bottom halves with ham and top halves with salami.
Cover completely with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 5 minutes, then broil until cheese bubbles.
Season with pepper.

title: mother's devil's food cake(birthday cake)
directions: Cream shortening; add sugar gradually.
Beat eggs.
Mix hot water and cocoa; beat until smooth.
Then add cocoa to first mixture.
Add milk, soda and flavoring.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder and mix in with other ingredients.
Bake in moderate oven for 25 minutes.
Frost with Devil's Food Cake Icing.

title: zucchini (apple) crisp
directions: Crust:
Mix flour, 2 cups sugar and salt.
Cut in butter until pea like crumbles form.
Press 1/2 of mixture into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 5 to 8 minutes or until lightly brown.
Into remaining 1/2 crust mixture, add 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon and set aside.
Take zucchini slices and cook in lemon juice until tender.
Add 1 cup sugar, nutmeg and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Simmer 1 minute and add 1 cup of crust mix until thick.
Let cool and spread mix into pan. Sprinkle with 1/2 cup crust mix.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes on 325°.

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: Combine chocolate pieces, evaporated milk and butter in a small saucepan.
Cook over low heat until mixture is creamy and smooth.
Combine remaining ingredients; gradually stir in the chocolate mixture.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake in moderate oven (375°) for 40 minutes, or until firm.
Cool pie completely before serving.

title: pesto
directions: Chop walnuts in blender or food processor.
Add garlic gloves and mix.
Add some olive oil (about 1/4 cup).
Add half of basil and mix. Add rest of basil, oil, salt and pepper.
Mix. Fold in the cheese.
Pesto!
Fold in 1 pound of pasta.

title: irish beef stew
directions: Coat beef with flour.
Heat oil in Dutch oven.
Brown beef and onions, slowly turning often to brown evenly.
Add wine, water, bouillon cubes and all seasonings.
Cover; simmer 2 1/2 hours or until tender.
During last half hour, add frozen stewed vegetables.
Bring stew to a boil; reduce heat.
Simmer slowly until vegetables and meat are tender.

title: ham, muffin and cheese
directions: Cook rice according to package directions.
Place approximately 2 ounces of ham and slice of tomato on toasted muffin.
Mound 1/4 cup rice on tomato and cover with slice of cheese.
Heat and melt cheese in broiler.

title: ugly cookies
directions: Beat the 4 eggs.
Add brown sugar.
Slowly add the Bisquick, coconut, chopped nuts and the chocolate chips.
Mix well.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour batter in and bake for 30 minutes in 400° oven.

title: cheese spread
directions: Mix together.
Make into ball and refrigerate.
Great served with Ritz crackers and grapes.

title: gourmet dressing
directions: Soften gelatin in 1/2 cup tomato juice; bring to a boil, stirring to dissolve gelatin.
Add salad dressing mix, vinegar and remaining tomato juice.
Blend thoroughly.
Chill.
Stir before serving.

title: butterscotch cake
directions: Cook pudding mix with milk according to package directions. Add hot pudding to cake mix in bowl. Mix well. Pour into greased and floured pan. Sprinkle with butterscotch chips and pecans. Bake for 30 minutes or until done.

title: creamy baked chicken breasts
directions: Arrange chicken breasts in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with cheese.
Combine soup and water/wine; spoon over cheese.
Sprinkle crushed stuffing over top.
Drizzle top with magarine.
Bake 45 to 55 minutes at 350°.

title: pancake syrup
directions: Combine all and cook slowly for 10 minutes.
Makes 1 1/2 quarts.
This is better than any bought syrup.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together.
Add other ingredients. Bake at 375° for approximately 1 hour.

title: dee's lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Add spaghetti sauce and spices; simmer while lasagna noodles are cooking.
Cook noodles according to package directions.
Layer 1/3 of noodles, 1/3 of the spaghetti sauce, 1/3 of all three cheeses, beginning with cottage cheese and ending with Mozzarella.
Repeat twice.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix cake mix, Jell-O, water, and oil.
Add eggs one at a time and beat after each. Add berries.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Spread icing on top of cake.

title: reuben chowder
directions: In large saucepan, combine milk, soup and cheese.
Cook until cheese is melted.
Add sauerkraut, cover and simmer 10 minutes. Add corned beef and heat for 10 minutes.
Serve with toasted rye bread.
Makes 4 - 6 servings.

title: haystacks
directions: Melt chips over low heat or in microwave.
Stir in peanuts. Then gently stir in noodles, a few handfuls at a time, until they are coated.
Drop by spoonful onto wax paper; chill in refrigerator.

title: cheese chilies cornbread
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Whisk together eggs, yogurt and butter in medium bowl.
Add dry ingredients and mix until well blended. Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into greased 10-inch heavy skillet and bake 40 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Place in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Mix chips and cheese.
Sprinkle on top.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 30 minutes or heated.
Yields 6 servings.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Join the crescent rolls on an ungreased pizza pan to make crust.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool.
Combine the cream cheese, Miracle Whip, dill weed and garlic powder.
Spread on cooled crust.
Sprinkle with finely chopped broccoli, cauliflower and shredded carrots.
Sprinkle with shredded sharp Cheddar cheese and Parmesan cheese.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix and cook in deep fat until golden brown.
Can be dipped with spoon or poured from plastic bag.
Makes about 24.

title: apple pandowdy
directions: Cream together the butter and sugar.
Add well-beaten egg. Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture.
Fold in apples and nuts. Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: fresh peach pie
directions: Combine
sugar,
cornstarch and 7-Up in saucepan.
Cook until thick.
Add gelatin and mix well.
Arrange peach slices in
pie shells.
Pour gelatin mixture over peaches;
refrigerate.
Top with whipped topping when ready to serve.

title: ziti with broccoli
directions: Cook ziti as package directs.
Saute mushrooms in butter for 5 minutes.
Combine them with cream, broccoli and basil.
Cook about 5 minutes.
Add ziti, salt and pepper, continuing to cook a few minutes longer.
Remove from heat; add Parmesan cheese and mix well.
Serves 6.

title: cheese pie
directions: Mix to ball.
Spread in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350°.

title: confetti rice
directions: In a large skillet, saut first 6 ingredients in olive oil until golden. Stir in the rice and dot with butter.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Tear angel food cake in pieces.
Place in 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Mix pudding, milk and ice cream.
Pour on top of cake.
Set in refrigerator.

title: pork and apple pie
directions: Cook bacon in a 12-inch skillet until slightly crisp; transfer to paper towel.
Reserve 2 tablespoons of the drippings, then add the pork.
Brown on all sides (10 minutes), remove and set aside. Preheat oven to 350°.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly. Remove from heat.
Add pork and bacon.
Spoon mixture into 9-inch pan.
Top with pie crust.
Make slits for steam to escape.
Bake 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Lightly cover crust with foil if crust becomes too brown.

title: parisienne chicken
directions: Combine sour cream, mushroom soup and sherry and mix.
Place chicken in baking dish.
Pour soup mixture over chicken.
Bake in a 375° oven until chicken is well done.
This makes chicken with gravy and can be served over rice or noodles.

title: tanner's quiche(serves 80)
directions: Trim and butter the bread.
Line pans with bread butter side down.
Crisp fry bacon and them crumble.
Cook chorizo and drain off fat and oil.
Drain on paper towel.
Layer cheese, and bacon/chorizo over bread.
Beat eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour over mixture into each pan.
Let stand overnight.
Bake the next morning at 350° for one hour.
It may take longer to cook if not a room temperature when placed in the oven.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Cook onion in butter in frying pan.
Add meat; cook until done.

title: ario con polo chicken puerto rico
directions: Brown in pan; sprinkle with paprika while frying.
Set chicken aside.

title: milk chocolate mini cookies
directions: In medium bowl combine flour, baking powder, and salt; set aside.
In a small heavy saucepan or double boiler, heat the chocolate over low heat until melted, stirring constantly.
Set aside.
In a medium mixing bowl beat butter with electric mixer on medium speed for 30 seconds.
Beat in sugar until fluffy.
Beat in melted chocolate, egg, and vanilla until combined.
Gradually beat in the flour mixture.
Divide dough into 4 equal portions.
Wrap each portion in plastic wrap and chill in freezer for 20 to 30 minutes (or in refrigerator for 1 hour) until firm enough to handle.

title: salmon spread
directions: Drain salmon, reserving 2 teaspoons liquid.
Remove skin and bones.
Mix with other ingredients.
Shape into a ball and refrigerate overnight.

title: pumpkin gingersnap pie
directions: Beat half and half and pudding mix with a whisk.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Fold in topping and remaining ingredients.
Spoon into crust.
Freeze until firm.
Let stand at room temperature 10 minutes before serving.
Store in freezer.

title: microwave party mix
directions: In large bowl, melt margarine on High 1 minute.
Stir in seasoned salt and Worcestershire sauce.
Add cereal and nuts.
Mix until all pieces are covered.
Microwave on High 6 to 8 minutes, stirring every 2 minutes.
Cool.
Store in covered container.

title: five hour stew
directions: Mix all ingredients together; don't stir.
Can put biscuits on top, if you like.
Can be done in crock-pot.

title: fresh fruit ambrosia
directions: Combine the orange juice, club soda and banana in a blender and puree until smooth.
Pour over the fresh fruit mixture. Sprinkle with the nutmeg and cardamon.
